B040C001V001	40	1	1	THE ancestral line of Jesus Christ, son of David, son of Abraham:
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham was the father of Isaac; Isaac was the father of Jacob; Jacob was the father of Judah and his brothers;
B040C001V003	40	1	3	Judah was the father of Perez and Zerah 
B040C001V004	40	1	4	Ram was the father of Amminadab; Amminadab was the father of Nahshon; Nahshon was the father of Salmon;
B040C001V005	40	1	5	Salmon was the father of Boaz 
B040C001V006	40	1	6	Jesse was the father of David the King. David was the father of Solomon 
B040C001V007	40	1	7	Solomon was the father of Rehoboam; Rehoboam was the father of Abijah; Abijah was the father of Asa;
B040C001V008	40	1	8	Asa was the father of Jehoshaphat; Jehoshaphat was the father of Joram; Joram was the father of Uzziah;
B040C001V009	40	1	9	Uzziah was the father of Jotham; Jotham was the father of Ahaz; Ahaz was the father of Hezekiah;
B040C001V010	40	1	10	Hezekiah was the father of Manasseh; Manasseh was the father of Amon; Amon was the father of Josiah;
B040C001V011	40	1	11	Josiah was the father of Jechoniah and his brothers at the time of the Babylonian exile.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	After the Babylonian exile, Jechoniah was the father of Shealtiel; Shealtiel was the father of Zerubbabel;
B040C001V013	40	1	13	Zerubbabel was the father of Abiud; Abiud was the father of Eliakim; Eliakim was the father of Azor;
B040C001V014	40	1	14	Azor was the father of Sadoc; Sadoc was the father of Achim; Achim was the father of Eliud;
B040C001V015	40	1	15	Eliud was the father of Eleazar; Eleazar was the father of Matthan; Matthan was the father of Jacob;
B040C001V016	40	1	16	Jacob was the father of Joseph the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	So there were in all fourteen generations from Abraham to David, and fourteen generations from David to the Babylonian exile, and fourteen generations from the Babylonian exile to the Christ.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	The birth of Jesus was in this way: His mother Mary had been betrothed to Joseph, but before they came together she was found to be with child by the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	Joseph, her husband, being an upright man, and yet not willing to make her a public example, resolved to dismiss her privately.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	But while he was thinking this over, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream and said, "Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary as your wife, for what has been conceived in her is of the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	She will bear a son and you shall call his name Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins."
B040C001V022	40	1	22	All this happened in fulfillment of what the Lord had spoken through the prophet:
B040C001V023	40	1	23	"Behold the virgin will conceive and will bear a son, and they will call his name Immanuel" 
B040C001V024	40	1	24	When Joseph awoke from sleep, he did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him, and took his wife to his home.
B040C001V025	40	1	25	But he did not live with her as a husband until she had borne a son. He called his name Jesus.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	AFTER Jesus had been born in Bethlehem, in Judaea, in the days of Herod the King, wise men from the East arrived at Jerusalem,
B040C002V002	40	2	2	saying, "Where is he who has been born King of the Jews? For we saw his star in the East and have come to do homage to him."
B040C002V003	40	2	3	When King Herod heard it, he was disturbed, and so was all Jerusalem.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	Then he called together all the high priests and scribes of the people and inquired of them where the Christ was to be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	They said to him, "In Bethlehem, in Juda. For so it was written by the prophet,
B040C002V006	40	2	6	'And thou, Bethlehem, land of Judah, art by no means least among the leaders of Judah; for from thee will come a leader who will shepherd my people Israel.' "
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod secretly summoned the wise men and learned from them exactly the time of the star's appearance,
B040C002V008	40	2	8	and as he sent them to Bethlehem he said, "Go and make careful inquiries about the child, and when you have found him bring me word, so that I too may come and do homage to him."
B040C002V009	40	2	9	After hearing the king, they journeyed on, and the star which they had seen in the East went before them until it came and stood over where the child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	When they saw the star, they were very joyful.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	They entered the house and saw the child with Mary his mother, and they fell down and did him homage. Then they opened their treasures and presented to him gifts, gold and frankincense and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	After this they were warned in a dream not to return to Herod, and so went by another mad back to their own country.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	After they had gone, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph and said, "Rise up, and take the child and his mother and flee into Egypt, and be there until I tell you, for Herod will search for the child in order to kill him."
B040C002V014	40	2	14	So Joseph rose up, and took the child and his mother in the night and went away to Egypt,
B040C002V015	40	2	15	and was there until the death of Herod, in order that the word of the Lord spoken through the prophet might be fulfilled, "Out of Egypt I called my Son."
B040C002V016	40	2	16	Then Herod, seeing that he had been outwitted by the wise men, became furious, and sent out and killed all the boy babies two years old and under in Bethlehem and all its neighborhood, guided by the date which he had carefully learned from the wise men.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then was fulfilled what was spoken through Jeremiah the prophet when he said,
B040C002V018	40	2	18	"A voice was heard in Ramah, wailing and bitter lamentation, Rachel weeping for her children, and she would not be comforted because they are not."
B040C002V019	40	2	19	But after Herod had died, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt
B040C002V020	40	2	20	and said, "Arise, and take the child and his mother and go into the land of Israel, for they are dead who sought the child's life."
B040C002V021	40	2	21	So he arose, and took the child and his mother and came into the land of Israel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	But when he heard that Archelaus was reigning over Judaea in place of his father Herod, he was afraid to go there, and being directed in a dream he went away to the region of Galilee
B040C002V023	40	2	23	and settled in a town called Nazareth, so that what had been spoken through the prophets might be fulfilled, "He will be called a Nazarene."
B040C003V001	40	3	1	IN those days John the Baptist came preaching in the wild part of Judaea
B040C003V002	40	3	2	and saying, "Repent; for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.
B040C003V003	40	3	3	For this is he who was foretold through Isaiah the prophet when he said: 'The voice of one crying aloud in the wilderness, Make ready the way of the Lord, make straight his paths.' "
B040C003V004	40	3	4	This John had his clothing of camel's hair and wore a leather belt around his waist, and his food was locusts and wild honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then went out to him Jerusalem and all Judaea and all the neighborhood of the Jordan
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and were baptized by him in the Jordan River, confessing their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	When he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming for baptism, he said, "Brood of vipers, who directed you to flee from the coming wrath?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Produce fruit fitting for a change of heart,
B040C003V009	40	3	9	and do not think of saying to yourselves, 'We have Abraham for our father,' for I tell you God is able out of these stones to raise up children for Abraham.
B040C003V010	40	3	10	Now the axe is lying at the root of the trees. Every tree that does not yield good fruit will be cut down and cast into the fire.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I baptize you with water for a change of heart, but he who is coming after me is more powerful than I; I am not worthy to carry his shoes; he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	He has his fan in his hand and will thoroughly clean his threshing-floor. He will gather his grain into his storehouse, but the chaff he will burn with fire unquenchable."
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then Jesus came from Galilee to the Jordan to John to be baptized by him.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But John opposed him, saying, "I have need to be baptized by you, and do you come to me?"
B040C003V015	40	3	15	Jesus replied, 
B040C003V016	40	3	16	Jesus, as soon as he was baptized, went up from the water, and the heavens were opened and he saw the Spirit of God descending as a dove and coming upon him.
B040C003V017	40	3	17	A voice from the heavens said, "This is my Son, the beloved in whom I delight."
B040C004V001	40	4	1	THEN Jesus was led by the Spirit up into the wild country to be tempted by the Devil.
B040C004V002	40	4	2	After he had fasted forty days and forty nights he was hungry.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	Then the tempter came and said to him, "If you are the Son of God, tell these stones to turn into loaves of bread."
B040C004V004	40	4	4	But he answered, 
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then the Devil took him with him to the holy city and placed him on the top of the temple
B040C004V006	40	4	6	and said to him, "If you are the Son of God, throw yourself down; for it is written, 'To his angels he will give charge of you, and on their hands they will bear you lest you strike your foot against a stone.' "
B040C004V007	40	4	7	Jesus said to him, 
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Again the Devil took him with him to a very high mountain and showed him all the kingdoms of the world and their glory,
B040C004V009	40	4	9	and said to him, "All these things I will give you if you will fall down and do homage to me."
B040C004V010	40	4	10	Jesus said to him, 
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then the Devil left him, and angels came and waited upon him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	When Jesus heard that John had been betrayed, he went away into Galilee.
B040C004V013	40	4	13	Leaving Nazareth, he came and lived in Capernaum on the lake shore on the borders of Zebulun and Naphtali,
B040C004V014	40	4	14	so that the word spoken by the prophet Isaiah might be fulfilled:
B040C004V015	40	4	15	"Land of Zebulun and land of Naphtali, road to the sea, country beyond the Jordan, Galilee of the Gentiles,
B040C004V016	40	4	16	the people that sat in darkness saw a great light and upon those sitting in the land and shadow of death light dawned."
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time Jesus began to proclaim and say, 
B040C004V018	40	4	18	As he was walking along the shore of the lake of Galilee, he saw two brothers, Simon who is called Peter, and Andrew his brother, casting a net into the lake, for they were fishermen;
B040C004V019	40	4	19	and he said to them, 
B040C004V020	40	4	20	They at once left the nets and followed him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	Going on from there, he saw two other brothers \'97 James the son of Zebedee and John his brother \'97 in their boat with Zebedee their father, mending their nets; and he called them.
B040C004V022	40	4	22	They at once left the boat and their father and followed him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	Jesus went around through the whole of Galilee, teaching in the synagogues and proclaiming the good news of the Kingdom, and healing every disease and every infirmity among the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	His fame spread out into all Syria, and they brought to him all who were sick with various diseases and those suffering from acute pain, demoniacs, lunatics, and paralytics, and he healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	Great crowds followed him from Galilee and Decapolis and Jerusalem and Judaea and from beyond the Jordan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	SEEING the crowds, he went up on the mountain, and when he had seated himself his disciples came to him.
B040C005V002	40	5	2	He opened his mouth and taught them, saying:
