B040C008V001	40	8	1	WHEN Jesus had come down from the mountain, great crowds followed him.
B040C008V002	40	8	2	And a leper came up and bowed before him, and said, "Sir, if you have the will, you have power to make me clean."
B040C008V003	40	8	3	Jesus stretched out his hand and touched him and said, 
B040C008V004	40	8	4	Jesus said to him, 
B040C008V005	40	8	5	When Jesus had entered Capernaum there came to him a Centurion who implored his help.
B040C008V006	40	8	6	"Sir," he said, "my servant lies in my house a paralytic, in great distress."
B040C008V007	40	8	7	Jesus said to him, 
B040C008V008	40	8	8	The Centurion answered, "Sir, I am not worthy to have you come under my roof; but just speak the word and my servant will be cured.
B040C008V009	40	8	9	For I am a man, \'97 under authority, \'97 with soldiers under me, and I say to this one, 'Go,' and he goes, and to another, 'Come,' and he comes, and to my slave, 'Do this,' and he does it."
B040C008V010	40	8	10	When Jesus heard this, he was astonished and said, 
B040C008V011	40	8	11	
        
B040C008V012	40	8	12	
        
B040C008V013	40	8	13	Then Jesus said to the Centurion, 
B040C008V014	40	8	14	When Jesus entered the house of Peter, he saw his wife's mother lying sick with fever.
B040C008V015	40	8	15	He touched her hand and the fever left her. Then she arose and waited upon him.
B040C008V016	40	8	16	When evening came, they brought to him many demoniacs and he cast out the spirits by a word, and all their sick he healed.
B040C008V017	40	8	17	This was in order to fulfill what was spoken through Isaiah the prophet, "He took our weaknesses and bore away our diseases."
B040C008V018	40	8	18	When Jesus saw a crowd around him, he gave directions to go over to the other side of the lake.
B040C008V019	40	8	19	Then a certain scribe came to him and said, "Teacher, I will follow you wherever you go."
B040C008V020	40	8	20	Jesus said to him, 
B040C008V021	40	8	21	Another of his disciples said to him, "Sir, let me first go and bury my father."
B040C008V022	40	8	22	But Jesus said to him, 
B040C008V023	40	8	23	Then he got into the boat and his disciples followed him.
B040C008V024	40	8	24	Soon a great storm broke on the lake so that the boat was hidden under the waves; but he was sleeping.
B040C008V025	40	8	25	His disciples came to him and woke him and said, "Master, save us. We are going down."
B040C008V026	40	8	26	But he said, 
B040C008V027	40	8	27	The men were astonished and said, "What sort of a person is this, whom even the winds and the lake obey?"
B040C008V028	40	8	28	When he arrived at the other side, the country of the Gadarenes, there met him two demoniacs coming out of the tombs. They were very fierce, so that no one was able to pass along that road.
B040C008V029	40	8	29	Suddenly they shouted, "Son of God, what have you to do with us? Have you come here to torment us before the time?"
B040C008V030	40	8	30	There was far off from them a herd of many swine feeding.
B040C008V031	40	8	31	The demons begged him, "If you cast us out, send us into the herd of swine."
B040C008V032	40	8	32	He said to them, 
B040C008V033	40	8	33	The herdsmen fled and went away to the town and told everything, including what had happened to the demoniacs.
B040C008V034	40	8	34	Then at once all the town came out to meet Jesus, and when they saw him they begged him to depart from their neighborhood.
