B040C009V008	40	9	8	The crowds that saw it were astonished and gave glory to God, who had given such power to men.
B040C009V009	40	9	9	As Jesus was passing along from there, he saw a man named Matthew sitting at the tax office. Jesus said to him, 
B040C009V010	40	9	10	It happened that, while he was reclining at table in the house, many tax collectors and sinners came in and reclined at the table with Jesus and his disciples.
B040C009V011	40	9	11	When the Pharisees saw it, they said to his disciples, "Why does your teacher eat with tax collectors and sinners?"
B040C009V012	40	9	12	Jesus heard it and said, 
B040C009V013	40	9	13	
        
B040C009V014	40	9	14	Then the disciples of John came to Jesus and said, "Why are we and the Pharisees fasting while your disciples are not fasting?"
B040C009V015	40	9	15	He said, 
B040C009V016	40	9	16	
        
B040C009V017	40	9	17	
        
B040C009V018	40	9	18	While Jesus was talking to them, a synagogue Director came and bowed down before him and said, "My daughter has just died; but come and lay your hand upon her and she will live."
B040C009V019	40	9	19	Jesus rose and followed him, and so did his disciples.
B040C009V020	40	9	20	Suddenly a woman who had been suffering for twelve years from hemorrhage came up behind him and touched the tassel of his cloak.
B040C009V021	40	9	21	For she said to herself, "If I touch only his cloak, I shall be healed."
B040C009V022	40	9	22	But Jesus turned and, seeing her, said, 
B040C009V023	40	9	23	Jesus entered the house of the Director and saw the flute-players and the crowd that was noisily lamenting, and he said,
B040C009V024	40	9	24	
        
B040C009V025	40	9	25	But after the crowd had been turned out, he went in and took hold of her hand and the girl rose up.
B040C009V026	40	9	26	The report of this spread through all that country.
B040C009V027	40	9	27	As Jesus was going along from there, two blind men followed him, calling out, "Have pity on us, Son of David."
B040C009V028	40	9	28	After he had entered the house, these blind men came to him. Jesus said to them, 
B040C009V029	40	9	29	Then he touched their eyes and said, 
B040C009V030	40	9	30	And their eyes were opened. Jesus sternly commanded them, 
B040C009V031	40	9	31	But they went out and spread his fame through all that country.
B040C009V032	40	9	32	As they were going out, a dumb man who was also a demoniac was brought to him.
