B041C016V001	41	16	1	WHEN the Sabbath had passed, Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James, and Salome bought perfumes to go and anoint him.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	Very early in the morning of the first day of the week they came to the tomb. The sun had risen.
B041C016V003	41	16	3	They were saying to one another, "Who will roll away the stone from the door of the tomb for us?"
B041C016V004	41	16	4	But when they looked they saw that the stone had been rolled away. It was very large.
B041C016V005	41	16	5	Entering the tomb, they saw a young man sitting on the right side dressed in a white robe, and they were frightened.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	But he said to them, "Do not be frightened. You are looking for Jesus the Nazarene who was crucified. He has risen. He is not here. This is the place where they laid him.
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go tell his disciples and Peter, He has gone before you into Galilee. There you will see him, as he told you."
B041C016V008	41	16	8	The women came out and fled from the tomb, for trembling and amazement seized them. They told nothing to any one, they were so frightened.
