B042C001V001	42	1	1	INASMUCH as many have taken in hand to draw up a narrative of those facts which are firmly believed among us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	just as those who from the beginning were eye-witnesses and who became bearers of the message handed them down to us;
B042C001V003	42	1	3	it has seemed good to me also \'97 since I have followed everything from the beginning accurately \'97 to write a consecutive account for you, most excellent Theophilus,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	so that you may know the exact truth in regard to the matters which you have been taught by word of mouth.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	There was in the days of Herod, King of Judaea, a certain priest by the name of Zacharias, of the course of Abijah. His wife was of the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	They were both righteous before God, walking in all the commandments and regulations of the Lord blameless.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	But they had no child, for Elizabeth was barren, and they were both advanced in years.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	It happened that as Zacharias was performing his priestly duties before God in the order of his course,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	according to the custom of the priesthood, it fell to him to enter the Temple of the Lord and offer the incense.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	All the congregation of people was in prayer outside, at the hour of incense.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	There appeared to him an angel of the Lord, standing at the right side of the altar of incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	Zacharias, on seeing him, was alarmed and fear fell upon him.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said to him, "Do not fear, Zacharias, for your prayer has been heard; and your wife Elizabeth will bear a son, and you will call his name John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	You will have joy and gladness and many will rejoice at his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he will be great before the Lord. He will not drink wine or strong drink. He will be full of the Holy Spirit even from his birth,
B042C001V016	42	1	16	and many of the sons of Israel will he turn to the Lord their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	He will go before him in the spirit and power of Elijah, to turn the hearts of fathers to their children and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous, to make ready for the Lord a people prepared for him."
B042C001V018	42	1	18	Zacharias said to the angel, "By what proof shall I know this? For I am an old man, and my wife is advanced in years."
B042C001V019	42	1	19	The angel answered, "I am Gabriel, who stands before the face of God, and I have been sent to speak to you and to give you this good news.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	And now you will be silent and unable to speak until the day that this comes to pass, because you have not believed my words, which will be fulfilled in their time."
B042C001V021	42	1	21	The people were waiting for Zacharias and wondering at his staying so long in the Temple.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	But when he came out, he could not speak to them, and they perceived that he had seen a vision in the Temple. He kept making signs to them and remained dumb.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	When the days of his priestly service were finished, he went away to his home.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	After these days Elizabeth his wife conceived and hid herself five months, saying,
B042C001V025	42	1	25	"So has the Lord done for me in the days in which he has looked upon me to take away my reproach among men."
B042C001V026	42	1	26	In the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God to a city of Galilee named Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	to a virgin betrothed to a man named Joseph, a descendant of David. The name of the virgin was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	The angel entered and said to her, "Hail, favored one, the Lord is with you!"
B042C001V029	42	1	29	But she was alarmed at his words, and wondered what such a greeting could mean.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	The angel said to her, "Do not fear, Mary; for you have found favor with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	You will conceive in your womb and will bear a son, and you must call his name Jesus.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	He will be great and will be called the Son of the Highest, and the Lord God will give him the throne of his father David.
B042C001V033	42	1	33	He will be king over the house of Jacob through the ages, and of his kingdom there will be no end."
B042C001V034	42	1	34	But Mary said to the angel, "How can this be, since I am not united to a man?"
B042C001V035	42	1	35	The angel replied, "The Holy Spirit will come upon you and the power of the Highest will overshadow you. For that reason the child that is begotten will be called holy, Son of God.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And, indeed, Elizabeth your relative, even she, has conceived a son, in her old age, and this is the sixth month with her who was called barren.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	For "no word that comes from God will fail."
B042C001V038	42	1	38	Mary said, "Here I am, the Lord's handmaid. Let it be to me according to your word." Then the angel left her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	In those days Mary arose and went with haste into the hill-country to a city of Judah,
B042C001V040	42	1	40	and entered the house of Zacharias and greeted Elizabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	When Elizabeth heard Mary's greeting, the babe leapt in her womb, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit
B042C001V042	42	1	42	and spoke out with a loud voice and said, "Blessed are you among women and blessed is the fruit of your womb!
B042C001V043	42	1	43	But why do I have the honor of having the mother of my Lord come to me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For, indeed, when the sound of your greeting fell upon my ears, the babe leapt for joy in my womb.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	Blessed is she who believed, for there will be a complete fulfillment of the things spoken to her from the Lord!"
B042C001V046	42	1	46	Then Mary said: "My soul magnifies the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	And my spirit rejoices in God my Savior;
B042C001V048	42	1	48	Because he has looked upon the low estate of his handmaid. Indeed, from this time all generations will call me blessed.
B042C001V049	42	1	49	Because the Mighty One has done great things for me. Holy is his name.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	His kindness is from generation to generation upon those who fear him.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He shows strength with his arm; He scatters the proud in the thoughts of their hearts.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He casts down princes from their thrones and raises up the lowly.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	The hungry he fills with good things and the affluent he sends away empty.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He brings help to Israel his servant, mindful of kindness,
B042C001V055	42	1	55	just as he promised our fathers, Abraham and his descendants, forever."
B042C001V056	42	1	56	Mary remained with her about three months and then returned to her home.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	When Elizabeth's due time came, she gave birth to a son.
B042C001V058	42	1	58	Her neighbors and relatives heard that the Lord had shown great kindness to her, and they rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	On the eighth day they came to circumcise the child, and they called him by the name of his father Zacharias.
B042C001V060	42	1	60	But his mother said, "No, but he shall be called John."
B042C001V061	42	1	61	They said to her, "There is no one of your family who is called by that name."
B042C001V062	42	1	62	Then they made signs to his father to know what he wanted him called.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	He asked for a tablet and wrote, "His name is John." They all wondered.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	At once Zacharias's mouth was opened and his tongue loosed and he spoke, praising God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	Awe fell on all their neighbors, and in the whole hill-country of Judaea all these matters were talked about.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	All who heard them laid them up in their minds, saying, "What then will this child be?" For the hand of the Lord was with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	Zacharias, his father, was filled with the Holy Spirit and said prophetically:
B042C001V068	42	1	68	"Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel! For he has looked upon his people, and made deliverance for them.
B042C001V069	42	1	69	He has raised up a horn of salvation for us in the house of David his servant,
B042C001V070	42	1	70	As he spoke through the mouth of his holy prophets of old,
B042C001V071	42	1	71	Salvation from our enemies and from the hands of all those that hate us,
B042C001V072	42	1	72	Dealing kindly with our forefathers, mindful of his holy covenant,
B042C001V073	42	1	73	The oath which he swore to Abraham our father,
B042C001V074	42	1	74	To grant that we, saved from the hands of our enemies, may serve him Without fear
B042C001V075	42	1	75	in holiness and righteousness before him all our days.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And you, child, will be called a prophet of the Most High. You will go before the face of the Lord to prepare his ways,
B042C001V077	42	1	77	To give the knowledge of salvation to his people by the forgiveness of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	Through the tender compassion of our God, With which the sunrise from on high will shine upon us;
B042C001V079	42	1	79	To give light to those who sit in darkness and the shadow of death, To guide our feet into the path of peace."
B042C001V080	42	1	80	The child grew and became strong in spirit, and he lived in the wilds until the day of his appearance before Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	IN those days a decree went out from Caesar Augustus for the registration of the whole world.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	This first registration took place while Cyrenius was Governor of Syria.
B042C002V003	42	2	3	Everybody went to be registered \'97 each to his own city.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	Joseph went up from Galilee, from the city of Nazareth, to Judaea, to the city of David, which is called Bethlehem, because he was of the house and lineage of David,
B042C002V005	42	2	5	to be registered with Mary who was betrothed to him, and was with child.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	While they were there, her time came
B042C002V007	42	2	7	and she gave birth to her son, her first-born, and she wrapped him up and laid him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the inn.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	There were shepherds in the same country staying in the fields and keeping watch over their flocks by night.
B042C002V009	42	2	9	Suddenly an angel of the Lord stood by them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them. They were much afraid,
B042C002V010	42	2	10	but the angel said to them, "Have no fear! Indeed, I am bringing you good news of a great joy which is to be for all the people;
B042C002V011	42	2	11	for there was born for you to-day in the city of David a Savior, who is Christ and Lord.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	This will be a sign for you: you will find the babe wrapped up and lying in a manger."
B042C002V013	42	2	13	And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude from the army of heaven, praising God, and saying,
B042C002V014	42	2	14	"Glory in highest heaven to God, and peace on earth among men in whom he delights."
B042C002V015	42	2	15	When the angels went away into heaven, the shepherds spoke to one another: "Let us go to Bethlehem and see this that has happened, which the Lord has made known to us."
B042C002V016	42	2	16	So they came with haste and found Mary and Joseph, and the babe lying in the manger.
B042C002V017	42	2	17	When they saw it, they told what had been spoken to them about this child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	All who heard it wondered at what was said to them by the shepherds.
B042C002V019	42	2	19	Mary kept all these things, pondering them in her heart.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	Then the shepherds went back glorifying and praising God for all that they had heard and seen, just as it had been told them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	When eight days had passed and the time to circumcise him had come, his name was called Jesus \'97 the name given by the angel before he was conceived in the womb.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	When the days of their purification were completed, according to the law of Moses, they brought him up to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord,
B042C002V023	42	2	23	as it is written in the Law of the Lord, "Every firstborn male shall be called holy to the Lord,"
B042C002V024	42	2	24	and to give an offering according to what is said in the law of the Lord, "a pair of doves or two young pigeons."
B042C002V025	42	2	25	There was in Jerusalem a man named Simeon, and this man was upright and God-fearing, looking forward to the consolation of Israel, and the Holy Spirit was upon him.
B042C002V026	42	2	26	It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he was not to see death before he saw the Lord's Christ.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	Led by the Spirit he came into the Temple courts, and when the parents brought in the child Jesus in order to do for him according to the custom of the law,
B042C002V028	42	2	28	he took him into his arms and blessed God, and said,
B042C002V029	42	2	29	"Now, O Lord, thou art letting thy servant depart in peace, according to thy word.
B042C002V030	42	2	30	For mine eyes have seen thy salvation,
B042C002V031	42	2	31	which thou hast prepared before the face of all the peoples,
B042C002V032	42	2	32	a light for revelation to Gentiles and a glory to thy people Israel."
B042C002V033	42	2	33	His father and his mother wondered at the things that were spoken about him.
B042C002V034	42	2	34	Simeon blessed them, and said to Mary his mother, "This child is destined for the fall and rise of many in Israel and for a sign much spoken against
B042C002V035	42	2	35	
        
B042C002V036	42	2	36	And there was Anna, a prophetess, a daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Asher. She was far advanced in years, having lived with her husband seven years from her maidenhood
B042C002V037	42	2	37	and having been a widow for now eighty-four years. She never left the Temple courts, but worshiped by fastings and prayers, night and day.
