B042C003V001	42	3	1	IN the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, when Pontius Pilate was Governor of Judaea and Herod Prince of Galilee, and Philip his brother Prince of Ituraea and Trachonitis, and Lysanias Prince of Abilene,
B042C003V002	42	3	2	during the high-priesthood of Annas and Caiaphas, the word of God came to John the son of Zacharias in the wild lands.
B042C003V003	42	3	3	Then he came into all the neighborhood of the Jordan proclaiming baptism for a change of heart in order to forgiveness of sins,
B042C003V004	42	3	4	as it is written in the book of the words of Isaiah the prophet, "The voice of one shouting in the wilderness, 'Prepare the way of the Lord, make his paths straight!'
B042C003V005	42	3	5	Every ravine shall be filled and every mountain and hill shall be graded down, and the crooked places shall become straight and the rough roads shall become smooth,
B042C003V006	42	3	6	and all men shall see the salvation of God."
B042C003V007	42	3	7	He said to the crowds that went out to be baptized by him, "Brood of vipers, who warned you to flee from the coming wrath?
B042C003V008	42	3	8	Produce then fruits suitable for a change of heart, and do not begin to say to yourselves, 'We have Abraham for our father.' For I tell you, God is able out of these stones to raise up children for Abraham.
B042C003V009	42	3	9	Already the axe is lying at the root of the trees. Every tree that does not yield good fruit is to be cut down and thrown into the fire."
B042C003V010	42	3	10	The crowds asked him, "What then shall we do?"
B042C003V011	42	3	11	He answered, "Let him who has two tunics give to him who has none, and let him who has food do likewise."
