B043C021V025	43	21	25	There are also many other things that Jesus did, but if these are written, every one, I do not think that the world itself will have room for the books when written.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	IN my first book, Theophilus, I told of all that Jesus did and taught from the beginning
B044C001V002	44	1	2	down to the day when, after giving commands, through the Holy Spirit, to the apostles whom he had chosen, he was taken up to heaven.
B044C001V003	44	1	3	By many proofs he revealed himself to these men as still alive after his sufferings; for he was seen by them for forty days and spoke of things relating to the kingdom of God.
B044C001V004	44	1	4	Also while eating with them, he charged them not to leave Jerusalem, but to wait for the promise of the Father, 
B044C001V005	44	1	5	
        
B044C001V006	44	1	6	When they came together, they asked him, "Master, will you at this time restore the kingdom to Israel?"
B044C001V007	44	1	7	He said to them, 
B044C001V008	44	1	8	
        
B044C001V009	44	1	9	He said this and then, while they were looking on, he was taken up and a cloud lifted him from their sight.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	They were gazing into the sky as he went, when suddenly two men in white robes were standing beside them
B044C001V011	44	1	11	and said, "Men of Galilee, why are you standing and looking up into the sky? This Jesus, who has been taken from you into heaven, will come back in the same way that you have seen him go into heaven."
B044C001V012	44	1	12	They then returned to Jerusalem from the mountain called the Olive Orchard, which is near Jerusalem, a Sabbath day's journey distant.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	When they came into the city, they went up to the upper room where they were staying. There were Peter and John, and James and Andrew, Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot, and Judas the son of James.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	All of these continued earnestly and unitedly in prayer with the women and Mary the mother of Jesus and with his brothers.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	In those days Peter stood up in the midst of the brethren 
B044C001V016	44	1	16	"Brethren, it was necessary that the Scripture should be fulfilled which the Holy Spirit spoke through the mouth of David concerning Judas, who became guide to those who arrested Jesus.
B044C001V017	44	1	17	For he was numbered among us and received a share in this service.
B044C001V018	44	1	18	(This man bought a piece of land with the price of his wickedness, and falling headlong he burst asunder and all his entrails were poured out.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	It became known to all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that that field was called in their own language Akeldama, that is, the Field of Blood.)
B044C001V020	44	1	20	For it is written in the book of Psalms, 'Let his dwelling become desolate and let there be no one living in it,' and, 'His overseership let another take.'
B044C001V021	44	1	21	It is needful, therefore, that of the men who have been with us during all the time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	from the baptism of John down to the day that he was taken up from us \'97 that one of these should become a witness with us of his resurrection."
B044C001V023	44	1	23	So they put forward two, Joseph who is called Barsabbas, surnamed Justus, and Matthias.
B044C001V024	44	1	24	In prayer they said, "O Lord, thou who knowest the hearts of all, show which one of these two thou has chosen
B044C001V025	44	1	25	to take the place in this service and apostleship which Judas deserted to go to his own place."
B044C001V026	44	1	26	Then they cast lots between them. The lot fell on Matthias and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	DURING the course of the day of Pentecost they were all together in the same place,
B044C002V002	44	2	2	when suddenly there came from heaven a sound as of a strong rushing wind, and it filled all the house where they were sitting.
B044C002V003	44	2	3	Then there appeared to them, as it were, tongues of flame distributing themselves, and one rested on each of them.
B044C002V004	44	2	4	They were all filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in foreign tongues, as the Spirit gave them power of expression.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	There were Jews living in Jerusalem, pious men from every nation under heaven.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	When this sound was heard, the crowd came together and were astonished because each one heard them speaking in his own language.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	They were amazed and, wondering, said, "Are not all these who are talking, Galilaean?
B044C002V008	44	2	8	How then does each of us hear them in his own native language?
B044C002V009	44	2	9	Parthians and Medes and Elamites and those who live in Mesopotamia, Judas and Cappadocia, Pontus and Asia,
B044C002V010	44	2	10	Phrygia and Pamphilia, Egypt and the regions of Libya toward Cyrene, visitors from Rome, Jews and proselytes,
B044C002V011	44	2	11	Cretans and Arabians \'97 we hear them speaking in our languages the mighty works of God."
B044C002V012	44	2	12	They were all astonished and at a loss, one saying to another, "What does this mean?"
B044C002V013	44	2	13	Some scoffingly said, "They are full of sweet wine."
B044C002V014	44	2	14	But Peter, standing up with the eleven, raised his voice and declared to them: "Fellow Jews, and all of you who live in Jerusalem, understand this and listen to my words.
B044C002V015	44	2	15	These are not drunk, as you assume, for it is only nine o'clock in the morning;
B044C002V016	44	2	16	but this is what was spoken through the prophet Joel:
B044C002V017	44	2	17	'It will be in the last days, says God, that I will pour out my Spirit upon all mankind, and your sons and your daughters will prophesy, and your young men will see visions, and your old men will dream dreams.
B044C002V018	44	2	18	Yes, upon the slave men and slave girls that are mine I will pour out my Spirit in those days, and they will prophesy.
B044C002V019	44	2	19	I will give portents in heaven above and signs on the earth beneath, blood and fire and vapor of smoke.
B044C002V020	44	2	20	The sun will be turned into darkness and the moon into blood before the day of the Lord comes \'97 that great and glorious day.
B044C002V021	44	2	21	And every one who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.'
B044C002V022	44	2	22	Fellow Israelites, listen to these words: Jesus the Nazarene was a man proved to be sent to you from God by miracles, wonders, and signs which God did through him in the midst of you, as you yourselves know.
B044C002V023	44	2	23	But when he had been delivered up according to the fixed purpose and foreknowledge of God, you crucified and killed him through the hands of lawless men.
B044C002V024	44	2	24	But God freed him from the pangs of death and raised him up, since it was impossible that he should be held under the power of death.
B044C002V025	44	2	25	For David says of him, 'I saw the Lord always before my face, for he is at my right hand so that I may not be cast down.
B044C002V026	44	2	26	Therefore my heart is glad and my tongue rejoices, and my flesh still dwells in hope
B044C002V027	44	2	27	that thou wilt not leave my soul to Hades and wilt not let thy holy one see decay.
B044C002V028	44	2	28	Thou makest me know the paths of life. Thou wilt fill me with joy in thy presence.'
B044C002V029	44	2	29	"Brethren, allow me to say frankly to you regarding the patriarch David that he died and was buried and his tomb is among us to this day.
B044C002V030	44	2	30	But being a prophet and knowing that God had sworn to him an oath to place a descendant of his body upon his throne,
B044C002V031	44	2	31	he foreseeing spoke of the resurrection of the Christ, saying that he was not left to Hades and that his flesh did not see decay.
B044C002V032	44	2	32	This Jesus, God raised up, and all of us are witnesses of it.
B044C002V033	44	2	33	Therefore having been exalted to the right hand of God and having received from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, he has poured out this which you see and hear.
B044C002V034	44	2	34	For David did not ascend into the heavens, but he says, 'The Lord said to my Lord, Sit at my right hand,
B044C002V035	44	2	35	till I make your enemies your footstool.'
B044C002V036	44	2	36	Let all the house of Israel know surely that this Jesus, whom you crucified, God has made both Lord and Christ."
B044C002V037	44	2	37	Hearing this they were cut to the heart and said to Peter and the other apostles, "What shall we do, brethren?"
B044C002V038	44	2	38	Peter said to them, "Repent and be baptized every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ, for the forgiveness of your sins, and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.
B044C002V039	44	2	39	For the promise belongs to you and to your children and to all those who are far off, as many as the Lord your God may call."
B044C002V040	44	2	40	With many other words he bore witness and exhorted them, "Save yourselves from this perverse generation."
B044C002V041	44	2	41	Those who accepted his message were baptized, and there were added on that day about three thousand souls.
B044C002V042	44	2	42	These gave constant attention to the teaching of the apostles and to the fellowship and the breaking of bread and the prayers.
B044C002V043	44	2	43	Awe came on every soul. Many wonders and signs were done by the apostles.
B044C002V044	44	2	44	All who believed had all things together in common.
B044C002V045	44	2	45	They would sell their lands and goods and distribute to all as any one had need.
B044C002V046	44	2	46	Every day, continuing with one accord in the Temple courts and in breaking bread from house to house, they ate together in joy and simplicity of heart,
B044C002V047	44	2	47	praising God and having favor with all the people. The Lord added daily to their number those who were being saved.
B044C003V001	44	3	1	PETER and John were going up into the Temple courts at the hour of prayer, three o'clock,
B044C003V002	44	3	2	when a man lame from his birth was being carried along. This man used to be placed every day near the gate of the Temple courts \'97 the one called the Beautiful Gate \'97 to beg of those who were entering.
B044C003V003	44	3	3	Seeing Peter and John about to go into the Temple courts, he begged to receive something.
B044C003V004	44	3	4	But Peter fixing his eyes on him, along with John, said, "Look at us."
B044C003V005	44	3	5	He gave attention to them, expecting to receive something from them.
B044C003V006	44	3	6	But Peter said, "Silver and gold I have not; but what I have I will give you. In the name of Jesus Christ the Nazarene, walk."
B044C003V007	44	3	7	Grasping his right hand he lifted him up. Immediately his feet and ankles became strong,
B044C003V008	44	3	8	and he sprang up and stood and walked and entered the Temple court with them, walking and leaping and praising God.
B044C003V009	44	3	9	All the people saw him walking about and praising God,
B044C003V010	44	3	10	and when they recognized that it was he who had sat begging at the Beautiful Gate of the Temple court, they were filled with wonder and amazement at what had happened to him.
B044C003V011	44	3	11	While he still clung to Peter and John, all the people ran crowding around them in what was called Solomon's Colonnade, greatly astonished.
B044C003V012	44	3	12	Peter, seeing the people, explained, "Fellow Israelites, why do you wonder at this, or why do you gaze so at us, as if by our own power or piety we had made him walk?
B044C003V013	44	3	13	The God of Abraham and of Isaac and of Jacob, the God of our fathers, has glorified his servant Jesus whom you delivered up and disowned before Pilate when he had decided to release him.
B044C003V014	44	3	14	You disowned the holy and righteous one and begged to have a murderer granted you.
B044C003V015	44	3	15	You killed the Author of life, but God raised him from the dead. Of this we are witnesses.
B044C003V016	44	3	16	And now by faith in his name this man whom you see and know has been made strong by his name, and the faith that is through him has given this man this perfect soundness before you all.
B044C003V017	44	3	17	"Now, brethren, I know that you acted in ignorance, as also your rulers did.
B044C003V018	44	3	18	God in this way fulfilled what he had predicted through the mouths of all the prophets that his Christ should suffer.
B044C003V019	44	3	19	Therefore, repent and turn about, that your sins may be wiped away and the gracious face of the Lord may bring times of refreshing,
B044C003V020	44	3	20	and he may send Jesus Christ, long ago appointed,
B044C003V021	44	3	21	but whom heaven must receive until the times of the restoration of all things, of which God spoke through the mouths of his holy prophets of old.
B044C003V022	44	3	22	"Moses indeed said, 'The Lord God will raise up for you a prophet from among your brethren, as he raised me; listen to all that he may say to you.
B044C003V023	44	3	23	It shall be that every person who does not listen to that prophet will be utterly destroyed from among the people.'
B044C003V024	44	3	24	And all the prophets, Samuel and those who followed him, all who spoke, also foretold these days.
B044C003V025	44	3	25	You are the sons of the prophets and of the covenant which God established with your fathers when he said to Abraham, 'In your descendants all the families of the earth will be blessed.'
B044C003V026	44	3	26	To you first God, when he raised up his servant, sent him, to bless you by turning each one of you from his wicked ways."
B044C004V001	44	4	1	WHILE they were speaking to the people, the priests and the commandant of the Temple and the Sadducees came upon them,
B044C004V002	44	4	2	being offended because they were teaching the people and proclaiming in the case of Jesus the resurrection from the dead.
B044C004V003	44	4	3	They laid hands on them and placed them in custody until the next day, for it was already evening.
B044C004V004	44	4	4	But many of those who had heard the message believed, and the number of the men grew to be about five thousand.
B044C004V005	44	4	5	On the next day there was a gathering of their rulers and elders and scribes in Jerusalem,
B044C004V006	44	4	6	with Annas the High Priest and Caiaphas and John and Alexander and all who were of high priestly race.
B044C004V007	44	4	7	They placed the apostles in the midst and asked them, "By what power and in what name did you do this?"
B044C004V008	44	4	8	Then Peter, full of the Holy Spirit, said to them, "Rulers of the people and elders,
B044C004V009	44	4	9	if we must answer to-day regarding a benefit done to an infirm man, by what name he has been healed,
B044C004V010	44	4	10	be it known to all of you and to all the people of Israel, that by the name of Jesus Christ the Nazarene, whom you crucified, whom God raised from the dead \'97 by this name, this man stands here before you sound.
B044C004V011	44	4	11	This is the stone which was despised by you the builders, and which has become the corner stone.
B044C004V012	44	4	12	Nor is there salvation in any other. For there is no other name under heaven given among men by which we must be saved."
B044C004V013	44	4	13	Observing the fearless outspokenness of Peter and John and perceiving that they were common, uneducated men, they were astonished, and they recognized them as former companions of Jesus.
B044C004V014	44	4	14	Seeing the man who had been healed standing there with the apostles, they had nothing to say in opposition.
B044C004V015	44	4	15	After ordering them to go out of the council, they conferred together,
B044C004V016	44	4	16	saying, "What shall we do to these men? For that a notable miracle has been done by them is plain to all who live in Jerusalem, and we cannot deny it.
B044C004V017	44	4	17	But that it may not spread further among the people, let us sternly forbid them to speak any longer in this name to any one."
B044C004V018	44	4	18	So, calling them in, they commanded them absolutely not to speak or teach in the name of Jesus.
B044C004V019	44	4	19	But Peter and John answered them, "Whether it is right in the sight of God to listen to you rather than to God, judge for yourselves.
B044C004V020	44	4	20	We, for our part, cannot refrain from saying what we have seen and heard."
