B044C019V041	44	19	41	By saying this he dissolved the gathering.
B044C020V001	44	20	1	WHEN the uproar had ceased, Paul sent for the disciples, and, after encouraging them, he bade them farewell and left to proceed to Macedonia.
B044C020V002	44	20	2	Passing through those parts and encouraging them by many addresses, he came into Greece.
B044C020V003	44	20	3	There he spent three months. When a plot was formed against him by the Jews as he was about to sail for Syria, he decided to return through Macedonia.
B044C020V004	44	20	4	There were in company with him Sopater of Beraea, the son of Pyrrhus, and of the Thessalonians Aristarchus and Secundus, and Gaius of Derbe and Timothy, and from Asia Tychicus and Trophimus.
B044C020V005	44	20	5	These went on and were waiting for us in Troas.
B044C020V006	44	20	6	After the Days of Unleavened Bread we sailed from Philippi and came to them in Troas in five days. There we spent seven days.
B044C020V007	44	20	7	On the first day of the week, when we all were assembled to break bread, Paul was discoursing to them, being about to leave in the morning, and he extended his address until midnight.
B044C020V008	44	20	8	There were many lamps in the upper room where we were assembled.
B044C020V009	44	20	9	A certain young man named Eutychus, sitting in a window, was overcome with deep sleep while Paul went on discoursing. At last overpowered by sleep he fell from the third story and was taken up dead.
B044C020V010	44	20	10	But Paul went down and threw himself on him and embraced him and said, "Do not make a noisy wailing; for his life is still in him."
B044C020V011	44	20	11	Then he went up and broke bread and ate and talked on till daybreak and so departed.
B044C020V012	44	20	12	They brought the boy living, and were not a little comforted.
B044C020V013	44	20	13	We went in advance to the ship and sailed for Assos, intending to take on Paul there, for so he had arranged, intending to come himself by land.
B044C020V014	44	20	14	So when he joined us at Assos, we took him aboard and came to Mitylene.
B044C020V015	44	20	15	From there we sailed next day and arrived off Chios. The next day we came to Samos, and on the following day to Miletus.
B044C020V016	44	20	16	For Paul had determined to sail by Ephesus in order not to spend time in Asia. He was hurrying to be in Jerusalem, if possible, on the Day of Pentecost.
B044C020V017	44	20	17	From Miletus he sent to Ephesus for the elders of the church.
B044C020V018	44	20	18	When they came to him, he said to them, "You know how I have lived among you the whole time since the first day I set foot in Asia,
B044C020V019	44	20	19	serving the Lord with all humility and with tears and with trials that befell me through the plots of the Jews \'97
B044C020V020	44	20	20	how I did not shrink from telling you anything that was profitable or from teaching you publicly and from house to house,
B044C020V021	44	20	21	urging upon both Jews and Greeks the need of a change of heart toward God and of faith in our Lord Jesus.
B044C020V022	44	20	22	"And now I am on my way, bound in spirit, to Jerusalem, not knowing what is to befall me there,
B044C020V023	44	20	23	except that the Holy Spirit testifies from city to city that chains and trials are waiting for me.
