B044C020V033	44	20	33	I have coveted no man's silver or gold or apparel.
B044C020V034	44	20	34	You yourselves know that these hands provided for my needs and the needs of my companions.
B044C020V035	44	20	35	In all things I showed you that so laboring we ought to help the weak, and to remember the words of the Lord Jesus, that he said, 
B044C020V036	44	20	36	After saying this he kneeled with them all and prayed.
B044C020V037	44	20	37	All wept aloud, and falling on Paul's neck they kissed him affectionately,
B044C020V038	44	20	38	grieving especially because he had said that they would never see his face again; and they escorted him to the ship.
B044C021V001	44	21	1	WHEN we had torn ourselves away from them and had sailed, we made a straight run to Cos, then on the next day to Rhodes and from there to Patara.
B044C021V002	44	21	2	There finding a ship crossing to Phoenicia we went on board and sailed.
B044C021V003	44	21	3	After sighting Cyprus and leaving it on the left, we sailed on to Syria and landed at Tyre; for there the ship was to discharge her cargo.
