B044C025V013	44	25	13	When some days had passed, Agrippa the King and Bernice came to Caesarea to pay their respects to Festus.
B044C025V014	44	25	14	As they were spending a good many days there, Festus laid Paul's case before the King. "There is a man here," he said, "who was left a prisoner by Felix,
B044C025V015	44	25	15	against whom when I was in Jerusalem the high priests and the elders of the Jews had much to say, asking to have him condemned.
B044C025V016	44	25	16	I answered them that it is not the custom of the Romans to give up any person for punishment before the accused has his accusers face to face and has opportunity for defense against the charge.
B044C025V017	44	25	17	"So they came along down here and, without making any delay, on the very next day I took my seat on the judge's bench and ordered the man to be brought in.
B044C025V018	44	25	18	When his accusers arose, they brought no charge of such crimes as I was expecting,
B044C025V019	44	25	19	but they had some disputes with him about their own religion and concerning a certain Jesus who had died and whom Paul affirmed to be alive.
B044C025V020	44	25	20	Being at a loss about a question of this kind, I asked if he would be willing to go to Jerusalem and be tried there on the charges.
B044C025V021	44	25	21	But when Paul appealed to be kept for the examination of the Emperor, I ordered him to be kept until I could send him to Caesar."
B044C025V022	44	25	22	Agrippa said to Festus, "I should like to hear the man myself." "To-morrow," he replied, "you shall hear him."
B044C025V023	44	25	23	So on the next day Agrippa came and Bernice with much display, and they entered the auditorium with the military tribunes and the principal men of the city, and at Festus' command Paul was led in.
B044C025V024	44	25	24	Festus said, "King Agrippa and all present here with us, you see this man against whom all the multitude of the Jews pleaded with me, both in Jerusalem and here, crying out that he ought not to live any longer.
B044C025V025	44	25	25	But I understood that he had done nothing worthy of death, and when he himself had appealed to the Emperor, I decided to send him.
B044C025V026	44	25	26	Concerning him I have nothing certain to write to my Lord. Therefore I have brought him before you all, and especially before you, King Agrippa, that after an examination I may have something to write.
B044C025V027	44	25	27	For it seems to me unreasonable in sending a prisoner not to specify the charges against him."
B044C026V001	44	26	1	AGRIPPA said to Paul, "You are at liberty to speak for yourself." Then Paul stretched out his hand and made his defense:
B044C026V002	44	26	2	"In regard to all of the things of which I am accused by Jews, King Agrippa, I consider myself fortunate that I am to make my defense to-day before you,
B044C026V003	44	26	3	since you are especially expert in all Jewish customs and questions. Therefore I pray you to hear me patiently.
B044C026V004	44	26	4	"My life from boyhood, which was from the beginning among my own nation and in Jerusalem, all Jews know.
B044C026V005	44	26	5	They knew me from long ago, if they were willing to testify, and that according to the strictest sect of our religion I lived a Pharisee.
B044C026V006	44	26	6	And now I stand to be tried for the hope of the promise which God made to our fathers,
B044C026V007	44	26	7	to which our twelve tribes devotedly serving God night and day hope to attain. For this hope I am accused by the Jews, O King.
B044C026V008	44	26	8	"Why do all of you consider it incredible if God raises dead men?
B044C026V009	44	26	9	I thought with myself that I ought to do much against the name of Jesus the Nazarene.
B044C026V010	44	26	10	And I did it in Jerusalem and many holy men I shut up in prison, getting authority from the high priests, and when they were put to death I gave my vote against them.
B044C026V011	44	26	11	In all the synagogues and often I punished them and compelled them to say profane words. Being excessively mad against them, I pursued them even to foreign cities.
B044C026V012	44	26	12	"Thus engaged, as I was journeying to Damascus with authority and commission from the high priests,
B044C026V013	44	26	13	about midday, on the road, I saw, O King, a light above the brightness of the sun shining from heaven around me and my companions.
B044C026V014	44	26	14	We all fell to the ground and I heard a voice saying to me in Hebrew, 
B044C026V015	44	26	15	I said, 'Who is speaking?' He said, 
B044C026V016	44	26	16	
        
B044C026V017	44	26	17	
        
B044C026V018	44	26	18	
        
B044C026V019	44	26	19	After that, King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly vision,
B044C026V020	44	26	20	but first to the people in Damascus and then to the people of Jerusalem and through all the land of Judaea and to the Gentiles, I proclaimed that they should repent and turn to God and do deeds suitable for a change of heart.
B044C026V021	44	26	21	"For this reason Jews seized me in the Temple courts and tried to kill me.
B044C026V022	44	26	22	But obtaining help from God I have continued until this day witnessing to small and great, saying nothing but what the prophets and Moses said would be,
B044C026V023	44	26	23	that the Christ would suffer and that he first, by rising from the dead, would proclaim light to our people and to the Gentiles."
B044C026V024	44	26	24	While Paul was thus defending himself, Festus said loudly, "You are raving, Paul. Much learning is driving you insane."
B044C026V025	44	26	25	"I am not insane," he said, "most noble Festus, but am uttering words of truth and soberness.
B044C026V026	44	26	26	The King knows about this, and to him I speak with perfect frankness, for I am persuaded that not one of these things has escaped his attention, for this has not been done in a corner.
B044C026V027	44	26	27	King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know that you believe them."
B044C026V028	44	26	28	Agrippa said to Paul, "With little effort you are persuading me to become a Christian."
B044C026V029	44	26	29	Paul said, "I would to God that whether with little or with much, not only you, but all who hear me this day, would become such as I am \'97 except for these chains."
B044C026V030	44	26	30	Then the King rose and the Governor and Bernice and those who had been sitting with them,
B044C026V031	44	26	31	and after withdrawing they said to one another, "This man is doing nothing deserving of death or chains."
B044C026V032	44	26	32	Agrippa said to Festus, "This man could have been set at liberty if he had not appealed to Caesar."
B044C027V001	44	27	1	WHEN it was decided that we should sail for Italy, they committed Paul and certain other prisoners to a centurion named Julius, of an imperial battalion.
B044C027V002	44	27	2	Going on board a ship of Adramyttium which was about to sail to the places along the coast of Asia we put to sea. Aristarchus, a Macedonian of Thessalonica, was with us.
B044C027V003	44	27	3	On the next day we reached Sidon, where Julius treated Paul kindly and allowed him to go to see his friends and enjoy their attentions.
B044C027V004	44	27	4	Putting to sea from there, we sailed under the lee of Cyprus because the winds were contrary.
B044C027V005	44	27	5	After crossing the sea off Cilicia and Pamphylia, we came to Myra in Lycia.
B044C027V006	44	27	6	There the centurion found an Alexandrian ship bound for Italy and put us on board of her.
B044C027V007	44	27	7	By slow sailing for many days we with difficulty arrived off Cnidus. Then the wind being against us, we sailed under the lee of Crete off Salmone
B044C027V008	44	27	8	and with difficulty got past it and came to a place called Fair Havens, near which was the city of Lasea.
B044C027V009	44	27	9	When much time had passed and sailing was now dangerous because it was already after the Fast, Paul addressed them.
B044C027V010	44	27	10	"Men," he said, "I see that the voyage is going to be rough and with much loss not only of the cargo and the ship but also of our lives."
B044C027V011	44	27	11	But the Centurion listened more to the sailing master and the ship owner than to what Paul said,
B044C027V012	44	27	12	and as the harbor was not convenient to winter in, the majority adopted the purpose of sailing away on the chance of being able to reach Phoenix and winter there. Phoenix is a harbor of Crete facing the southwest and the northwest.
B044C027V013	44	27	13	When the south wind blew softly, thinking that they had secured their purpose, they weighed anchor and coasted along Crete.
B044C027V014	44	27	14	But before long a hurricane, such as is called Euraquilo, swept down off the land.
B044C027V015	44	27	15	When the ship was caught and unable to keep her head to the wind, we gave up and let her drive before it.
B044C027V016	44	27	16	Running under the lee of an island called Cauda, we contrived with difficulty to secure the small boat.
B044C027V017	44	27	17	When we had got it in, we used ropes to undergird the ship. Fearing that we might get stranded on the Syrtis, they lowered the sail and so drifted.
B044C027V018	44	27	18	So violently were we battered by the storm that on the next day they lightened the ship
B044C027V019	44	27	19	and on the third day with their own hands they threw over the ship's tackle.
B044C027V020	44	27	20	When for many days neither sun nor stars appeared and no small tempest lay on us, at last all hope of our being saved was being taken away.
B044C027V021	44	27	21	After they had long gone without food, Paul stood up in the midst of them and said, "Men, you ought to have listened to me and not to have sailed away from Crete and met this rough experience and loss.
B044C027V022	44	27	22	But now I beg you to have courage, for there will be no loss of life of any of you, but only of the ship.
B044C027V023	44	27	23	For this night an angel of the God whose I am and whom I serve stood by me
B044C027V024	44	27	24	and said, 'Never fear, Paul! You must stand before Caesar. And now God has granted to you all the men who are sailing with you.'
B044C027V025	44	27	25	So cheer up, men. For I trust in God that it will be as it has been told me.
B044C027V026	44	27	26	We must, however, run on to a certain island."
B044C027V027	44	27	27	When the fourteenth night came, as we were being driven through the Adriatic, about midnight the sailors surmised that land was getting near.
B044C027V028	44	27	28	Sounding they found twenty fathoms, and after a little they sounded again and found fifteen fathoms.
B044C027V029	44	27	29	Then fearing that they might run into rocky places, they cast out four anchors from the stern and prayed for day to come.
B044C027V030	44	27	30	The sailors were intent on escaping from the ship and lowered the small boat into the sea under the pretense of laying out anchors from the bow,
B044C027V031	44	27	31	but Paul said to the Centurion and the soldiers, "Unless these men stay in the ship, you cannot be saved."
B044C027V032	44	27	32	Then the soldiers cut the ropes of the small boat and let her fall off.
B044C027V033	44	27	33	Until day began to dawn, Paul kept urging all to take food. He said, "To-day is the fourteenth day that you have been on the watch fasting, not taking anything.
B044C027V034	44	27	34	Therefore, I beg you, take some food. For this is for your safety. Not a hair of the head of any one of you is going to perish."
B044C027V035	44	27	35	Saying this he took a loaf and gave thanks to God before all and broke it and began to eat.
B044C027V036	44	27	36	Then all cheered up and themselves took food.
B044C027V037	44	27	37	We in the ship were in all two hundred and seventy-six souls.
B044C027V038	44	27	38	After eating heartily, they lightened the ship, throwing over the wheat into the sea.
B044C027V039	44	27	39	When day came they did not recognize the land, but they observed a bay with a beach. Into this they planned to run the ship if they could.
B044C027V040	44	27	40	So abandoning the anchors they left them in the sea; at the same time loosening the bands of the steering oars and raising the foresail to the wind, they made for the beach.
B044C027V041	44	27	41	But falling into a place where there were cross-currents they ran the ship aground. The bow stuck fast and remained immovable, but the stern was breaking up under the violence of the sea.
B044C027V042	44	27	42	The soldiers' advice was to kill the prisoners for fear that some one of them might swim out and escape.
B044C027V043	44	27	43	But the Centurion, wishing to save Paul, kept them back from their plan. He ordered those who could swim to jump overboard first and get to shore,
B044C027V044	44	27	44	and the rest to follow, some on boards and some on things from the ship. And so all got safe to land.
B044C028V001	44	28	1	WHEN we were safe ashore, we found that the island was called Melita.
B044C028V002	44	28	2	The foreign people showed us uncommon kindness. For they kindled a fire and welcomed us all because of the rain that was falling and the cold.
B044C028V003	44	28	3	Paul had collected a bundle of sticks and laid it on the fire, when a snake came out of the heat and fastened on his hand.
B044C028V004	44	28	4	When the foreigners saw the creature hanging from his hand, they said to one another, "Certainly this man is a murderer, whom, although he has escaped the sea, Justice does not permit to live."
B044C028V005	44	28	5	He however shook off the creature into the fire and felt no harm.
B044C028V006	44	28	6	They kept watching to see him swell up or suddenly fall down dead. But after watching a long time and seeing nothing amiss happen to him, they changed their minds and said that he was a god.
B044C028V007	44	28	7	In the neighborhood of that place were lands belonging to the Governor of the island, whose name was Publius. He welcomed us and for three days hospitably entertained us.
B044C028V008	44	28	8	It happened that the father of Publius was lying ill with fever and dysentery. Paul went in to see him and prayed and laid his hands on him and healed him.
B044C028V009	44	28	9	After this happened, the rest in the island who had infirmities came also and were healed.
B044C028V010	44	28	10	They bestowed many honors on us and when we sailed they put on board supplies for our needs.
B044C028V011	44	28	11	After three months we sailed in a ship that had wintered in the island. She was from Alexandria and her figure-head was the Twin Brothers.
B044C028V012	44	28	12	Landing at Syracuse we remained there three days.
B044C028V013	44	28	13	From there we came around and got to Rhegium. After one day there, a south wind sprang up and we came on the second day to Puteoli.
B044C028V014	44	28	14	Here we found brethren and were begged by them to stay seven days. And so we came to Rome.
B044C028V015	44	28	15	From there the brethren, when they got news of us, came to meet us as far as the Market of Appius and the Three Taverns. On seeing them Paul thanked God and took courage.
B044C028V016	44	28	16	When we reached Rome, Paul was allowed to live by himself with a soldier who guarded him.
B044C028V017	44	28	17	After three days he invited the leading men among the Jews, and when they had assembled, he said to them, "Brethren, although I had done nothing against our people or our ancestral customs, I was delivered up as a prisoner from Jerusalem into the hands of the Romans.
B044C028V018	44	28	18	They, after investigating my case, wished to set me free because I had done nothing deserving of death.
B044C028V019	44	28	19	But when the Jews spoke against it, I was compelled to appeal to Caesar, not that I have any charge to bring against my own nation.
B044C028V020	44	28	20	For this reason I have invited you to see me and talk with me; because it is for the sake of the hope of Israel that I have this chain around me."
B044C028V021	44	28	21	They said to him, "We on our part have received no letters about you from Judaea nor has any one of the brethren come and reported or spoken anything evil of you.
B044C028V022	44	28	22	We think it well to hear from you what your views are; for as to this sect we know that it is everywhere spoken against."
B044C028V023	44	28	23	They appointed a day for him and many came to him at his lodging. He explained to them, testifying to the kingdom of God, trying to persuade them concerning Jesus from the Law of Moses and from the Prophets, from early morning until evening.
B044C028V024	44	28	24	Some were persuaded by what he said and some did not believe.
B044C028V025	44	28	25	They dispersed, disagreeing with one another, after Paul had said one word, "Well said the Holy Spirit through Isaiah, the prophet, to your fathers,
B044C028V026	44	28	26	'Go to this people and say, You will hear plainly but you will not understand, and you will see plainly but you will not perceive.
B044C028V027	44	28	27	For the heart of this people has grown fat and with their ears they are hard of hearing and their eyes they have shut, so that they may never see with their eyes nor hear with their ears nor understand with their heart and repent, so that I may heal them.'
B044C028V028	44	28	28	Therefore be it known to you that this salvation of God has been sent to the Gentiles. They will listen."
B044C028V029	44	28	29	
        
B044C028V030	44	28	30	Paul remained two whole years in his own rented lodging and received all who came to him,
B044C028V031	44	28	31	proclaiming the kingdom of God and teaching about the Lord Jesus Christ with all freedom of speech, unhindered.
B045C001V001	45	1	1	PAUL, a servant of Christ Jesus, called to be an apostle, set apart to bear the good news of God,
B045C001V002	45	1	2	which he foretold through his prophets in Holy Scripture,
B045C001V003	45	1	3	concerning his Son Jesus Christ our Lord (who became one of the descendants of David according to the flesh,
B045C001V004	45	1	4	and was with power proved to be the Son of God according to the Spirit of holiness by his resurrection from the dead);
B045C001V005	45	1	5	through whom we obtained grace and apostleship to promote obedience of faith for the sake of his name,
B045C001V006	45	1	6	among all the Gentiles, among whom are you, called by Jesus Christ;
B045C001V007	45	1	7	to all who are in Rome, beloved by God, called to be holy: Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C001V008	45	1	8	First of all I thank my God through Jesus Christ for all of you, because your faith is spoken of through all the world.
B045C001V009	45	1	9	For God, whom I serve in my spirit in the good news of his Son, is my witness how unceasingly I make mention of you, always in my prayers
B045C001V010	45	1	10	asking if I may somehow at some time by the will of God find the way open to come to you.
B045C001V011	45	1	11	For I long to see you that I may impart to you some spiritual gift of grace in order that you may be strengthened,
B045C001V012	45	1	12	that is, that I may be encouraged with you and by you through our mutual faith, yours and mine.
B045C001V013	45	1	13	I am not willing that you should be ignorant, brethren, that often I have purposed to come to you 
B045C001V014	45	1	14	I am a debtor to Greeks and to Barbarians, to wise men and to unthinking men;
B045C001V015	45	1	15	so, for my part, I am eager to tell the good news also to you in Rome.
B045C001V016	45	1	16	For I am not ashamed of the good news. It is the power of God for salvation to every one who believes, to the Jew first and also to the Greek.
B045C001V017	45	1	17	For a righteousness of God is revealed in it from faith to faith, as it is written, "He who is righteous by faith shall live."
B045C001V018	45	1	18	For the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all impiety and wickedness of men who hold the truth but practice unrighteousness.
B045C001V019	45	1	19	Because what may be known of God is manifest within them, for God has manifested it to them.
B045C001V020	45	1	20	For God's invisible qualities \'97 his everlasting power and deity \'97 are, since the creation of the world, clearly seen, being known from what he has made. So they are without any excuse.
B045C001V021	45	1	21	For although they knew God they did not glorify him as God and did not give him thanks, but fell into futile speculations and their stupid hearts were darkened.
B045C001V022	45	1	22	Boasting of being wise, they became fools
B045C001V023	45	1	23	and changed the glory of the incorruptible God into images of mortal man, and of birds and beasts and reptiles.
B045C001V024	45	1	24	Therefore God gave them over, in the lusts of their hearts, to uncleanness, to dishonor their bodies mutually.
B045C001V025	45	1	25	They changed the truth of God into a lie, and reverenced and paid worship to the creature rather than to the Creator \'97 who is blessed forever, Amen!
B045C001V026	45	1	26	Therefore God gave them over to disgraceful passions. For their females changed the natural use for one contrary to nature,
B045C001V027	45	1	27	and their males, leaving the natural use of the female, burned in their lust for one another, males with males practicing indecency and receiving in themselves the deserved penalty of their error.
B045C001V028	45	1	28	And as they did not think fit to keep God in their knowledge, God gave them over to an abandoned mind, to do the things that are shameful,
B045C001V029	45	1	29	filled with all injustice, wickedness, greed, malice, full of envy, murder, strife, fraud, malignant craftiness, whisperers,
B045C001V030	45	1	30	slanderers, hateful to God, insolent, arrogant, boasters, inventors of evil things, disobedient to parents,
B045C001V031	45	1	31	without common sense, without faithfulness, without family affection, without pity.
B045C001V032	45	1	32	They know the just judgment of God that those who practice such things are worthy of death, yet they not only do them themselves, but are pleased with those who practice them.
B045C002V001	45	2	1	THEREFORE you are without excuse, O man, whoever you are, when you judge. For in judging another you condemn yourself. For you, the judge, practice the same things.
B045C002V002	45	2	2	But we know that the judgment of God is according to truth upon those who practice such things.
B045C002V003	45	2	3	Do you think, O man, you who judge those who practice such things while you do the same, that you will escape the judgment of God?
B045C002V004	45	2	4	Or do you despise the wealth of his kindness and forbearance and long-suffering, not knowing that the kindness of God is calling you to a change of heart?
B045C002V005	45	2	5	Are you with a hard and unrepentant heart treasuring for yourself wrath for the day of wrath and for the revelation of the just judgment of God?
B045C002V006	45	2	6	He will give to each an award according to his works.
B045C002V007	45	2	7	To those who by constancy in good work seek for glory and honor and immortality he will award life eternal.
B045C002V008	45	2	8	But to those of a partisan spirit who do not obey the truth, but obey wickedness, there will be wrath and hot anger.
B045C002V009	45	2	9	Distress and crushing calamity will fall upon every human soul that works evil, upon the Jew first and also upon the Greek.
B045C002V010	45	2	10	But glory and honor and peace will come to every one who works good, to the Jew first and also to the Greek.
B045C002V011	45	2	11	For God has no partiality.
B045C002V012	45	2	12	As many as have sinned without a law will perish without a law, and as many as have sinned under law will be judged by law
B045C002V013	45	2	13	(for it is not the hearers of law who are righteous before God, but the doers of law are pronounced righteous;
B045C002V014	45	2	14	for when Gentiles who have no law do by nature what the Law enjoins, these, although they have no law, are a law to themselves;
B045C002V015	45	2	15	they show the requirements of the Law written in their hearts, since their conscience corroborates it and their thoughts argue in mutual accusation or in self-defense),
B045C002V016	45	2	16	on the day when God judges the secrets of men through Jesus Christ, as my good news sets forth.
B045C002V017	45	2	17	But if you bear the name of Jew and rely upon the Law, and make your boast in God
B045C002V018	45	2	18	and know his will and are a judge of things that differ, because you have been taught out of the Law
B045C002V019	45	2	19	and are confident that you yourself are a guide of the blind, a light of those who are in darkness,
B045C002V020	45	2	20	an instructor of the unwise, a teacher of the simple, because you have the form of knowledge and of truth in the Law \'97
B045C002V021	45	2	21	you who are teaching another, do you not teach yourself? You who preach not to steal, do you steal?
B045C002V022	45	2	22	You who say not to commit adultery, do you commit adultery? You who abhor idols, do you rob temples?
B045C002V023	45	2	23	You who boast of the Law, do you dishonor God by breaking the Law?
B045C002V024	45	2	24	For "The name of God is reviled among the Gentiles because of you," as it is written.
B045C002V025	45	2	25	Circumcision has value if you obey the Law. But if you are a breaker of the Law, your circumcision has become uncircumcision.
B045C002V026	45	2	26	If an uncircumcised man keeps the requirements of the Law, shall not his uncircumcision be credited for circumcision?
B045C002V027	45	2	27	And the natural uncircumcision if it keeps the Law will judge you who with a written code and circumcision are still a law-breaker.
B045C002V028	45	2	28	For it is not he who is one outwardly that is a Jew, nor is that circumcision which is outward in the flesh.
B045C002V029	45	2	29	But he who is one secretly is a Jew, and circumcision is of the heart and in the spirit, not in the letter. His praise is not from men, but from God.
B045C003V001	45	3	1	WHAT then is the advantage of the Jew, or what is the benefit of circumcision?
B045C003V002	45	3	2	Much in every way. First, they were intrusted with the oracles of God.
B045C003V003	45	3	3	For what if some were faithless, will their faithlessness prevent the faithfulness of God?
B045C003V004	45	3	4	Never. Let God be true, but every man a liar, as it is written, "That thou mayest be proved right in thy words and triumph when thou art judged."
B045C003V005	45	3	5	But if our unrighteousness shows the righteousness of God, what shall we say? Is God unrighteous when he inflicts his wrath? 
B045C003V006	45	3	6	Never. If so how can God judge the world?
B045C003V007	45	3	7	But if the truth of God has become more abundant to his glory through my lie, why am I still condemned as a sinner?
B045C003V008	45	3	8	We are not going to say, as some people slanderously affirm that we say, "Let us do evil that good may come," are we? The condemnation of such people is just.
B045C003V009	45	3	9	What then? Have we an advantage? Not at all. We have already brought the charge against both Jews and Greeks that they are all under sin,
B045C003V010	45	3	10	as it is written, "There is not even one righteous;
B045C003V011	45	3	11	there is none that seeks God.
B045C003V012	45	3	12	All have turned away; together they have become worthless; there is none who does what is useful, not even one.
B045C003V013	45	3	13	Their throat is an open sepulcher; with their tongues they deceive; the poison of asps is under their lips.
B045C003V014	45	3	14	Their mouth is full of cursing and bitterness;
B045C003V015	45	3	15	their feet are swift to shed blood;
B045C003V016	45	3	16	ruin and misery are in their paths.
B045C003V017	45	3	17	The path of peace they do not know.
B045C003V018	45	3	18	There is no reverence for God before their eyes."
B045C003V019	45	3	19	We know that all that the Law says, it says to those who are under the Law, that every mouth may be shut and all the world may come under the condemnation of God.
B045C003V020	45	3	20	Therefore by works of the Law no human being will be pronounced righteous before him. For through the Law comes the knowledge of sin.
B045C003V021	45	3	21	But now, apart from law, a righteousness of God has been revealed, confirmed by the Law and the Prophets \'97
B045C003V022	45	3	22	a righteousness from God through faith in Jesus Christ for all believers. For there is no difference.
B045C003V023	45	3	23	All have sinned and have come short of the glory of God.
B045C003V024	45	3	24	All are pronounced righteous by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus,
B045C003V025	45	3	25	whom God has set forth as a propitiation by his blood through faith, for the manifestation of his righteousness, because of the passing over of previous sins in the forbearance of God \'97
B045C003V026	45	3	26	for a manifestation at the present time of his righteousness, that he may himself be righteous and may accept as righteous him who has faith in Jesus.
B045C003V027	45	3	27	Where then is boasting? It is excluded. By what law? That of works? No, but by the law of faith.
B045C003V028	45	3	28	For we reason that a man is pronounced righteous by faith aside from works of law.
B045C003V029	45	3	29	Does God belong to the Jews only? Does he not belong also to the Gentiles? Yes, to the Gentiles,
B045C003V030	45	3	30	if God is one and will pronounce the circumcision righteous by faith and the uncircumcision righteous through faith.
B045C003V031	45	3	31	Do we then by faith nullify the Law? Never. On the contrary we establish the Law.
B045C004V001	45	4	1	WHAT then shall we say that Abraham, our forefather according to the flesh, experienced?
B045C004V002	45	4	2	For if Abraham was pronounced righteous because of works, he had something to boast of. But he had nothing before God;
B045C004V003	45	4	3	for what says the Scripture? "Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him for righteousness."
B045C004V004	45	4	4	To him who works, wages are credited not as by grace, but as due;
B045C004V005	45	4	5	but to him who does not work, but believes in him who calls the unrighteous man righteous, his faith is credited for righteousness.
B045C004V006	45	4	6	Just so David speaks of the blessedness of the man to whom God credits righteousness apart from works,
B045C004V007	45	4	7	"Blessed are they whose lawless acts have been forgiven, and whose sins have been covered over.
B045C004V008	45	4	8	Blessed is the man whose sin the Lord will not charge up to him."
B045C004V009	45	4	9	Does this blessedness come to the circumcision, or also to the uncircumcision? For we say, "Faith was credited to Abraham for righteousness."
B045C004V010	45	4	10	How was it credited, when he was in circumcision or in uncircumcision? Not in circumcision, but in uncircumcision.
B045C004V011	45	4	11	And he received the sign of circumcision as a seal of the righteousness of faith that he had in uncircumcision, so that he should be the father of all who believe while uncircumcised, and righteousness should be credited to them;
B045C004V012	45	4	12	and the father of the circumcised, that is, of those who are not only circumcised, but who walk in the steps of the faith which our father Abraham had while uncircumcised.
B045C004V013	45	4	13	It was not through the Law that the promise came to Abraham or to his descendants that he should be the heir of the world, but through the righteousness of faith.
B045C004V014	45	4	14	For if those who are of the Law are heirs, faith is emptied of value and the promise is nullified.
B045C004V015	45	4	15	For the Law works wrath. But where there is no law, neither is there lawbreaking.
B045C004V016	45	4	16	Therefore all depends on faith, that it may be of grace, and thus the promise be sure for all his descendants, not only those who are of the Law, but also those who are of the faith of Abraham, who is the father of all of us
B045C004V017	45	4	17	
        
B045C004V018	45	4	18	Abraham, when hope was past, believed in hope so that he became the father of many nations, according to what was said to him, "So shall your descendants be";
B045C004V019	45	4	19	and without being weakened in faith he recognized his own body as dead, when he was about a hundred years old, and the deadness of Sarah's womb.
B045C004V020	45	4	20	Still he did not hesitate through want of faith in the promise of God, but was strong in faith, thus giving glory to God,
B045C004V021	45	4	21	and was fully confident that what God had promised he was able to perform.
B045C004V022	45	4	22	Therefore it was credited to him for righteousness.
B045C004V023	45	4	23	It was not written for his sake only, that it was credited to him,
B045C004V024	45	4	24	but also for our sake, to whom it will be credited if we believe in him who raised up from the dead Jesus our Lord,
B045C004V025	45	4	25	who was delivered up on account of our sins and was raised again that we might be accounted righteous.
B045C005V001	45	5	1	SO then, since we have been accounted righteous by faith, let us have peace with God, through our Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C005V002	45	5	2	Through him we obtained entrance into this grace in which we stand and exult in hope of the glory of God.
B045C005V003	45	5	3	Not only so, but we also exult in trials, knowing that trial develops endurance,
B045C005V004	45	5	4	and endurance develops a tested character, and a tested character develops hope,
B045C005V005	45	5	5	and hope does not disappoint, for the love of God has been poured out in our hearts through the Holy Spirit granted to us.
B045C005V006	45	5	6	For while we were still without strength Christ, at the due time, died for the unrighteous.
B045C005V007	45	5	7	Hardly for a righteous man will any one die. For a good man some one perhaps may dare to die.
B045C005V008	45	5	8	But God shows his own love to us in that while we were still sinners Christ died for us.
B045C005V009	45	5	9	Much more then, now that we have been pronounced righteous through his blood, shall we be saved from wrath by him.
B045C005V010	45	5	10	For if while enemies we were reconciled to God through the death of his Son, much more, now that we are reconciled, shall we be saved by his life.
B045C005V011	45	5	11	And not only so, but we exult in God through our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom we have now obtained the reconciliation.
B045C005V012	45	5	12	Therefore as through one man sin entered the world, and through sin death entered, and so death spread to all men, since all sinned \'97
B045C005V013	45	5	13	for down to the time of the Law sin was in the world, and yet sin is not charged where there is no law;
B045C005V014	45	5	14	but death reigned from Adam to Moses even over those who had not sinned like Adam, who is the type of him who was coming.
B045C005V015	45	5	15	But the gracious gift is not like the fall. For if by the fall of the one the many sinned, much more did the grace of God and the free gift by the grace of the one man Jesus Christ abound to the many.
B045C005V016	45	5	16	And the free gift was not like the sentence that came through one who sinned; for the sentence came from one fall for condemnation, but the free gift was that men should be called righteous in spite of many falls.
B045C005V017	45	5	17	For if by the fall of one man death reigned through that one, much more those who receive the abounding grace and the free gift of righteousness will reign in life through one, that is, through Jesus Christ.
B045C005V018	45	5	18	As then through one fall sentence came upon all men and they were condemned; so through one righteous act the free gift came to all men so that they are pronounced righteous and live.
B045C005V019	45	5	19	For as by the disobedience of the one man the many were set down as sinners, so by the obedience of the one the many will be set down as righteous.
B045C005V020	45	5	20	But law came in alongside that the fall might be greater; but where sin became greater grace became greater still,
B045C005V021	45	5	21	in order that as sin reigned in death grace might reign through righteousness and issue in life eternal through Jesus Christ our Lord.
B045C006V001	45	6	1	WHAT shall we say then? Shall we remain in sin so that grace may be great?
B045C006V002	45	6	2	Never. How shall we who died to sin still live in it?
B045C006V003	45	6	3	Are you ignorant that all of us who have been baptized into Christ Jesus were baptized into his death?
B045C006V004	45	6	4	We were buried with him by baptism into death, in order that as Christ was raised from the dead through the glory of the Father, so we too might walk in newness of life.
B045C006V005	45	6	5	For if we have grown into union with him by the likeness of his death, surely we shall be united with him by the likeness of his resurrection.
B045C006V006	45	6	6	For we know this, that our old-time humanity was crucified with him, in order that the sinful body might be made powerless, that we might no longer be slaves of sin.
B045C006V007	45	6	7	For one who has died has been pronounced righteous and free from sin.
B045C006V008	45	6	8	But if we died with Christ we believe that we shall live with him,
B045C006V009	45	6	9	knowing that Christ, after being raised from the dead, dies no more; death no more reigns over him.
B045C006V010	45	6	10	For the death that he died, he died to sin once for all; but the life that he lives, he lives to God.
B045C006V011	45	6	11	So you must think yourselves dead to sin, but living to God in Christ Jesus.
B045C006V012	45	6	12	Do not let sin reign in your mortal body so that you will obey its lusts,
B045C006V013	45	6	13	and do not yield your members to sin as the instruments of wickedness; but present yourselves to God as men once dead, but now living, and yield your members to God as the instruments of righteousness.
B045C006V014	45	6	14	For sin shall not be king over you; for you are not under law, but under grace.
B045C006V015	45	6	15	What then? May we sin because we are not under law, but under grace? Never.
B045C006V016	45	6	16	Do you not know that to whom you present yourselves as servants intending obedience, you are the servants of the one you obey, whether of sin, resulting in death, or of obedience, resulting in righteousness?
B045C006V017	45	6	17	Thanks be to God that though you were slaves of sin you became obedient from the heart to the type of teaching in which you were instructed.
B045C006V018	45	6	18	You were made free from sin and made servants to righteousness.
B045C006V019	45	6	19	I am speaking humanly on account of the weakness of your human nature. As you did present your members as servants to impurity and to lawlessness to do lawlessness, so now you have presented your members as servants to righteousness for holy living.
B045C006V020	45	6	20	When you were servants of sin you were free from righteousness.
B045C006V021	45	6	21	What fruit did you have then? Fruit of which you are now ashamed; for the end of those things is death.
B045C006V022	45	6	22	But now freed from sin and having become servants of God you have your fruit in holy living and its outcome, life eternal.
B045C006V023	45	6	23	For the wages of sin is death, but the gracious gift of God is life eternal in Christ Jesus our Lord.
B045C007V001	45	7	1	ARE you ignorant, brethren, for I am speaking to those who know law, that the Law rules over a person while he is living?
B045C007V002	45	7	2	For a married woman is by law bound to her husband while he is living. But if the husband dies, she is freed from the law of her husband.
B045C007V003	45	7	3	Therefore while her husband is living she is called an adulteress if she becomes another man's. But if her husband dies she is free from the law, so that she is not an adulteress when she becomes another man's.
B045C007V004	45	7	4	So, my brethren, you were made dead to the Law through the body of Christ, that you might become wedded to another, to him who was raised from the dead, that we might bear fruit to God.
B045C007V005	45	7	5	For when we were in the flesh the sinful passions that arise through the Law were active in our members, so that we bore fruit to death.
B045C007V006	45	7	6	But now the Law has been made inoperative on us, since we have died to that by which we were held, so that we serve in newness of the spirit and not in oldness of the letter.
B045C007V007	45	7	7	What shall we say then? Is the Law sin? Never. But I should not have come to know sin except through the Law. I should not have known lust if the Law had not said, "Thou shalt not lust."
B045C007V008	45	7	8	Sin, taking occasion through the commandment, worked in me every lust. For apart from the Law sin is dead.
B045C007V009	45	7	9	I was living once, apart from law. But when the commandment came, sin began to live and I died,
B045C007V010	45	7	10	and the commandment which meant life was found to mean death.
B045C007V011	45	7	11	For sin, taking occasion through the commandment, deceived me and by it killed me.
B045C007V012	45	7	12	So the Law is holy and the commandment is holy and just and good.
B045C007V013	45	7	13	Did then what is good become death to me? Never. But sin, that it might appear sin, worked death in me through the good, in order that it might become beyond measure sinful.
B045C007V014	45	7	14	For we know that the Law is spiritual; but I am fleshly, sold under sin.
B045C007V015	45	7	15	For what I am doing I do not understand. For not what I choose is what I practice, but what I hate, this I do.
B045C007V016	45	7	16	But if I do what I do not choose, I agree with the law that it is right.
B045C007V017	45	7	17	And now it is no longer I that do it, but the Sin that dwells in me.
B045C007V018	45	7	18	
        
B045C007V019	45	7	19	
        
B045C007V020	45	7	20	
        
B045C007V021	45	7	21	I find then this rule, when I choose to do the right, that evil is present with me.
B045C007V022	45	7	22	I delight in the Law in my inner man,
B045C007V023	45	7	23	but I see another law in my members, warring with the law of my mind and leading me captive under the law of sin which is in my members.
B045C007V024	45	7	24	Wretched man that I am! who will deliver me from this body of death?
B045C007V025	45	7	25	Thanks be to God through Jesus Christ our Lord! So then I myself with my mind serve the Law of God, but with my flesh the law of sin.
B045C008V001	45	8	1	THERE is therefore now no condemnation to those who are in Christ Jesus.
B045C008V002	45	8	2	For the law of the Spirit of life in Christ Jesus has freed you from the Law of sin and death.
B045C008V003	45	8	3	For, what was impossible for the Law, because it was weak through the flesh \'97 God, sending his own Son in the form of sinful flesh and for sin, condemned the sin that is in the flesh,
B045C008V004	45	8	4	so that the righteousness required by the Law might be fulfilled in us who live not according to the flesh, but according to the spirit.
B045C008V005	45	8	5	For those who are living according to the flesh have their minds on the things of the flesh, but those who are living according to the spirit have their minds on the things of the spirit.
B045C008V006	45	8	6	Fleshly mindedness is death, but spiritual mindedness is life and peace.
B045C008V007	45	8	7	Therefore fleshly mindedness is hostile to God; for it is not subject to the Law of God, nor can it be.
B045C008V008	45	8	8	Those who are in the flesh cannot please God.
B045C008V009	45	8	9	But you are not in the flesh, but in the spirit, if the Spirit of God dwells in you. If any one has not the Spirit of Christ, that man is not his.
B045C008V010	45	8	10	If Christ is in you the body is dead because of sin, but the spirit is life because of righteousness.
B045C008V011	45	8	11	If the Spirit of him who raised up Jesus from the dead dwells in you, he who raised up Christ Jesus from the dead gives life even to your mortal bodies, through his indwelling Spirit in you.
B045C008V012	45	8	12	So then, brethren, we are debtors, not to the flesh to live according to the flesh;
B045C008V013	45	8	13	for if you live according to the flesh, you will die; but if by the Spirit you put to death the practices of the body, you will live.
B045C008V014	45	8	14	For as many as are led by the Spirit of God, they are the sons of God.
B045C008V015	45	8	15	For you did not receive a spirit of bondage leading again to fear, but you received a spirit of sonship, in which we cry, Abba, Father.
B045C008V016	45	8	16	The Spirit itself witnesses with our spirits that we are children of God.
B045C008V017	45	8	17	And if children, we are also heirs \'97 heirs of God, joint heirs with Christ, since we suffer with him that we may also be glorified with him.
B045C008V018	45	8	18	For I estimate that the sufferings of this present time amount to nothing in comparison with the glory that is to be revealed for us.
B045C008V019	45	8	19	For the earnest expectation of the creation is waiting for the revelation of the sons of God.
B045C008V020	45	8	20	For the creation was made subject to folly not willingly, but for the sake of him who subjected it, in hope,
B045C008V021	45	8	21	because the creation itself will be freed from the slavery of decay into the glorious freedom of the children of God.
B045C008V022	45	8	22	For we know that all the creation groans in the pangs of childbirth until now.
B045C008V023	45	8	23	And not the creation alone, but we ourselves also who have the first-fruits of the Spirit, groan within ourselves in expectation of the sonship, the liberation of our bodies.
B045C008V024	45	8	24	For we are saved by hope; but hope that is seen is not hope, for what any one sees, why does he hope for?
B045C008V025	45	8	25	But if we hope for what we do not see, we patiently wait for it.
B045C008V026	45	8	26	Thus also the Spirit helps us in our weakness. For we do not know what to pray for as we ought, but the Spirit itself intercedes for us with sighs beyond words.
B045C008V027	45	8	27	And he who searches hearts knows what is the mind of the Spirit, because he intercedes for the holy according to the will of God.
B045C008V028	45	8	28	We know that all things work together for good to those who love God, to those who are called according to his purpose.
B045C008V029	45	8	29	For those whom he foreknew he also predetermined to be conformed to the image of his Son, that he might be the first-born among many brethren.
B045C008V030	45	8	30	And those whom he predetermined he also called, and those whom he called he also pronounced righteous, and those whom he pronounced righteous he also glorified.
B045C008V031	45	8	31	What then shall we say to this? If God is for us, who is against us?
B045C008V032	45	8	32	He who did not spare his own Son, but gave him up for us all, how shall he not with him graciously give us all things?
B045C008V033	45	8	33	Who shall bring a charge against God's elect? God pronounces them righteous.
B045C008V034	45	8	34	Who is there to condemn? Christ Jesus died, or rather was raised, and he is on the right hand of God interceding for us.
B045C008V035	45	8	35	Who shall separate us from Christ's love? Shall trial or distress or persecution or famine or nakedness or danger or sword?
B045C008V036	45	8	36	
        
B045C008V037	45	8	37	On the contrary, in all these we more than conquer through him who loved us.
B045C008V038	45	8	38	For I am persuaded that neither death nor life nor angels nor archangels, nor things present nor things to come, nor powers,
B045C008V039	45	8	39	nor height nor depth nor any other created thing will be able to separate us from God's love in Christ Jesus our Lord.
B045C009V001	45	9	1	I AM speaking the truth in Christ; I am saying nothing false; my conscience bears witness with me in the Holy Spirit
B045C009V002	45	9	2	that I have great grief and unceasing pain in my heart.
B045C009V003	45	9	3	For I could wish myself to be accursed and cast away from Christ for the sake of my brethren, my kinsmen according to the flesh,
B045C009V004	45	9	4	who are Israelites, whose is the sonship and the glory and the covenants and the reception of the law and the worship and the promises;
B045C009V005	45	9	5	whose are the fathers and from whom by physical descent the Christ came. God who is over all be blessed through the ages! Amen.
B045C009V006	45	9	6	Not that God's word has failed. For not all who are of Israel are Israel;
B045C009V007	45	9	7	nor because they are descendants of Abraham are they all children; but "through Isaac shall your descendants be named."
B045C009V008	45	9	8	That is, not the physical descendants are children, but the children of the promise are counted for descendants.
B045C009V009	45	9	9	For the wording of the promise was, "At this time next year I will come and Sarah shall have a son."
B045C009V010	45	9	10	And not only so, but when Rebecca was about to bear children to our father Isaac,
B045C009V011	45	9	11	though the same man was father of both children and they were not yet born and had done nothing good or bad, in order that the purpose of God according to his choice might stand, not according to their works, but according to his call,
B045C009V012	45	9	12	it was said to her, "The older shall serve the younger."
B045C009V013	45	9	13	In the same way it is written, "Jacob I loved, but Esau I hated."
B045C009V014	45	9	14	What shall we say then? Is there unrighteousness on God's part? Never.
B045C009V015	45	9	15	For he says to Moses, "I will have mercy on whom I have mercy and I will have compassion on whom I have compassion."
B045C009V016	45	9	16	So then it is not a question of the man who wills or who runs, but of God who shows mercy.
B045C009V017	45	9	17	For the Scripture says to Pharaoh, "For this very purpose I raised you up in order to show my power upon you and to have my name proclaimed in all the earth."
B045C009V018	45	9	18	So then he has mercy on whom he chooses and he hardens whom he chooses.
B045C009V019	45	9	19	You will say to me then, "Why does he still find fault? For who has opposed his will?"
B045C009V020	45	9	20	But who are you, O man, who are answering back to God? Does the thing that is moulded say to the moulder, "Why have you made me so?"
B045C009V021	45	9	21	Has not the potter the right to make from the same lump of clay one vessel for honor and another for dishonor?
B045C009V022	45	9	22	What if God, choosing to exhibit his wrath and to make known what he can do, bore in long patience the vessels of wrath made for destruction,
B045C009V023	45	9	23	and in order to make known the richness of his glory upon the vessels of mercy which he had prepared for glory
B045C009V024	45	9	24	called us not only from the Jews but also from the Gentiles?
B045C009V025	45	9	25	As also he says in Hosea, "Those who are not my people I will call my people, and her who has not been beloved I will call beloved,
B045C009V026	45	9	26	and in the place where it was said to them, 'You are not my people,' there they shall be called sons of the living God."
B045C009V027	45	9	27	Isaiah cried aloud regarding Israel, "Though the number of the sons of Israel is as the sand of the sea, only a remnant will be saved.
B045C009V028	45	9	28	For the Lord will execute his sentence on the earth completely and speedily."
B045C009V029	45	9	29	Even as Isaiah predicted, "Unless the Lord of armies had left us some descendants, we should have become like Sodom and should have been made to resemble Gomorrah."
B045C009V030	45	9	30	What shall we say then? That Gentiles who did not pursue righteousness obtained righteousness, the righteousness of faith,
B045C009V031	45	9	31	but Israel pursuing after the Law of righteousness did not attain to the Law.
B045C009V032	45	9	32	Why? Because they pursued it not by faith, but as it were by works. They stumbled over that stumbling stone,
B045C009V033	45	9	33	as it is written, "See, I am laying in Zion a stumbling stone, a rock to trip over, but he who has faith in him will never be put to shame."
B045C010V001	45	10	1	BRETHREN, the desire of my heart and my prayer to God for them is for their salvation.
B045C010V002	45	10	2	For I bear them witness that they have a zeal for God, but not an intelligent one.
B045C010V003	45	10	3	For, ignorant of God's righteousness and seeking to establish their own, they have not submitted to God's righteousness.
B045C010V004	45	10	4	For Christ is the end of the Law for righteousness to every believer.
B045C010V005	45	10	5	For Moses writes that he who does the righteousness of the Law shall live by it.
B045C010V006	45	10	6	But the righteousness of faith says, "Do not say in your heart, 'Who shall ascend into heaven?' that is, to bring Christ down \'97 "
B045C010V007	45	10	7	or, 'Who shall descend into the abyss?' " \'97 that is, to bring up Christ from the dead.
B045C010V008	45	10	8	But what does it say? "The word is near you, in your mouth and in your heart" \'97 that is, the word of faith which we are proclaiming,
B045C010V009	45	10	9	that if you confess with your mouth the Lord Jesus and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead you will be saved.
B045C010V010	45	10	10	For with the heart a man believes and becomes righteous, and with the mouth he confesses and attains salvation.
B045C010V011	45	10	11	For the Scripture says, "No one who believes in him will be put to shame."
B045C010V012	45	10	12	For there is no difference between Jew and Greek. For there is the same Lord of all, rich toward all who call upon him.
B045C010V013	45	10	13	For "Every one who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved."
B045C010V014	45	10	14	How then shall they call on him in whom they have not believed? How shall they believe in him of whom they have not heard? How shall they hear without some one to proclaim him?
B045C010V015	45	10	15	How shall they proclaim him unless they are sent? As it is written, "How beautiful are the feet of those who bring good news!"
B045C010V016	45	10	16	But have not all heard the good news? For Isaiah says, "Lord, who has believed our report?"
B045C010V017	45	10	17	So then faith comes from the report and report comes through the word of Christ.
B045C010V018	45	10	18	But I say, it cannot be true that they have not heard, can it? On the contrary, "Their sound has gone out into all the earth and their words to the ends of the world."
B045C010V019	45	10	19	I say, it cannot be that Israel did not know, can it? First Moses says, "I will excite you to jealousy by what is not a nation and by a foolish nation I will provoke you to anger."
B045C010V020	45	10	20	And Isaiah makes bold to say, "I was found by those who were not seeking me: I became manifest to those who were not inquiring for me."
B045C010V021	45	10	21	But to Israel he says, "All day long I stretched forth my hands to a people who disobey and answer back."
B045C011V001	45	11	1	I SAY then, can it be that God has repudiated his people? Never. For I am an Israelite, a descendant of Abraham, of the tribe of Benjamin.
B045C011V002	45	11	2	God has not repudiated his people whom he foreknew. Do you not know what the Scripture says in the story of Elijah, how he prays to God against Israel?
B045C011V003	45	11	3	"Lord, they have killed thy prophets: they have demolished thy altars, and I only am left and they are seeking my life."
B045C011V004	45	11	4	But what was the divine response? "I have left to myself seven thousand men who have not knelt to Baal."
B045C011V005	45	11	5	So at this present time there is a remnant according to a gracious selection.
B045C011V006	45	11	6	But if it is by grace it is no longer because of works, for then grace would be no longer grace.
B045C011V007	45	11	7	What then? Israel has not found what it is seeking, but the chosen have found it. And the rest have been made dull,
B045C011V008	45	11	8	as it is written, "God gave them a stupid spirit, eyes not for seeing and ears not for hearing until this day."
B045C011V009	45	11	9	And David says, "Let their table become a snare and a trap, a stumbling block and a retribution.
B045C011V010	45	11	10	Let their eyes be darkened so as not to see, and bow down their backs always."
B045C011V011	45	11	11	I say, then, have they stumbled just in order that they may fall? Never. But by their fall salvation comes to the Gentiles so as to arouse the emulation of the Jews.
B045C011V012	45	11	12	If their fall is the riches of the world and their loss the riches of the Gentiles, how much more will their full restoration be!
B045C011V013	45	11	13	But I say to you Gentiles \'97 since I am an apostle to Gentiles I glory in my office,
B045C011V014	45	11	14	if in any way I may arouse to emulation my own kindred and save some of them \'97
B045C011V015	45	11	15	if their rejection is the reconciliation of the world, what will their welcome back be but life from the dead?
B045C011V016	45	11	16	If the first fruit was holy, so will the mass be; and if the root was holy, so will be the branches.
B045C011V017	45	11	17	If some of the branches were broken off and you, who are a wild olive, were grafted in among them and became a sharer in the root and rich sap of the olive,
B045C011V018	45	11	18	do not exult over the branches. Even though you exult, it is not you who are supporting the root, but the root is supporting you.
B045C011V019	45	11	19	You will say then, "Branches were broken off so that I might be grafted in."
B045C011V020	45	11	20	Certainly, for lack of faith they were broken off, and you are standing by faith. Do not be proud, but be afraid.
B045C011V021	45	11	21	For if God did not spare the natural branches, neither will he spare you.
B045C011V022	45	11	22	See the kindness and the rigor of God, toward those who fell rigor, but toward you God's kindness, if you continue in his kindness, else you too will be cut off.
B045C011V023	45	11	23	And they if they do not continue in their unbelief will be grafted in.
B045C011V024	45	11	24	For God is able to graft them back. For if you were cut from your natural stock, a wild olive tree, and were grafted, contrary to nature, into a good olive tree, how much more will the natural branches be grafted into their own olive tree!
B045C011V025	45	11	25	I would not have you ignorant, brethren, of this mystery, that you may not be self-conceited, because stupidity in a measure has come upon Israel until the full number of Gentiles comes in,
B045C011V026	45	11	26	and thus all Israel will be saved, as it is written, "From Zion will come the deliverer. He will remove ungodliness from Jacob.
B045C011V027	45	11	27	And this is my covenant with them when I take away their sins."
B045C011V028	45	11	28	According to the good news they are enemies for your sake, but according to the promise they are beloved for their fathers' sake.
B045C011V029	45	11	29	God never changes his mind about his gifts and his call.
B045C011V030	45	11	30	For as you were once disobedient to God, but now have found mercy through their disobedience,
B045C011V031	45	11	31	so they have now been disobedient in your time of mercy, that they too may now obtain mercy.
B045C011V032	45	11	32	For God has shut up all in unbelief in order that he may have mercy on all.
B045C011V033	45	11	33	O the depth of the wealth both of the wisdom and the knowledge of God! How unsearchable are his judgments, how untraceable his ways!
B045C011V034	45	11	34	For who has known the mind of the Lord? Or who became his counsellor?
B045C011V035	45	11	35	Who first gave to him so as to receive repayment?
B045C011V036	45	11	36	For from him and through him and to him are all things. To him be glory through the ages! Amen.
B045C012V001	45	12	1	I BEG you therefore, brethren, by the mercies of God, to present your bodies as a living and holy sacrifice, pleasing to God \'97 your rational worship.
B045C012V002	45	12	2	Do not follow the fashions of this world, but be transformed by the renewal of your minds so as to recognize what is the good and pleasing and perfect will of God.
B045C012V003	45	12	3	Through the grace given to me I say to every one among you not to think of himself more highly than he ought, but to think so as to become wise, as God has allotted to each a measure of faith.
B045C012V004	45	12	4	For as in one body we have many members and the members do not all have the same function,
B045C012V005	45	12	5	so we who are many are one body in Christ and individually members of one another.
B045C012V006	45	12	6	Having gifts differing according to the grace given to us, if it is prophecy, let us use it according to the proportion of our faith;
B045C012V007	45	12	7	if it is service, let us use it in service. Let the teacher use his gift in teaching.
B045C012V008	45	12	8	Let the exhorter use his gift in exhorting. Let him who gives do it in simplicity. Let him who manages do it earnestly. Let him who helps the needy do it cheerfully.
B045C012V009	45	12	9	Let your love be without pretense. Abhor what is evil; cling to the good.
B045C012V010	45	12	10	Have brotherly love toward one another like family affection, in honor preferring one another,
B045C012V011	45	12	11	never flagging in zeal, fervent in spirit, serving the Lord,
B045C012V012	45	12	12	rejoicing in hope, patient in trial, constant in prayer,
B045C012V013	45	12	13	contributing to the needs of the holy, devoted to hospitality.
B045C012V014	45	12	14	Pray for blessings on your persecutors, blessings, not curses.
B045C012V015	45	12	15	Rejoice with those who rejoice, weep with those who weep.
B045C012V016	45	12	16	Be in harmony with one another. Do not be thinking of high things, but be content with humble things. Do not become conceited.
B045C012V017	45	12	17	Repay to no one evil for evil. Aim at what is honorable in the sight of all men.
B045C012V018	45	12	18	If possible, so far as depends on you, live at peace with all men.
B045C012V019	45	12	19	Do not revenge yourselves, beloved, but give place to God's wrath. For it is written, "Vengeance is mine; I will repay, says the Lord."
B045C012V020	45	12	20	But, "if your enemy is hungry, feed him; if he is thirsty, give him drink; for in so doing you will heap coals of fire on his head."
B045C012V021	45	12	21	Do not be overcome by evil, but overcome evil with good.
B045C013V001	45	13	1	LET every person be obedient to the superior authorities. For there is no authority except from God and the actual authorities have been appointed by God.
B045C013V002	45	13	2	So he who resists the authority opposes the arrangement of God. Those who resist will bring on themselves condemnation.
B045C013V003	45	13	3	For rulers are not a terror to good deeds, but to bad. Do you wish not to fear the authority? Do what is good and you will have praise from it.
B045C013V004	45	13	4	For he is a servant of God to promote your good. But if you are doing evil, be afraid; for he does not bear the sword to no purpose. For he is God's servant to inflict his wrath on him who practices evil.
B045C013V005	45	13	5	Therefore we must be obedient, not only because of the punishment but as a matter of conscience.
B045C013V006	45	13	6	For this reason also you pay tribute. For they are God's officers attending to this very thing.
B045C013V007	45	13	7	Pay to all their dues, tribute to whom tribute is due, custom to whom custom is due, respect to whom respect is due, honor to whom honor is due.
B045C013V008	45	13	8	Owe no one anything, except to love one another. He who loves the other has fulfilled the Law.
B045C013V009	45	13	9	For the commandments, "Thou shalt not commit adultery," "Thou shalt not commit murder," "Thou shalt not steal," "Thou shalt not covet," and any other that there may be, are summed up in this: "Thou shalt love thy neighbor as thyself."
B045C013V010	45	13	10	Love works no evil to a neighbor. Love therefore is full obedience to the Law.
B045C013V011	45	13	11	Live thus because you know this crisis, for it is already time for you to awake from sleep. For now our salvation is nearer than when we became believers.
B045C013V012	45	13	12	The night is far spent, the day draws near. Let us put away the deeds of darkness, let us put on the weapons of light.
B045C013V013	45	13	13	Let us live becomingly as in the day, not in revelry and drunkenness, not in sensuality and licentiousness, not in quarrelling and jealousy.
B045C013V014	45	13	14	But put on the Lord Jesus Christ and make no provision for gratifying physical passions.
B045C014V001	45	14	1	WELCOME him who is weak in the faith, but not in order to decide disputed questions.
B045C014V002	45	14	2	One man believes in eating all things. The weak man eats vegetables.
B045C014V003	45	14	3	The man who eats is not to despise the one who does not eat, and he who does not eat is not to judge the one who eats. For God has accepted him.
B045C014V004	45	14	4	Who are you to judge the servant of another? To his own master he stands or falls, and stand he will, for God is able to make him stand.
B045C014V005	45	14	5	One man esteems one day above another, another man esteems every day. Let each be fully persuaded in his own mind.
B045C014V006	45	14	6	He who regards the day regards it to the Lord and he who eats eats to the Lord, for he gives thanks to God. And he who does not eat abstains for the Lord and gives thanks to God.
B045C014V007	45	14	7	For no one of us is living for himself and no one dies for himself.
B045C014V008	45	14	8	If we live we live for the Lord and if we die we die for the Lord. So whether we live or die we are the Lord's.
B045C014V009	45	14	9	For to this end Christ died and lived again, in order that he might be Lord both of the dead and of the living.
B045C014V010	45	14	10	But you, why do you judge your brother? Or you, why do you treat your brother with contempt? For we shall all stand before the judgment seat of God.
B045C014V011	45	14	11	For it is written, "As I live, says the Lord, every knee shall bend to me and every tongue shall confess to God."
B045C014V012	45	14	12	So then each one of us shall give account for himself to God.
B045C014V013	45	14	13	Therefore let us no longer judge one another, but let us rather decide not to put a stumbling block in a brother's way, or anything to trip him up.
B045C014V014	45	14	14	I know and am persuaded in the Lord Jesus that nothing is defiling in itself. But to one who thinks anything to be defiling it is defiling.
B045C014V015	45	14	15	If because of your food your brother is grieved, you are no longer walking in love. Do not with your food destroy him for whom Christ died.
B045C014V016	45	14	16	Do not let what is good to you be spoken of as evil.
B045C014V017	45	14	17	For the kingdom of God is not food and drink, but righteousness and peace and joy in the Holy Spirit.
B045C014V018	45	14	18	For he who thus serves Christ is pleasing to God and esteemed by men.
B045C014V019	45	14	19	Therefore, let us seek for what makes for peace and our mutual upbuilding.
B045C014V020	45	14	20	Do not for the sake of food break down the work of God. All things are pure, but anything is evil to the man who eats it with a feeling of doing wrong.
B045C014V021	45	14	21	It is noble not to eat meat or to drink wine or to do anything over which your brother stumbles.
B045C014V022	45	14	22	The faith that you have, have to yourself before God. Blessed is the man who does not condemn himself for what he allows himself.
B045C014V023	45	14	23	He who has doubts and still eats stands condemned, because he is not acting from faith. But whatever does not spring from faith is sin.
B045C015V001	45	15	1	WE who are strong ought to bear the infirmities of the weak, and not to please ourselves.
B045C015V002	45	15	2	Each of us should please his neighbor for his good so as to build him up.
B045C015V003	45	15	3	For Christ did not please himself, but, as it is written, "The reproaches of those who were reproaching thee fell on me."
B045C015V004	45	15	4	All that was written of old was written for our instruction, in order that by patience and by the encouragement of the Scriptures we may have hope.
B045C015V005	45	15	5	May the God of patience and encouragement grant to you to have harmony with one another, in the manner of Christ Jesus,
B045C015V006	45	15	6	so that with one mind and one voice you may glorify the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C015V007	45	15	7	Therefore, welcome one another as Christ welcomed us, to the glory of God.
B045C015V008	45	15	8	For I say that Christ became a servant of circumcision for the sake of God's truth, in order to confirm the promises given to the fathers
B045C015V009	45	15	9	and that the Gentiles might glorify God for his mercy, as it is written, "For this will I confess thee among the Gentiles and sing to thy name."
B045C015V010	45	15	10	And again Scripture says, "Rejoice, Gentiles, with his people."
B045C015V011	45	15	11	And again, "Sing to the Lord, all Gentiles, and let all the peoples praise him."
B045C015V012	45	15	12	And again Isaiah says, "There will be a root of Jesse, and one who rises to rule Gentiles: in him Gentiles will hope."
B045C015V013	45	15	13	May the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing, so that you may abound in hope through the power of the Holy Spirit!
B045C015V014	45	15	14	I am persuaded, my brethren \'97 yes, I myself \'97 regarding you, that you are full of goodness, filled with all knowledge, able to instruct one another.
B045C015V015	45	15	15	But I have written rather boldly to you, partly to remind you, because of the grace given to me from God,
B045C015V016	45	15	16	that I may be a minister of Christ Jesus to the Gentiles, in priestly service of the good news of God, in order that the offering of the Gentiles may be acceptable, sanctified by the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V017	45	15	17	I do boast in Christ Jesus of my work for God.
B045C015V018	45	15	18	For I will not venture to speak except of what Christ has done through me to promote obedience of Gentiles, by word and deed,
B045C015V019	45	15	19	through the power of signs and wonders, by the power of the Holy Spirit, so that from Jerusalem around to Illyricum, I have fully proclaimed the good news of Christ,
B045C015V020	45	15	20	being ambitious to tell the good news where Christ has not been named, so that I might not build on any other man's foundation,
B045C015V021	45	15	21	but as it is written, "They who have had no message of him shall see and they who have not heard shall understand."
B045C015V022	45	15	22	This is why I have been so much hindered in coming to you.
B045C015V023	45	15	23	But now having no more territory in these regions and having for many years had a strong desire to come to you
B045C015V024	45	15	24	while making a journey to Spain, I hope to see you as I pass through and to be furthered on my journey by you, after first partially satisfying my desire of being with you.
B045C015V025	45	15	25	But now I am on my way to Jerusalem to render service to the holy.
B045C015V026	45	15	26	For Macedonia and Achaia have been pleased to make a contribution for the poor among the holy in Jerusalem.
B045C015V027	45	15	27	They have been pleased to do this and indeed they are indebted to them. For if the Gentiles have shared their things of the spirit, they owe them sacred service in things of the body.
B045C015V028	45	15	28	So after completing this and sealing to them this fruit, I shall come away and pass by you to Spain.
B045C015V029	45	15	29	And I know that when I come to you it will be in the fullness of the blessing of Christ.
B045C015V030	45	15	30	I beg you, brethren, for the sake of our Lord Jesus and the love of the Spirit to join me in wrestling in prayer to God on my behalf,
B045C015V031	45	15	31	that I may be delivered from the unbelievers in Judaea and that my service in Jerusalem may be pleasing to the holy,
B045C015V032	45	15	32	that I may come to you with joy by the will of God and be refreshed with you.
B045C015V033	45	15	33	The God of peace be with all of you! Amen.
B045C016V001	45	16	1	I COMMEND to you our sister Phoebe, a servant of the church in Cenchreae,
B045C016V002	45	16	2	that you may receive her in the Lord in a way worthy of the holy, and help her in any matter in which she may need you. For she has been a provider for many, myself included.
B045C016V003	45	16	3	Give my greetings to Prisca and Aquila, my fellow workers in Christ Jesus,
B045C016V004	45	16	4	who for my life risked their own necks, to whom not I alone give thanks, but also all the churches of the Gentiles.
B045C016V005	45	16	5	Give my greetings also to the church in their house. Give my greetings to Epaenetus my beloved, who is the first-fruit of Asia for Christ.
B045C016V006	45	16	6	Give my greetings to Mary, who has worked hard for you.
B045C016V007	45	16	7	Give my greetings to Andronicus and Junias, men of my race and my companions in prison, who are eminent among the apostles, who also were in Christ before me.
B045C016V008	45	16	8	Give my greetings to Ampliatus my beloved in the Lord.
B045C016V009	45	16	9	Give my greetings to Urbanus our fellow worker in Christ, and to Stachys my beloved.
B045C016V010	45	16	10	Give my greetings to Apelles, that tested man in Christ. Give my greetings to the household of Aristobulus.
B045C016V011	45	16	11	Give my greetings to Herodion, who is of my race. Give my greetings to those of the household of Narcissus who are in the Lord.
B045C016V012	45	16	12	Give my greetings to Tryphaena and Tryphosa, those workers in the Lord. Give my greetings to Persis the beloved, who has worked hard in the Lord.
B045C016V013	45	16	13	Give my greetings to Rufus the chosen in the Lord, and to his mother and mine.
B045C016V014	45	16	14	Give my greetings to Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Petrobas, Hermas, and the brethren with them.
B045C016V015	45	16	15	Give my greetings to Philologus, and Julia, Nereus and his sister, and Olympas, and all the holy with them.
B045C016V016	45	16	16	Give my greetings to one another with a holy kiss. All the churches of Christ send their greetings to you.
B045C016V017	45	16	17	I beg you, brethren, to keep your eye on those who are making divisions and occasions for sin contrary to the teaching which you have learned, and to shun them.
B045C016V018	45	16	18	For such persons are not serving our Lord Christ, but their own stomachs, and by their smooth and pleasing talk they mislead the hearts of the innocent.
B045C016V019	45	16	19	For your obedience has come to the knowledge of all men. Therefore I rejoice over you, but I wish you to be wise regarding what is good, and simple in regard to what is evil.
B045C016V020	45	16	20	The God of peace will crush Satan under your feet shortly. The grace of our Lord Jesus be with you!
B045C016V021	45	16	21	Timothy, my fellow worker, sends his greeting, and so do Lucius and Jason and Sosipater, who are of my race.
B045C016V022	45	16	22	I, Tertius, who penned this letter, greet you in the Lord.
B045C016V023	45	16	23	Gaius, my host and the host of the whole church, sends his greetings. Erastus the city treasurer sends his greetings, and so does Quartus the brother.
B045C016V024	45	16	24	
        
B045C016V025	45	16	25	To him who is able to make you strong according to the good news which I bear, and the proclamation of Jesus Christ, and according to the revelation of the mystery kept secret through ages,
B045C016V026	45	16	26	but now made manifest through the prophetic Scriptures by the command of the eternal God, to promote obedience to the faith made known to all the Gentiles \'97
B045C016V027	45	16	27	to God, the only wise, be glory through Jesus Christ for the ages of the ages!
B046C001V001	46	1	1	PAUL called by the will of God to be an apostle of Christ Jesus, and Sosthenes our brother,
B046C001V002	46	1	2	to the Church of God in Corinth, made holy in Christ Jesus, called to be holy, with all everywhere who call upon the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, their Lord and ours:
B046C001V003	46	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and from the Lord Jesus Christ!
B046C001V004	46	1	4	I am always thanking God for you because of the grace of God given to you in Christ Jesus,
B046C001V005	46	1	5	that you are rich in him in everything, in readiness of speech and in all knowledge,
B046C001V006	46	1	6	so that my testimony to Christ has been confirmed among you
B046C001V007	46	1	7	and so that you are not lacking in any gift while waiting for our Lord Jesus Christ to be revealed.
B046C001V008	46	1	8	He will keep you strong to the end and free from reproach on the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V009	46	1	9	God is faithful, and it is by him that you have been called into the fellowship of his Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.
B046C001V010	46	1	10	I beg you, brethren, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, all to say the same thing and not to have divisions among you, but to be united in the same mind and in the same opinion.
B046C001V011	46	1	11	For it has been told me regarding you, brethren, by Chloe's people, that there are dissensions among you.
B046C001V012	46	1	12	I mean that each of you is saying, "I belong to Paul," "I belong to Apollos," "I belong to Cephas," or, "I belong to Christ."
B046C001V013	46	1	13	Has Christ been divided? Was Paul crucified for you? Or were you baptized in the name of Paul?
B046C001V014	46	1	14	I am thankful that I baptized no one of you except Crispus and Gaius,
B046C001V015	46	1	15	so that no one can say that you were baptized in my name.
B046C001V016	46	1	16	I baptized also the household of Stephanas. Beyond that I do not know that I baptized any one else.
B046C001V017	46	1	17	For Christ did not send me to baptize, but to proclaim the good news \'97 not in wisdom of words, that the cross of Christ might not be emptied of meaning.
B046C001V018	46	1	18	For the message of the cross is foolishness to those who are perishing, but to us who are being saved it is the power of God.
B046C001V019	46	1	19	For it is written, "I will destroy the wisdom of the wise and I will bring to nought the prudence of the prudent."
B046C001V020	46	1	20	Where is the wise? Where is the scribe? Where is the debater of this world? Has not God made foolish the wisdom of the world?
B046C001V021	46	1	21	For when in the wisdom of God the world by its wisdom did not come to know God, God was pleased to save through the foolishness of our proclamation those who believe.
B046C001V022	46	1	22	Jews ask for signs and Greeks seek for wisdom,
B046C001V023	46	1	23	but we proclaim Christ crucified, to Jews a stumbling block, to Gentiles folly,
B046C001V024	46	1	24	but to those who are called, whether Jews or Greeks, Christ, the power of God and the wisdom of God.
B046C001V025	46	1	25	For God's foolishness is wiser than men and God's weakness is stronger than men.
B046C001V026	46	1	26	Consider your own call, brethren, that not many wise, humanly speaking, not many powerful, not many high-born have been called.
B046C001V027	46	1	27	But God has chosen the foolish things of the world to put to shame the wise, and God has chosen the weak things of the world to put to shame the strong,
B046C001V028	46	1	28	and God has chosen the low-born things and the things of no account, the things that are not, to defeat the things that are,
B046C001V029	46	1	29	that no human being may boast in God's presence.
B046C001V030	46	1	30	By God's act you are in Christ Jesus, who has become to us wisdom from God and righteousness and holiness and deliverance,
B046C001V031	46	1	31	so that, as it is written, "Let him who boasts boast in the Lord."
B046C002V001	46	2	1	AND I in coming to you, brethren, did not come with superiority of speech or of wisdom, announcing to you the testimony of God.
B046C002V002	46	2	2	For I determined to know nothing among you but Jesus Christ \'97 and him crucified.
B046C002V003	46	2	3	And I came to you in weakness and in fear and in much trembling,
B046C002V004	46	2	4	and my speech and my proclamation were not in persuasive words of wisdom, but with spiritual and powerful proof,
B046C002V005	46	2	5	that your faith might not depend on the wisdom of man but on the power of God.
B046C002V006	46	2	6	We do speak wisdom among the mature, but a wisdom not of this world nor of the defeated rulers of this world.
B046C002V007	46	2	7	But we speak a wisdom of God in a mystery, the hidden wisdom which God predestined before the world began for our glory.
B046C002V008	46	2	8	None of the rulers of this world knew it, for if they had known it they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.
B046C002V009	46	2	9	But as it is written, "What eye has not seen and what ear has not heard and what has not entered human mind, God has prepared for those who love him."
B046C002V010	46	2	10	To us God has revealed this by his Spirit. For the Spirit searches all things, even the depths of God.
B046C002V011	46	2	11	For who of men knows what pertains to a man except the spirit of the man which is in him. Just so no one knows what pertains to God except the Spirit of God.
B046C002V012	46	2	12	But we did not receive the spirit of the world, but the Spirit that is from God, so that we know the gracious gifts of God.
B046C002V013	46	2	13	And these we speak of, not in words taught by man's wisdom, but in words taught by the Spirit, expressing spiritual things in spiritual words.
B046C002V014	46	2	14	But the animal man does not receive the things of the Spirit of God, for they are foolishness to him, nor can he know them because they are spiritually understood.
B046C002V015	46	2	15	But the spiritual man understands all things though he himself is understood by no one.
B046C002V016	46	2	16	For "Who has known the mind of the Lord? Who will teach him?" But we have the mind of Christ.
B046C003V001	46	3	1	AND I myself, brethren, could not speak to you as spiritual, but as fleshly, as babes in Christ.
B046C003V002	46	3	2	I fed you with milk, not solid food. For you were not able to take it. Nor are you yet able, for you are still fleshly.
B046C003V003	46	3	3	For while there is jealousy and strife among you, are you not fleshly and living in man's way?
B046C003V004	46	3	4	For when one says, "I belong to Paul," and another, "I belong to Apollos," are you not men?
B046C003V005	46	3	5	What then is Apollos? What is Paul? Servants through whom you were led to faith, as the Lord granted to each of us.
B046C003V006	46	3	6	I planted, Apollos watered, but God made the seed grow.
B046C003V007	46	3	7	So then neither is he who planted anything nor he who watered, but God who makes the seed grow.
B046C003V008	46	3	8	Each will receive his own reward according to his own labor.
B046C003V009	46	3	9	We are God's fellow workers: you are God's farm God's building.
B046C003V010	46	3	10	According to the grace of God granted to me, as a wise master-builder I have laid a foundation and another is building on it. But let each be careful how he builds on it.
B046C003V011	46	3	11	For no one can lay any other foundation than that which has been laid, which is Jesus Christ.
B046C003V012	46	3	12	If any one builds on this foundation gold, silver, costly stones, wood, hay, straw \'97
B046C003V013	46	3	13	every one's work will become manifest. For the day will show it, because it will be revealed in fire and the fire will test each one's work, of what quality it is.
B046C003V014	46	3	14	If the work which any one has built stands he will get a reward.
B046C003V015	46	3	15	If any one's work burns up he will suffer loss, though he himself will be saved, but as through fire.
B046C003V016	46	3	16	Do you not know that you are God's temple and the Spirit of God dwells in you?
B046C003V017	46	3	17	If any one mars the temple of God, God will mar him, for the temple of God is holy, and you are the temple.
B046C003V018	46	3	18	Let no one deceive himself. If any one of you thinks himself wise in this world, let him become a fool in order to become wise.
B046C003V019	46	3	19	For the wisdom of this world is foolishness in God's sight. For it is written, "He catches the wise in their own craftiness,"
B046C003V020	46	3	20	and again, "The Lord knows the reasonings of the wise to be futile."
B046C003V021	46	3	21	Therefore let no one boast in men. For all things are yours \'97
B046C003V022	46	3	22	Paul or Apollos or Cephas or the world or life or death or things present or things to come \'97 all are yours
B046C003V023	46	3	23	and you are Christ's and Christ is God's.
B046C004V001	46	4	1	LET a man view us as servants of Christ and stewards of God's mysteries.
B046C004V002	46	4	2	Moreover, in the case of stewards it is required that a man be found faithful.
B046C004V003	46	4	3	But it is of very slight importance to me to be judged by you or any human court. I do not even pass judgment on myself.
B046C004V004	46	4	4	For I am not conscious of any wrong, but I am not proved by that to be faultless. The Lord is my judge.
B046C004V005	46	4	5	So do not judge anything before the time, before the Lord comes. He will throw light on the hidden things of darkness and will make manifest the purposes of hearts. Then each one will have his praise from God.
B046C004V006	46	4	6	All this, brethren, I have applied to myself and Apollos for your sake, that you may learn the maxim, "Nothing beyond what is written," and may not be puffed up in partisanship for one against the other.
B046C004V007	46	4	7	For who gives you superiority? What have you that you did not receive? Why are you boasting as if you had not received it?
B046C004V008	46	4	8	You are already fully satisfied. You have already become rich. You have become kings without us. Would that you had become kings so that we might be kings with you!
B046C004V009	46	4	9	For it seems to me that God has set us apostles out last of all as men doomed to death, that we may be a spectacle to the world and to angels and to men.
B046C004V010	46	4	10	We are fools for Christ's sake, but you are wise in Christ; we are weak, but you are strong; you have glory, but we are despised.
B046C004V011	46	4	11	Up to this present hour we are hungry and thirsty and naked and beaten. We wander about
B046C004V012	46	4	12	and labor, working with our own hands. When abused we bless, when persecuted we endure it,
B046C004V013	46	4	13	when slandered we entreat. We have come to be, as it were, the sweepings of the world, the riffraff of all things up to now.
B046C004V014	46	4	14	I am not writing this to shame you, but to warn you as my beloved children.
B046C004V015	46	4	15	For if you have ten thousand teachers in Christ, still you have not many fathers. For I was your father in Christ Jesus through the good news.
B046C004V016	46	4	16	So I beg you to be imitators of me.
B046C004V017	46	4	17	For this very purpose I have sent to you Timothy, who is my loved and faithful child in the Lord. He will remind you of my ways in Christ \'97 how I teach everywhere in every church.
B046C004V018	46	4	18	Some persons have become puffed up, thinking that I am not coming to you.
B046C004V019	46	4	19	But I shall come to you shortly, if the Lord wills, and I will find out, not the talk of these puffed-up ones, but their power.
B046C004V020	46	4	20	For the kingdom of God is not in talk, but in power.
B046C004V021	46	4	21	Which do you wish? Shall I come with a rod or in love and a spirit of gentleness?
B046C005V001	46	5	1	IT is generally reported that there is unchastity among you, and such unchastity as is not even among the Gentiles, so that a man has his father's wife!
B046C005V002	46	5	2	And you are puffed up with pride and have not rather grieved and taken steps to expel from among you the doer of this deed!
B046C005V003	46	5	3	For I, absent in body, but present in spirit, have already as if I were present judged the man who has acted thus.
B046C005V004	46	5	4	When you assembled in the name of the Lord Jesus and my spirit was also present with the power of our Lord Jesus,
B046C005V005	46	5	5	I decided to deliver over such a one to Satan for the destruction of the flesh, that the spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord.
B046C005V006	46	5	6	Your boasting is unbecoming. Do you not know that a little yeast sets the whole mass fermenting?
B046C005V007	46	5	7	Cleanse out the old yeast that you may be new dough, free from yeast, as indeed you are. For Christ, our Passover, has been sacrificed.
B046C005V008	46	5	8	So let us keep the festival, not with the old yeast nor with the yeast of evil and wickedness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.
B046C005V009	46	5	9	I wrote to you in my letter not to associate with unchaste people,
B046C005V010	46	5	10	certainly not meaning the unchaste of this world, or the covetous or extortionate or idolaters, since in that case you would have to leave the world.
B046C005V011	46	5	11	But now I write to you not to associate with any one who is called a brother, if he is unchaste or covetous or idolatrous or abusive or drunken or extortionate \'97 not even to eat with such a one.
B046C005V012	46	5	12	For what business of mine is it to judge outsiders? Is it not for you to judge those inside?
B046C005V013	46	5	13	But outsiders God will judge. Expel the wicked man from among yourselves.
B046C006V001	46	6	1	DOES any one of you, if he has a grievance against another, dare to bring the case before the unrighteous and not before the holy?
B046C006V002	46	6	2	Do you not know that the holy are going to judge the world? If the world is to be judged by you, are you unfit for the most trivial cases?
B046C006V003	46	6	3	Do you not know that we are to judge angels, to say nothing of affairs of this life?
B046C006V004	46	6	4	If then you have affairs of this life, do you ask men who in the view of the church count for nothing to sit as judges?
B046C006V005	46	6	5	I say this to your shame. Is it true that there is among you no one wise enough to judge between a man and his brother,
B046C006V006	46	6	6	but brother goes to law with brother and that before unbelievers?
B046C006V007	46	6	7	Now this is an utter failure on your part that you have lawsuits with one another. Why not rather let yourselves be wronged? Why not rather be defrauded?
B046C006V008	46	6	8	But you yourselves practice wrongs and frauds \'97 and that upon your brethren.
B046C006V009	46	6	9	Do you not know that unrighteous people will not inherit the kingdom of God? Make no mistake, neither the unchaste, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor those who practice unnatural vices,
B046C006V010	46	6	10	nor thieves, nor the avaricious, nor drunkards, nor the abusive, nor extortioners will inherit the kingdom of God.
B046C006V011	46	6	11	And such some of you were. But you have washed yourselves; but you have been made holy; but you have been pronounced righteous in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ and in the Spirit of our God.
B046C006V012	46	6	12	All things are lawful for me, but not everything is beneficial. All things are lawful, but I will not be overpowered by anything.
B046C006V013	46	6	13	Food of all kinds is for the stomach and the stomach for foods. But God will end the function of one and the other. The body is not for unchastity, but for the Lord, and the Lord is for the body.
B046C006V014	46	6	14	God raised the Lord and will also raise us through his power.
B046C006V015	46	6	15	Do you not know that your bodies are members of Christ? Shall I then take the members of Christ and make them members of a prostitute? Never!
B046C006V016	46	6	16	Do you not know that he who unites himself to a prostitute is one body with her? For God says, "The two shall become one flesh."
B046C006V017	46	6	17	He who is united to the Lord is one spirit.
B046C006V018	46	6	18	Shun unchastity. Every other sin that a man does is apart from the body, but the unchaste sins against his own body.
B046C006V019	46	6	19	Do you not know that your body is the temple of the Holy Spirit within you, which you have from God, and that you are not your own?
B046C006V020	46	6	20	For you were bought with a price. Glorify God then in your bodies.
B046C007V001	46	7	1	WITH reference to the matters you wrote of: It is an excellent thing for a man not to touch a woman.
B046C007V002	46	7	2	But because of the prevailing unchastity, let each man have his own wife and each woman her own husband.
B046C007V003	46	7	3	Let the husband pay his wife conjugal dues and the wife her husband.
B046C007V004	46	7	4	The wife has not power over her own body, but her husband has. In the same way the husband has not power over his own body, but his wife has.
B046C007V005	46	7	5	Do not deprive one another, unless by agreement for a time, that you may have freedom for prayer, and again come together. You must not let Satan tempt you through your lack of self-control.
B046C007V006	46	7	6	I say this by way of indulgence, not by way of command.
B046C007V007	46	7	7	I wish that every one were just as I am. But each has his own gift from God, one in one way and one in another.
B046C007V008	46	7	8	I say to the unmarried and the widows, it is excellent for them to remain as I do.
B046C007V009	46	7	9	But if they lack self-control, let them marry. It is better to marry than to burn.
B046C007V010	46	7	10	To the married I command \'97 yet not I, but the Lord \'97 that the wife is not to leave her husband
B046C007V011	46	7	11	
        
B046C007V012	46	7	12	To the rest I say \'97 not the Lord: If any brother has a wife who is an unbeliever and she is pleased to live with him, let him not put her away.
B046C007V013	46	7	13	And if any woman has a husband who is an unbeliever and he is pleased to live with her, let her not put him away.
B046C007V014	46	7	14	For the unbelieving husband has been made holy by the wife and the unbelieving wife has been made holy by the husband. Otherwise your children would be impure, but now they are holy.
B046C007V015	46	7	15	But if the unbelieving one actually leaves, let him leave. The brother or sister is not under bondage in such cases; but God has called you to peace.
B046C007V016	46	7	16	For how do you know, O wife, whether you will save your husband? Or how do you know, O husband, whether you will save your wife?
B046C007V017	46	7	17	But, as the Lord has allotted to each, let each go on living as when God called him. So I prescribe in all the churches.
B046C007V018	46	7	18	Was any one already circumcised when called? Let him not efface it. Was any one called when uncircumcised? Let him not become circumcised.
B046C007V019	46	7	19	Circumcision is nothing and uncircumcision is nothing, but the keeping of the commandments of God is all.
B046C007V020	46	7	20	Let each stay in that condition in which he was called.
B046C007V021	46	7	21	Were you called when a slave? Let it not trouble you. On the contrary, even if you can become free, take it in preference.
B046C007V022	46	7	22	For the slave who has been called in the Lord is the Lord's freedman. Just so the free man, when called, is the slave of Christ.
B046C007V023	46	7	23	You were bought with a price. Do not become slaves of men.
B046C007V024	46	7	24	Let each one, brethren, stay in that condition in which he was called, close to God.
B046C007V025	46	7	25	In regard to unmarried women I have no command of the Lord, but I give my opinion as one who through the mercy of the Lord is trustworthy.
B046C007V026	46	7	26	I think then that this is an excellent thing on account of the present distress \'97 that it is an excellent thing for a person to be unmarried.
B046C007V027	46	7	27	Have you been bound to a wife? Seek not release. Have you been freed from a wife? Do not seek a wife.
B046C007V028	46	7	28	But even if you marry, you have not sinned. Even if a maiden marries, she has not sinned. But such will have trouble in the flesh, and I would spare you.
B046C007V029	46	7	29	But this I say, brethren: The time is shortened. For what remains let those who have wives be as if they had none,
B046C007V030	46	7	30	and those who weep as if they wept not, and those who rejoice as if they rejoiced not, and those who buy as if they possessed nothing,
B046C007V031	46	7	31	and those who use the world as if not overusing it. For the present order of this world is passing away.
B046C007V032	46	7	32	I wish you to be free from worry. The unmarried man is anxious about the things of the Lord \'97 how be may please the Lord.
B046C007V033	46	7	33	The married man is anxious about the things of the world \'97 how he may please his wife,
B046C007V034	46	7	34	and his interest is divided. So the unmarried woman or the maiden is anxious about the things of the Lord, that she may be holy in body and spirit. But the married woman is anxious about the things of the world \'97 how she may please her husband.
B046C007V035	46	7	35	This I say for your benefit, not to throw a noose over you, but to promote decorum and constant devotion to the Lord without distraction.
B046C007V036	46	7	36	If any one thinks that he is acting unbecomingly toward his virgin, if she is ripe for marriage and there is need, let him do what he will. He does not sin. Let them marry.
B046C007V037	46	7	37	He who stands firm in his heart, having no necessity, and has power over his own will and has decided in his heart to keep his virgin, will do well.
B046C007V038	46	7	38	So he who marries his virgin does well, and he who does not marry her will do better.
B046C007V039	46	7	39	A woman is bound as long as her husband is living. But if her husband falls asleep, she is free to marry whom she will, though only in the Lord.
B046C007V040	46	7	40	But in my opinion she is happier if she stays as she is. And I think that I have the Spirit of God.
B046C008V001	46	8	1	NOW as to things that have been sacrificed to idols, we know that we all have knowledge. Knowledge puffs up, but love builds up.
B046C008V002	46	8	2	If any one think; that he knows anything, he does not yet know as he ought to know.
B046C008V003	46	8	3	If any one loves God, he is known by him.
B046C008V004	46	8	4	Regarding the eating of things that have been sacrificed to idols, then, we know that an idol is nothing in the world, and that there is no God but one.
B046C008V005	46	8	5	And though there are so-called gods in heaven and on earth, for there are gods many and lords many,
B046C008V006	46	8	6	still to us there is one God the Father, of whom are all things and we for him, and one Lord, Jesus Christ, through whom are all things and we through him.
B046C008V007	46	8	7	But all have not this knowledge. Some, having been accustomed to idols up to the present time, eat the food as a sacrifice to an idol, and their conscience being weak is stained.
B046C008V008	46	8	8	But food does not bring us near to God, for neither do we lose by not eating nor gain by eating.
B046C008V009	46	8	9	But be careful that this power of yours may not become a stumbling block to the weak.
B046C008V010	46	8	10	For if any one sees you who have knowledge reclining at table in an idol's temple, will not the conscience of that weak one be emboldened to eat things that have been sacrificed to idols?
B046C008V011	46	8	11	Thus the weak man is ruined by your knowledge \'97 the brother for whom Christ died.
B046C008V012	46	8	12	So sinning against the brethren and wounding their weak consciences you sin against Christ.
B046C008V013	46	8	13	Therefore if food makes my brother stumble I will not eat meat while the world stands, for fear of making my brother stumble.
B046C009V001	46	9	1	AM I not free? Am I not an apostle? Have I not seen Jesus our Lord? Are you not my work in the Lord?
B046C009V002	46	9	2	If to others I am not an apostle, certainly I am to you. For you are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord.
B046C009V003	46	9	3	My defence to those who criticize me is this:
B046C009V004	46	9	4	Have we not the right to eat and drink?
B046C009V005	46	9	5	Have we not the right to take about with us a sister as wife, as the rest of the apostles do and the brothers of the Lord and Cephas?
B046C009V006	46	9	6	Or am I only, and Barnabas, without the right not to do manual labor?
B046C009V007	46	9	7	Who ever serves as a soldier and supplies his own pay and rations? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat the fruit of it? Who keeps a flock and does not drink any of the milk of the flock?
B046C009V008	46	9	8	Am I saying these things from a man's point of view or does not the Law also say them?
B046C009V009	46	9	9	For in the Law of Moses it is written, "You shall not muzzle an ox when he is treading out grain." Is God thinking of the oxen?
B046C009V010	46	9	10	or does he say this wholly for our sakes? For our sakes; for it was written because the plowman ought to plow in hope and the thresher ought to thresh in hope of having a share.
B046C009V011	46	9	11	If we sowed for you things of the spirit, is it a great matter if we reap your things of the flesh?
B046C009V012	46	9	12	If others share this right over you, do not we still more? But we have not used this right. No, we endure all things in order not to cause any hindrance to the good news of Christ.
B046C009V013	46	9	13	Do you not know that those who do the work of the Temple eat the things that come from the Temple, and those who minister at the altar share with the altar?
B046C009V014	46	9	14	So the Lord has directed that those who proclaim the good news shall have their living from the good news.
B046C009V015	46	9	15	But I have used none of these rights and I am not writing this in order that it may be done in my case. For it would be better for me to die \'97 No one shall make my boast an empty one!
B046C009V016	46	9	16	For although I tell the good news I have nothing to boast of. For a necessity is laid upon me. Alas for me if I do not tell the good news!
B046C009V017	46	9	17	If I do it voluntarily I have a reward, but if reluctantly, I have been charged with a responsibility.
B046C009V018	46	9	18	What then is my reward? That in telling the good news I make the good news free, and do not take full advantage of my rights in the good news.
B046C009V019	46	9	19	For though I am free from all I have enslaved myself to all that I may gain the more.
B046C009V020	46	9	20	I became to the Jews a Jew, to gain the Jews; to those under law as under law, though not myself under law, to gain those who are under law.
B046C009V021	46	9	21	To those without law, I became as without law, though not without the law of God and under the law of Christ, to gain those who are without law.
B046C009V022	46	9	22	To the weak I became weak to gain the weak. To all men I became all things in order by all means to save some.
B046C009V023	46	9	23	I do all things for the sake of the good news that I may become a partner with it.
B046C009V024	46	9	24	Do you not know that those who run in a stadium all run, yet one gets the prize? Run so as to win.
B046C009V025	46	9	25	Every one who contends in the games practices self-restraint in all things. They do it to win a fading crown, but we for an unfading one.
B046C009V026	46	9	26	Thus I run with no uncertain goal: thus I strike, not as if pounding the air.
B046C009V027	46	9	27	On the contrary, I maul and master my body so that I may not, after preaching to others, become myself unable to stand the test.
B046C010V001	46	10	1	I DO not wish you to be ignorant, brethren, that our fathers were all under the cloud and all passed through the sea
B046C010V002	46	10	2	and all received baptism in the cloud and in the sea,
B046C010V003	46	10	3	and all ate the same spiritual food
B046C010V004	46	10	4	and all drank the same spiritual drink. For they drank from a spiritual rock that followed them, and the rock was Christ.
B046C010V005	46	10	5	But with the most of them God was not well pleased. For they were strewn in the desert.
B046C010V006	46	10	6	These things happened as warnings for us, that we may not be eager for evil things as they were eager.
B046C010V007	46	10	7	Be not idolaters, as some of them were, as it is written, "The people sat down to eat and drink and rose up to dance."
B046C010V008	46	10	8	Nor let us be unchaste, as some of them were and twenty-three thousand fell dead in one day.
B046C010V009	46	10	9	Nor let us try the patience of the Lord, as some of them tried him and were destroyed by serpents.
B046C010V010	46	10	10	Nor murmur, as some of them murmured and perished by the destroyer.
B046C010V011	46	10	11	These things happened to those people as warnings and they were written for the instruction of us to whom the closing events of the ages have come.
B046C010V012	46	10	12	So let him who thinks that he is standing beware of falling.
B046C010V013	46	10	13	No trial has taken you but what belongs to human nature. God is faithful and he will not let you be tried beyond your power, but will make, with the trial, a way of escape so that you can endure it.
B046C010V014	46	10	14	Therefore, my beloved, shun idolatry.
B046C010V015	46	10	15	I speak as to thoughtful men. Judge for yourselves what I am saying.
B046C010V016	46	10	16	The cup of blessing which we bless, is it not a fellowship in the blood of Christ? The bread which we break, is it not a fellowship in the body of Christ?
B046C010V017	46	10	17	Because there is one bread we though many are one body; for we all partake of the one bread.
B046C010V018	46	10	18	Look at Israel according to the flesh; are not those who eat of the sacrifice partakers of the altar?
B046C010V019	46	10	19	What then am I saying? That meat sacrificed to idols is anything or that an idol is anything?
B046C010V020	46	10	20	But I say that what they sacrifice they sacrifice to demons and not to God. And I would not have you become partakers with demons.
B046C010V021	46	10	21	You cannot drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You cannot partake of the table of the Lord and the table of demons.
B046C010V022	46	10	22	Or are we arousing the jealousy of the Lord? Are we stronger than he?
B046C010V023	46	10	23	All things are lawful, but not all are beneficial. All things are lawful, but not all build up character.
B046C010V024	46	10	24	Let no one seek his own interest, but the interest of others.
B046C010V025	46	10	25	Everything that is sold in market eat, raising no questions of conscience.
B046C010V026	46	10	26	For "the earth is the Lord's and the fullness thereof."
B046C010V027	46	10	27	If any one of the unbelievers invites you and you wish to go, eat whatever is set before you, raising no questions of conscience.
B046C010V028	46	10	28	But if any one says to you, "This is meat that has been sacrificed," do not eat, for the sake of him who mentioned it and for conscience' sake \'97
B046C010V029	46	10	29	conscience, I say, not yours, but the other man's. For why is my liberty judged by the conscience of another?
B046C010V030	46	10	30	If I partake with thanksgiving, why am I denounced for that for which I give thanks?
B046C010V031	46	10	31	Therefore, if you eat or if you drink or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God.
B046C010V032	46	10	32	Cause no offense either to Jews or Greeks or to the church of God,
B046C010V033	46	10	33	as I also in all things accommodate myself to all men, not seeking my own interest but that of the many, in order that they may be saved.
B046C011V001	46	11	1	IMITATE me as I imitate Christ.
B046C011V002	46	11	2	I praise you because you remember me in all things and hold firmly the traditions as I passed them on to you.
B046C011V003	46	11	3	I wish you to know that the head of every man is Christ, and the head of a woman is her husband, and the head of Christ is God.
B046C011V004	46	11	4	Every man praying or prophesying with his head draped dishonors his head.
B046C011V005	46	11	5	But every woman praying or prophesying bareheaded dishonors her head. For it is one and the same as if she had her head shaved.
B046C011V006	46	11	6	For if a woman is not covered, then let her cut off her hair. But if it is a shame to a woman to cut off her hair or to shave, let her veil herself.
B046C011V007	46	11	7	For a man has no need to cover his head since he is the image and glory of God. But the woman is the glory of man.
B046C011V008	46	11	8	For man was not from woman, but woman from man,
B046C011V009	46	11	9	for man was not formed for woman, but woman for man.
B046C011V010	46	11	10	Therefore, the woman ought to have a badge of authority on her head because of the angels.
B046C011V011	46	11	11	Yet neither is woman without man nor man without woman in the Lord.
B046C011V012	46	11	12	For as woman is from man so is man through woman, but all things from God.
B046C011V013	46	11	13	Decide for yourselves: is it becoming for a woman to pray to God unveiled?
B046C011V014	46	11	14	Does not Nature herself teach you that if a man has long hair, it is a dishonor to him,
B046C011V015	46	11	15	but that if a woman has long hair, it is a glory to her? Because the hair is given to her for a covering.
B046C011V016	46	11	16	But if any one cares to be contentious, we have no such custom, nor have the churches of God.
B046C011V017	46	11	17	In giving the following directions I do not praise you, because you do not assemble for the better, but for the worse.
B046C011V018	46	11	18	For, in the first place, I hear that when you assemble as a church there are parties among you, and to some extent I believe it.
B046C011V019	46	11	19	For there must be parties among you in order that it may become plain who are worthy of approval.
B046C011V020	46	11	20	When, therefore, you assemble it is not possible to eat the Lord's supper.
B046C011V021	46	11	21	For in eating each one tries to get his own supper first and one is hungry and another is drunken.
B046C011V022	46	11	22	Have you not homes to eat and drink in? Or do you mean to show contempt for the church of God and put to shame those who have no homes? What shall I say to you? Shall I praise you? For this I do not praise you.
B046C011V023	46	11	23	For I received from the Lord that which I passed on to you that the Lord Jesus, on the night in which he was betrayed, took bread,
B046C011V024	46	11	24	and when he had given thanks he broke it and said, 
B046C011V025	46	11	25	In like manner he took also the cup after supper, saying, 
B046C011V026	46	11	26	For as often as you eat this bread and drink the cup you proclaim the Lord's death, until he comes.
B046C011V027	46	11	27	Therefore, whoever eats the bread or drinks the cup of the Lord unworthily will be guilty of the body and blood of the Lord.
B046C011V028	46	11	28	But let a man examine himself and so let him eat of the bread and drink of the cup.
B046C011V029	46	11	29	For he who eats and drinks eats and drinks condemnation to himself, if he does not honor the Lord's body.
B046C011V030	46	11	30	For this reason many are weak and sickly among you and a number are asleep.
B046C011V031	46	11	31	If we judged ourselves we should not be judged.
B046C011V032	46	11	32	But when we are judged by the Lord, we are disciplined in order that we may not be condemned along with the world.
B046C011V033	46	11	33	So then, my brethren, when you assemble to eat, wait for one another.
B046C011V034	46	11	34	If any one is hungry, let him eat at home, that your assembling may not bring condemnation on you. The other matters I will arrange when I come.
B046C012V001	46	12	1	CONCERNING spiritual things, brethren, I do not wish you to be ignorant.
B046C012V002	46	12	2	For you know that when you were Gentiles you were led away after the dumb idols just as might happen.
B046C012V003	46	12	3	Therefore I inform you that no one speaking in the Spirit of God says, "Jesus is accursed," and no one can say, "Jesus is Lord," except in the Holy Spirit.
B046C012V004	46	12	4	There are varieties of gifts, but the same Spirit.
B046C012V005	46	12	5	And there are varieties of service, but the same Lord.
B046C012V006	46	12	6	And there are varieties of products, but the same God who produces all things in all.
B046C012V007	46	12	7	To each one is given some manifestation of the Spirit for what is profitable.
B046C012V008	46	12	8	To one are given, through the Spirit, words of wisdom, to another words of knowledge by the same Spirit,
B046C012V009	46	12	9	to another faith by the same Spirit, to another gifts of healing by the same Spirit,
B046C012V010	46	12	10	to another works of power, to another prophecy, to another the discernment of spirits, to another varieties of tongues, to another interpretation of tongues.
B046C012V011	46	12	11	One and the same Spirit produces all of these gifts, distributing to each one individually as he will.
B046C012V012	46	12	12	For as the body is one and yet has many members, and all the members of the body, though many, are one body, so also is Christ.
B046C012V013	46	12	13	For in one Spirit we were all baptized into one body, whether Jews or Greeks, whether slaves or free, and were all made to drink of one Spirit.
B046C012V014	46	12	14	For the body is not one member, but many.
B046C012V015	46	12	15	If the foot says, "Because I am not a hand I am not of the body," it is not for that reason not of the body.
B046C012V016	46	12	16	And if the ear says, "Because I am not an eye I am not of the body," it is not for that reason not of the body.
B046C012V017	46	12	17	If the whole body were an eye, where would be the hearing? If the whole were hearing, where would be the smelling?
B046C012V018	46	12	18	But now God has placed the members each one of them in the body as he pleased.
B046C012V019	46	12	19	If all were one member, where would be the body?
B046C012V020	46	12	20	But now the members are many, but the body is one.
B046C012V021	46	12	21	And the eye cannot say to the hand, "I have no need of you," or the head to the feet, "I have no need of you."
B046C012V022	46	12	22	Indeed, much more those members of the body that seem to be the weaker are necessary,
B046C012V023	46	12	23	and those that we deem the less honorable parts of the body we surround with greater honor and our uncomely parts have additional dignity,
B046C012V024	46	12	24	while our comely parts have no need. But God has organized the body, giving greater honor to the part that lacks,
B046C012V025	46	12	25	that there may be no discord in the body, but that the members may have a common concern for one another.
B046C012V026	46	12	26	And if one member suffers, all the members suffer with it; if a member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.
B046C012V027	46	12	27	You are the body of Christ and individually members.
B046C012V028	46	12	28	God placed some in the church first as apostles, secondly as prophets, thirdly as teachers, then miracle-workers, then those with gifts of healing, helpers, administrators, speakers of different kinds of tongues.
B046C012V029	46	12	29	Are all apostles? Are all prophets? Are all teachers? Are all miracle-workers?
B046C012V030	46	12	30	Do all have gifts of healing? Do all speak with tongues? Do all interpret?
B046C012V031	46	12	31	Seek earnestly for the greater gifts; and yet I will show you a way that surpasses all.
B046C013V001	46	13	1	IF I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, but have not love, I have become sounding brass or a clanging cymbal.
B046C013V002	46	13	2	And if I have the power of prophecy and understand all mysteries and all knowledge, and if I have all faith, so as to remove mountains, but have not love, I am nothing.
B046C013V003	46	13	3	And if I distribute all that I have to feed the poor, and if I give my body to be burned, but have not love, it profits me nothing.
B046C013V004	46	13	4	Love is longsuffering, love is kind, is not jealous, love does not boast, is not conceited,
B046C013V005	46	13	5	does not behave unbecomingly, does not seek her own interest, is not irritable, does not count up her wrongs,
B046C013V006	46	13	6	does not rejoice in wickedness, but rejoices with the truth,
B046C013V007	46	13	7	excuses all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.
B046C013V008	46	13	8	Love never fails; but if there are prophetic powers, they will become useless; if there are tongues, they will cease; if there is knowledge, it will become useless.
B046C013V009	46	13	9	For we know in part and we prophesy in part,
B046C013V010	46	13	10	but when the perfect comes what is in part will become useless.
B046C013V011	46	13	11	When I was a child, I talked like a child, I thought like a child, I reasoned like a child. Since I have become a man, I have no use for childish things.
B046C013V012	46	13	12	For as yet we are looking at puzzling reflections in a mirror, but then face to face. As yet I know in part, but then I shall know fully, as I have been fully known.
B046C013V013	46	13	13	But now faith, hope, love \'97 these three \'97 endure. And the greatest of these is love.
B046C014V001	46	14	1	SEEK love earnestly, be eager for spiritual gifts, but most to prophesy.
B046C014V002	46	14	2	For he who speaks with a tongue speaks not to men, but to God. For no one understands, and he speaks mysteries in the Spirit.
B046C014V003	46	14	3	But he who prophesies speaks to men what will build up, encourage, and comfort.
B046C014V004	46	14	4	He who speaks in a tongue builds himself up, but he who prophesies builds up the church.
B046C014V005	46	14	5	I wish you all to speak with tongues, but I wish more to have you prophesy. He who prophesies is greater than he who speaks with tongues, unless he interprets so that the church may receive upbuilding.
B046C014V006	46	14	6	Now, brethren, if I come to you speaking with tongues, what benefit will I be to you unless I speak to you in a revelation or in knowledge or in prophecy or in teaching.
B046C014V007	46	14	7	Inanimate things that give a sound, such as the flute or harp, \'97 unless they give a distinction in the sounds, how will it be known what is being played on flute or harp?
B046C014V008	46	14	8	If the trumpet gives a dubious sound, who will prepare himself for battle?
B046C014V009	46	14	9	And so you, if you do not give by the tongue words easy to understand, how will it be known what is said? For you will be talking into the air.
B046C014V010	46	14	10	There are, it may be, so many kinds of languages in the world, and none without meaning.
B046C014V011	46	14	11	If then I do not know the meaning of the language, I shall be a barbarian to him who is speaking, and he will be a barbarian to me.
B046C014V012	46	14	12	And so you, since you are eager for spiritual gifts, seek to abound in what will build up the church.
B046C014V013	46	14	13	Therefore let him who speaks with a tongue pray to interpret.
B046C014V014	46	14	14	For if I pray in a tongue my spirit prays, but my understanding is unfruitful.
B046C014V015	46	14	15	What then? I will pray with the spirit and with the understanding. I will sing with the spirit and with the understanding.
B046C014V016	46	14	16	If you thank God with the spirit, how shall he who fills the place of the ordinary man say Amen to your thanksgiving? For he does not know what you are saying.
B046C014V017	46	14	17	You give thanks excellently, but the other is not helped by it.
B046C014V018	46	14	18	I thank God that I speak with tongues more than any of you.
B046C014V019	46	14	19	But in church I would rather speak five words with my understanding so as to instruct others, than to speak ten thousand words in a tongue.
B046C014V020	46	14	20	Brethren, be not children in intelligence, but be babes in wickedness. In intelligence be adults.
B046C014V021	46	14	21	In the Law it is written, "By men of strange speech and by the lips of strangers I will speak to this people, and not even thus will they listen to me, says the Lord."
B046C014V022	46	14	22	So then tongues are for a sign not to believers, but to unbelievers, and prophecy is not for unbelievers, but for believers.
B046C014V023	46	14	23	If therefore the whole church assembles and all speak with tongues and ordinary men or unbelievers come in, will they not say that you are insane?
B046C014V024	46	14	24	But if all prophesy and any unbeliever or ordinary man comes in, he is convinced by all, he is judged by all,
B046C014V025	46	14	25	the secrets of his heart become manifest, and so falling on his face he worships God, declaring that God is really among you.
B046C014V026	46	14	26	What then, brethren? When you assemble each one has a psalm, has a teaching, has a revelation, has a tongue, has an interpretation. Let all things be done for the upbuilding of character.
B046C014V027	46	14	27	If any one speaks with a tongue, let it be two, or at the most three, at a time and in turn and let one interpret.
B046C014V028	46	14	28	If there is no interpreter, let the man keep silent in church and let him speak to himself and to God.
B046C014V029	46	14	29	Of the prophets let two or three speak and let the others reflect.
B046C014V030	46	14	30	If a revelation comes to another who is sitting by, let the first become silent.
B046C014V031	46	14	31	For you can all prophesy one by one so that all may learn and all be encouraged.
B046C014V032	46	14	32	The spirits of the prophets are under the control of the prophets.
B046C014V033	46	14	33	For God is not a God of confusion, but of peace. As in all the churches of the holy,
B046C014V034	46	14	34	let the women be silent in your assemblies. For it is not allowed to them to speak; but let them be in subjection as also the Law says.
B046C014V035	46	14	35	If they wish to learn anything, let them ask their own husbands at home. For it is disgraceful for a woman to speak in church.
B046C014V036	46	14	36	Did the message of God come out from you or did it come to you alone?
B046C014V037	46	14	37	If any one thinks himself a prophet or spiritual, let him recognize that what I am writing to you is the command of the Lord.
B046C014V038	46	14	38	But if any one does not know, he is himself unknown.
B046C014V039	46	14	39	So then, my brethren, seek earnestly to prophesy and do not hinder speaking with tongues.
B046C014V040	46	14	40	Let all things be done becomingly and in order.
B046C015V001	46	15	1	LET me recall to your minds, brethren, the good news which I announced to you and which you accepted, in which also you stand,
B046C015V002	46	15	2	through which also you are being saved, if you hold fast the message that I announced to you, unless your faith was thoughtless.
B046C015V003	46	15	3	For among the first things I passed on to you what I had received, that Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures,
B046C015V004	46	15	4	and that he was buried, and that he was raised on the third day, according to the Scriptures,
B046C015V005	46	15	5	and that he was seen by Cephas, then by the twelve,
B046C015V006	46	15	6	then he was seen by more than five hundred brethren at once, of whom the most are still living, but some have fallen asleep,
B046C015V007	46	15	7	then he appeared to James, then to all the apostles.
B046C015V008	46	15	8	Last of all, as if to one untimely born, he appeared also to me.
B046C015V009	46	15	9	For I am the least of the apostles and am not fit to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.
B046C015V010	46	15	10	But by the grace of God I am what I am, and his grace toward me was not without result, but I labored more abundantly than all of them, yet not I, but the grace of God that was with me.
B046C015V011	46	15	11	Whether then it was I or they, so we proclaim and so you believed.
B046C015V012	46	15	12	But if Christ is proclaimed \'97 that he has been raised from the dead \'97 how do some among you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?
B046C015V013	46	15	13	If there is no resurrection of the dead, then neither has Christ been raised.
B046C015V014	46	15	14	If Christ has not been raised, then our proclamation is an empty thing and your faith is an empty thing.
B046C015V015	46	15	15	And we are found false witnesses of God because we testified regarding God that he raised up Christ, whom he did not raise if the dead are not raised.
B046C015V016	46	15	16	For if the dead are not raised, neither has Christ been raised.
B046C015V017	46	15	17	And if Christ has not been raised, your faith is futile, you are still in your sins.
B046C015V018	46	15	18	Then also those who have fallen asleep in Christ have perished.
B046C015V019	46	15	19	If in this life only we have hope in Christ, we are of all men most pitiable.
B046C015V020	46	15	20	But now Christ has been raised from the dead, the first-fruit of those who have fallen asleep.
B046C015V021	46	15	21	For since by a man came death, by a man also came resurrection of the dead.
B046C015V022	46	15	22	For as in Adam all die, so also in Christ all will be made alive.
B046C015V023	46	15	23	But each in his own order. The first-fruit is Christ, then those who are Christ's, at his coming.
B046C015V024	46	15	24	Then will be the end when he delivers up the kingship to God his Father, when he has defeated every archangel and authority and power.
B046C015V025	46	15	25	For he must be king until he "puts all his enemies under his feet."
B046C015V026	46	15	26	The last enemy to be defeated will be death.
B046C015V027	46	15	27	For "he subjected all things under his feet." But when it says, "all things have been subjected," it is plain that it means all things except God who subjected all things to him.
B046C015V028	46	15	28	But when all things have been subjected to him, then the Son himself will be subjected to him who subjected all things to him, that God may be all in all.
B046C015V029	46	15	29	Then what shall they do who are baptized for the dead? If the dead do not rise at all, why are they then baptized for them?
B046C015V030	46	15	30	And why do we run risks every hour?
B046C015V031	46	15	31	I die every day, I swear it by the boast I make of you and which I have in Christ Jesus our Lord.
B046C015V032	46	15	32	If, humanly speaking, I fought wild beasts at Ephesus, what is my gain? If the dead do not rise, "let us eat and drink, for to-morrow we die."
B046C015V033	46	15	33	Do not be led astray; "bad associations corrupt good morals."
B046C015V034	46	15	34	Return to soberness and cease to sin, for some are ignorant of God. I say it to your shame.
B046C015V035	46	15	35	But some one will say, How are the dead raised, and with what sort of bodies do they come?
B046C015V036	46	15	36	Thoughtless man! What you yourself sow does not come to life unless it dies.
B046C015V037	46	15	37	And what you sow is not the body that will come, but a mere grain, perhaps of wheat or of something else.
B046C015V038	46	15	38	But God gives it a body as he has pleased, and to each kind of seed a body of its own.
B046C015V039	46	15	39	All flesh is not the same flesh, but there is one kind of flesh of men, another flesh of beasts, another flesh of birds, and another flesh of fishes.
B046C015V040	46	15	40	There are bodies celestial and bodies terrestrial. But the glory of the celestial is of one kind and the glory of the terrestrial is of another.
B046C015V041	46	15	41	There is one glory of the sun and another glory of the moon and another glory of the stars. For star differs from star in glory.
B046C015V042	46	15	42	So also will be the resurrection of the dead. It is sown in decay; it is raised imperishable.
B046C015V043	46	15	43	It is sown in dishonor; it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness; it is raised in power.
B046C015V044	46	15	44	It is sown an animal body; it is raised a spiritual body. If there is an animal body there is also a spiritual body.
B046C015V045	46	15	45	Just as it is written, "The first man Adam became a living animal," the last Adam became a lifegiving spirit.
B046C015V046	46	15	46	But the spiritual is not first, but the animal, then the spiritual.
B046C015V047	46	15	47	The first man was from the earth, earthly; the second man is the Lord from heaven.
B046C015V048	46	15	48	As is the earthly man such are also those who are earthly, and as is the heavenly man such are also those who are heavenly.
B046C015V049	46	15	49	And as we have borne the image of the earthly man, we shall bear the image of the heavenly man.
B046C015V050	46	15	50	But I say this, brethren, flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God, nor will decay inherit imperishability.
B046C015V051	46	15	51	I am telling you a mystery. We shall not all fall asleep, but we shall all be transformed,
B046C015V052	46	15	52	in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet-call. For the trumpet will sound and the dead will be raised imperishable, and we shall be transformed.
B046C015V053	46	15	53	For this perishable must clothe itself with imperishability, and this mortal must clothe itself with immortality.
B046C015V054	46	15	54	When this perishable has clothed itself with imperishability and this mortal has clothed itself with immortality, then will come to pass the word that is written, "Death has been swallowed up in victory.
B046C015V055	46	15	55	O Death, where is thy victory? O Death, where is thy sting?"
B046C015V056	46	15	56	The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the Law.
B046C015V057	46	15	57	But thanks be to God who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ!
B046C015V058	46	15	58	So then, my beloved brethren, be firm, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord; since you know that your labor is not fruitless in the Lord.
B046C016V001	46	16	1	REGARDING the collection for the holy, as I arranged for the churches of Galatia, you must do the same.
B046C016V002	46	16	2	On the first day of the week let each of you lay up at home something according as he may be prospering, in order that no collections may be going on when I come.
B046C016V003	46	16	3	When I come, whatever persons you may approve, I will send with letters to carry your gracious gift to Jerusalem.
B046C016V004	46	16	4	And if it seems best for me to go, they shall go with me.
B046C016V005	46	16	5	I shall come to you alter I pass through Macedonia. For I shall pass through Macedonia
B046C016V006	46	16	6	and perhaps I shall make some stay with you or pass the winter with you, so that you may send me forward wherever I may be going.
B046C016V007	46	16	7	I do not wish to see you now merely in passing, for I hope to spend some time with you, if the Lord permits.
B046C016V008	46	16	8	I shall remain in Ephesus until Pentecost,
B046C016V009	46	16	9	for a great and effective door has been opened to me, and there are many opponents.
B046C016V010	46	16	10	If Timothy comes, see to it that he becomes free from fear in his relations to you. For he is doing the Lord's work, just as I am.
B046C016V011	46	16	11	So let no one think him of no account. Send him forward in peace on his journey to me, for I am expecting him with the brethren.
B046C016V012	46	16	12	As to Apollos our brother, I urged him strongly to go to you with the brethren. But it was not at all his will to go now, but he will come when it is convenient.
B046C016V013	46	16	13	Watch, stand firmly in the faith, be manly, be strong,
B046C016V014	46	16	14	let all that you do be done in love.
B046C016V015	46	16	15	I beg you, brethren \'97 you know the household of Stephanas, that it is the first-fruit of Achaia and they have devoted themselves to serving the holy \'97
B046C016V016	46	16	16	I beg you to show deference to such and to every fellow worker and laborer.
B046C016V017	46	16	17	I rejoice in the arrival of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus, because they made up for my lack of you.
B046C016V018	46	16	18	For they refreshed my spirit and yours. Appreciate such men.
B046C016V019	46	16	19	The churches of Asia send you their greetings. Aquila and Prisca with the church in their house greet you heartily in the Lord.
B046C016V020	46	16	20	All the brethren send greetings to you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B046C016V021	46	16	21	Here is the greeting of me, Paul, by my own hand.
B046C016V022	46	16	22	If any one does not love the Lord, let him be accursed! Maran atha!
B046C016V023	46	16	23	The grace of the Lord Jesus be with you.
B046C016V024	46	16	24	My love to all of you in Christ Jesus.
B047C001V001	47	1	1	PAUL, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, and Timothy the brother, to the church of God that is in Corinth with all the holy that are in all Achaia:
B047C001V002	47	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ!
B047C001V003	47	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of loving kindness and the God of all encouragement,
B047C001V004	47	1	4	who encourages us in every distress so that we may be able to encourage those who are in every distress by the encouragement by which we ourselves have been encouraged by God.
B047C001V005	47	1	5	Because as the sufferings of Christ are abundant in our case, so through Christ our encouragement is abundant.
B047C001V006	47	1	6	But if we are in distress, it is for your encouragement and salvation. If we are encouraged, it is for your encouragement which is effective in the endurance of the same sufferings that we suffer.
B047C001V007	47	1	7	Our hope is strong regarding you, since we know that as you are partakers of the sufferings so you are of the encouragement.
B047C001V008	47	1	8	For we do not wish you to be ignorant, brethren, regarding the distress that came on us in Asia \'97 that we were exceedingly weighed down, beyond our strength, so that we despaired even of life.
B047C001V009	47	1	9	Indeed we have the sentence of death within ourselves, that our trust may not rest on ourselves, but on God who raises the dead.
B047C001V010	47	1	10	He delivered us from such a death and will deliver, and we have hope in him that he will go on delivering,
B047C001V011	47	1	11	while you help by your prayers for us, so that from many persons thanksgiving may arise for the gift granted to us through the prayers of many for us.
B047C001V012	47	1	12	For this is what we boast of, the witness of our conscience that in holiness, and sincerity before God, not in fleshly wisdom, but in the grace of God, we have lived in the world and especially toward you.
B047C001V013	47	1	13	For we are not writing to you anything but what you read and acknowledge and I hope you will acknowledge to the end,
B047C001V014	47	1	14	as you have partly acknowledged it about us, that we are your ground of boasting and you are ours on the day of our Lord Jesus.
B047C001V015	47	1	15	With this confidence I intended to come to you first, so that you might have a second favor,
B047C001V016	47	1	16	by my visiting you on the way to Macedonia and again coming back from Macedonia to you and being sped by you on my way toward Juda.
B047C001V017	47	1	17	When I was intending this, did I show fickleness? Or do I plan what I plan according to the flesh, so that I may say yes, yes, and no, no?
B047C001V018	47	1	18	As God is faithful, my word to you is not yes and no.
B047C001V019	47	1	19	For the Son of God, Christ Jesus, who was proclaimed among you by us \'97 myself and Silvanus and Timothy \'97 was not yes and no, but in him was yes.
B047C001V020	47	1	20	For all the promises of God, however many, have their yes in him. Therefore also through him is the Amen to the glory of God through us.
B047C001V021	47	1	21	It is God who makes us and you steadfast to Christ, and has anointed us
B047C001V022	47	1	22	and sealed us and has given the pledge of the Spirit in our hearts.
B047C001V023	47	1	23	I call God as a witness against my soul that in order to spare you I have not yet come to Corinth.
B047C001V024	47	1	24	Not that we are lords over your faith, but fellow workers sharing your joy, for you are standing firm in the faith.
B047C002V001	47	2	1	BUT I decided this in my own mind, not to come again to you in sorrow.
B047C002V002	47	2	2	For if I grieve you, who is there to cheer me except those who are grieved by me?
B047C002V003	47	2	3	I am writing this very thing so that I may not come and have grief from those who ought to make me glad, for I am confident in regard to all of you that my joy is yours.
B047C002V004	47	2	4	For out of great distress and pain of heart I am writing with many tears, not that you may be grieved, but that you may know the love that I have beyond measure for you.
B047C002V005	47	2	5	But if any one has caused grief, he has grieved not me, but to some extent \'97 not to be too severe \'97 all of you.
B047C002V006	47	2	6	Sufficient for such a one is this punishment by the majority,
B047C002V007	47	2	7	so that on the contrary you should rather forgive him and encourage him, that such a one may not be swallowed up in excessive grief.
B047C002V008	47	2	8	Therefore I beg you to assure him of your love.
B047C002V009	47	2	9	Because for this purpose I am writing, that I may know your tested character, whether you are obedient in everything.
B047C002V010	47	2	10	To whomever you forgive anything I also forgive it, and what I have forgiven, if I have forgiven anything, it was for your sake in the sight of Christ,
B047C002V011	47	2	11	that Satan may not take advantage of us, for we are not ignorant of his purposes.
B047C002V012	47	2	12	When I came to Troas for the good news of Christ and a door had been opened for me in the Lord,
B047C002V013	47	2	13	I had no rest in my spirit because I did not find Titus my brother, but bidding them farewell I came away to Macedonia.
B047C002V014	47	2	14	Thanks be to God who always leads us in his triumph in Christ and spreads through us the sweet odor of the knowledge of him in every place.
B047C002V015	47	2	15	For we are for God a sweet odor of Christ \'97 in the saved and in the perishing.
B047C002V016	47	2	16	To the latter an odor from death to death, to the former an odor from life to life. And who is competent for this?
B047C002V017	47	2	17	For we are not, like the most, adulterating the message of God for gain, but in sincerity, as from God, in the presence of God, we speak in Christ.
B047C003V001	47	3	1	ARE we beginning again to recommend ourselves? Do we need, as some do, letters of recommendation to you or from you?
B047C003V002	47	3	2	You are our letter, written in our hearts, known and read by all men,
B047C003V003	47	3	3	evidently a letter of Christ delivered by us, written not with ink, but with the Spirit of the living God, not on stone tablets, but on tablets that are hearts of flesh.
B047C003V004	47	3	4	We have such confidence through Christ toward God.
B047C003V005	47	3	5	Not that of ourselves we are fit to reason out anything as from ourselves, but our fitness is from God,
B047C003V006	47	3	6	who has fitted us to be servants of a new covenant, not of the letter, but of the spirit. For the letter kills, but the spirit gives life.
B047C003V007	47	3	7	If the service that brought death, engraved in letters on stones, came in glory, so that the children of Israel could not look steadily at the face of Moses because of the glory of his face \'97 that fading glory \'97
B047C003V008	47	3	8	how much more glorious will not the service of the Spirit be?
B047C003V009	47	3	9	For if the service that brought condemnation was glory, much more will the service that brings righteousness surpass in glory.
B047C003V010	47	3	10	For what was made so glorious is in a way no longer glorious compared with the glory that surpasses it.
B047C003V011	47	3	11	For if what was to be ended came in glory, much more glorious must be that which is enduring.
B047C003V012	47	3	12	With such a hope then we speak with great frankness,
B047C003V013	47	3	13	and are not like Moses, who used to put a veil over his face so that the children of Israel might not see when the vanishing glory ended;
B047C003V014	47	3	14	but their thinking was dulled. For to this day the same veil remains unlifted when the old covenant is read; because it is done away only in Christ.
B047C003V015	47	3	15	To this day when Moses is read the veil lies on their hearts;
B047C003V016	47	3	16	"but when they turn to the Lord the veil is taken away."
B047C003V017	47	3	17	The Lord is the Spirit, and where the Spirit of the Lord is there is liberty.
B047C003V018	47	3	18	And we all, with unveiled face, reflecting the glory of the Lord, are changed into the same likeness from glory to glory as by the Spirit of the Lord.
B047C004V001	47	4	1	THEREFORE, having this service through God's mercy, we are not downhearted,
B047C004V002	47	4	2	but we have renounced shameful secret things, not living in craftiness nor adulterating God's message, but by the openness of truth commending ourselves to every man's conscience in the sight of God.
B047C004V003	47	4	3	If our good news is veiled, it is veiled to those who are going to ruin,
B047C004V004	47	4	4	in whom the god of this world has blinded the thinking of the unbelieving so that the light of the glorious good news of Christ, who is the image of God, may not shine in.
B047C004V005	47	4	5	For we are not proclaiming ourselves but Christ Jesus as Lord, and ourselves as your servants for Jesus' sake.
B047C004V006	47	4	6	Because it is the God who said, "Light shall shine out of darkness," who has shone in our hearts bringing the light of the glorious knowledge of God in the face of Christ.
B047C004V007	47	4	7	But we have this treasure in earthen jars, that the surpassing power may be God's and not ours \'97
B047C004V008	47	4	8	in every way distressed, but not reduced to straits, perplexed, but not in despair,
B047C004V009	47	4	9	persecuted, but not forsaken, cast down, but not destroyed,
B047C004V010	47	4	10	always bearing about in our bodies the death of Jesus that the life also of Jesus may be manifest in our bodies.
B047C004V011	47	4	11	For we, though living, are always delivered up to death for Jesus' sake, that also the life of Jesus may be manifested in our mortal flesh.
B047C004V012	47	4	12	So death works in us, but life in you.
B047C004V013	47	4	13	Having the same spirit of faith, as it is written, "I believed, therefore I spoke," we too believe and therefore speak,
B047C004V014	47	4	14	knowing that he who raised up Jesus will also raise us up with Jesus and place us in his presence with you.
B047C004V015	47	4	15	For all things are for your sake, that grace abounding through many may overflow in thanksgiving to the glory of God.
B047C004V016	47	4	16	Therefore we are not downhearted, but even if our outward man is wasting away, yet our inward man is renewed day by day.
B047C004V017	47	4	17	For our momentary and light distress is working out for us a far surpassing and eternal weight of glory
B047C004V018	47	4	18	while we contemplate not the things that are seen, but the things unseen. For the things that are seen are transient, but the things unseen are eternal.
B047C005V001	47	5	1	FOR we know that if this tent, our earthly home, is thrown down, we have a building of God, a home not made by hands, eternal in the heavens.
B047C005V002	47	5	2	For in this we sigh in earnest desire to put on our dwelling that comes from heaven,
B047C005V003	47	5	3	since if we put that on we shall not be found naked.
B047C005V004	47	5	4	For while we are in this tent we sigh being burdened, not that we wish to be unclothed, but to put on the other, that what is mortal may be swallowed up in life.
B047C005V005	47	5	5	He who has prepared us for this very thing is God, and he has given to us the pledge of the Spirit.
B047C005V006	47	5	6	So being always of good courage and knowing that while living at home in the body we are living in a foreign land away from the Lord \'97
B047C005V007	47	5	7	for we walk by faith, not by sight \'97
B047C005V008	47	5	8	I say we are of good courage and wish rather to live in the land foreign to the body and be at home with the Lord.
B047C005V009	47	5	9	Therefore also we are ambitious to be pleasing to him, whether at home with him or in this foreign land.
B047C005V010	47	5	10	For we must all appear as we truly are before the judgment seat of Christ, that each may receive the award for what he has done with his body, according to his actions, whether good or bad.
B047C005V011	47	5	11	Knowing, therefore, the fear of the Lord, we are persuading men. What we are is plain to God, and I hope that it is also plain to your consciences.
B047C005V012	47	5	12	We are not recommending ourselves again to you, but giving occasion to you for boasting on our behalf, that you may have it to use against those who boast of appearances and not of heart.
B047C005V013	47	5	13	For if we were out of our minds it was for God, and if we are sane it is for you.
B047C005V014	47	5	14	For the love of Christ impels us, convinced of this, that if one died for all, then all died,
B047C005V015	47	5	15	and he died for all that the living may no longer live for themselves, but for him who died for them and was raised again.
B047C005V016	47	5	16	So we, from now on, know no man according to the flesh. Even if we have known Christ according to the flesh, yet now we know him so no more.
B047C005V017	47	5	17	So if any one is in Christ he is a new creature. The old things have passed away, they have become new.
B047C005V018	47	5	18	And all things are from God, who has reconciled us to himself through Christ and given to us the service of reconciliation \'97
B047C005V019	47	5	19	to proclaim that God was in Christ reconciling the world to himself, not counting against men their sins, and that he has committed to us the message of reconciliation.
B047C005V020	47	5	20	So we are ambassadors for Christ, as if God were appealing to you through us. We pray you on Christ's behalf to be reconciled to God.
B047C005V021	47	5	21	Him who knew no sin God made sin for our sake that we might become the righteousness of God in him.
B047C006V001	47	6	1	AS God's fellow workers we also beg you not to receive his grace fruitlessly.
B047C006V002	47	6	2	For he says, "At a favorable time I heard you and on a day of salvation I helped you." Now is a particularly favorable time, now is a day of salvation.
B047C006V003	47	6	3	We give no occasion for stumbling to any one that our service may not be blamed,
B047C006V004	47	6	4	but in everything we commend ourselves as God's servants in great patience, in distresses, in necessities, in hardships,
B047C006V005	47	6	5	in floggings, in prisons, in riots, in toils, in sleepless nights, in fastings,
B047C006V006	47	6	6	with purity, with knowledge, with long-suffering, with kindness, with the Holy Spirit, with sincere love,
B047C006V007	47	6	7	with the message of truth, with the power of God; by the weapons of righteousness in the right hand and the left,
B047C006V008	47	6	8	by honor and shame, by slander and praise; as deceivers yet true,
B047C006V009	47	6	9	as unknown yet well known, as dying and yet we are living, as chastised yet not put to death,
B047C006V010	47	6	10	as sorrowful yet always rejoicing, as poor yet making many rich, as having nothing yet owning all things.
B047C006V011	47	6	11	Our mouth is open to you, Corinthians, our heart expands itself.
B047C006V012	47	6	12	You find no narrowness in us, the narrowness is in your own sympathies.
B047C006V013	47	6	13	As a fair return, I am speaking as to my children, let your hearts expand.
B047C006V014	47	6	14	Do not be yoked up, like unmatched animals, with unbelievers. For what partnership have righteousness and lawlessness, or what fellowship has light with darkness,
B047C006V015	47	6	15	or what harmony has Christ with Belial, or what share has a believer with an unbeliever?
B047C006V016	47	6	16	What agreement has the Temple of God with idols? For we are the Temple of the living God, as God said, "I will dwell in them and walk among them, and I will be their God and they shall be my people.
B047C006V017	47	6	17	Therefore come out from the midst of them and be separate, says the Lord, and do not touch an unclean thing, and I will receive you
B047C006V018	47	6	18	and will be a Father to you and you shall be sons and daughters to me, says the Lord, the Ruler of all."
B047C007V001	47	7	1	HAVING then these promises, beloved, let us purify ourselves from every defilement of flesh or spirit, in reverence for God making our holiness complete.
B047C007V002	47	7	2	Make room for us in your hearts. We have wronged no one; we have injured no one; we have taken advantage of no one.
B047C007V003	47	7	3	I am not saying this to condemn you, for I have already said that you have such a place in our hearts that we are ready to die with you or to live with you.
B047C007V004	47	7	4	Great is my frankness in speaking to you; great is my boasting of you; I am filled with encouragement, running over with joy at every distress of ours.
B047C007V005	47	7	5	For since we came to Macedonia our flesh has had no rest, but we have been distressed in every way, conflicts without, fears within.
B047C007V006	47	7	6	But God, who encourages the depressed, encouraged us by the coming of Titus,
B047C007V007	47	7	7	and not by his coming only, but also by the encouragement by which he was encouraged about you. He told us of your longing for me, your lamentation, your zeal in my behalf, so that I rejoice the more.
B047C007V008	47	7	8	For if I grieved you in my letter I do not regret it, though I did regret it, seeing that that letter grieved you even for a time,
B047C007V009	47	7	9	but I am glad now, not that you were grieved, but that your grief led to a change of heart. You were grieved as God approves so that you should in nothing suffer loss from us.
B047C007V010	47	7	10	For such grief as God approves works a change of heart leading to salvation and is never to be regretted. But the grief of the world results in death.
B047C007V011	47	7	11	Notice this very grieving as God approves, how great earnestness resulted from it in your case, what effort to defend yourselves, what indignation, what fear, what longing, what zeal, what just punishment! In everything you showed yourselves blameless in the matter.
B047C007V012	47	7	12	So although I wrote to you, I did it not for the sake of him who did the wrong, nor for the sake of him who suffered wrong, but that your earnestness for us might be made plain to you before God.
B047C007V013	47	7	13	On this account we have been encouraged. In addition to this encouragement of ours, we rejoiced very much more over the joy of Titus because his spirit has been refreshed by you all,
B047C007V014	47	7	14	for if I have made any boast regarding you I have not been put to shame, but as we spoke everything in truth to you so our boasting over Titus turned out the truth.
B047C007V015	47	7	15	And his affections go out more strongly to you when he remembers the obedience of you all, how with reverence and trembling you received him.
B047C007V016	47	7	16	I am glad to be in every respect of good courage regarding you.
B047C008V001	47	8	1	I MUST tell you, brethren, of the grace of God that has been given to the churches of Macedonia,
B047C008V002	47	8	2	that in a great trial of distress their abundant joy and their deep poverty have abounded in the wealth of their liberality.
B047C008V003	47	8	3	For according to their ability, I bear witness, and beyond their ability, of their own accord,
B047C008V004	47	8	4	with great urgency they begged of us the favor of fellowship in the service for the holy,
B047C008V005	47	8	5	and this not as we had hoped, but first they gave themselves to the Lord and to us through the will of God.
B047C008V006	47	8	6	Therefore we encouraged Titus that as he had begun so he should complete this grace among you.
B047C008V007	47	8	7	But as you excel in every way, in faith and speech and knowledge and in all earnestness and in the love you learned from us, be sure to excel in this grace also.
B047C008V008	47	8	8	I speak not by way of command, but testing the genuineness of your love by the earnestness of others.
B047C008V009	47	8	9	For you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that though he was rich yet for your sake he became poor, that you by his poverty might become rich.
B047C008V010	47	8	10	In this I give my opinion, for this is advantageous for you, since a year ago you were first to begin not only the doing but the wanting to do anything.
B047C008V011	47	8	11	But now complete the doing, that as there was a readiness in willing so there may be a completion according to your means.
B047C008V012	47	8	12	For if there is first the readiness, a gift is acceptable according to what a man has, not according to what he has not.
B047C008V013	47	8	13	I do not mean that others shall have relief and you shall have trouble,
B047C008V014	47	8	14	but by equality at the present time your abundance may supply their need so that their abundance may come at your need \'97 that there may be equality,
B047C008V015	47	8	15	as it is written, "He who gathered much had nothing over and he who gathered little had no lack."
B047C008V016	47	8	16	Thanks be to God who puts into the heart of Titus the same interest in you.
B047C008V017	47	8	17	For he welcomed our appeal, but being unusually interested comes to you of his own choice.
B047C008V018	47	8	18	With him we are sending the brother whose praise for service to the good news has spread through all the churches,
B047C008V019	47	8	19	and not only that, but he was appointed by the churches as our fellow traveler in this gracious errand carried out by us to the glory of the Lord himself and by our own eager desire.
B047C008V020	47	8	20	We are taking care that no one shall blame us for our administration of this bountiful fund,
B047C008V021	47	8	21	for we are providing arrangements honorable, not only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of men.
B047C008V022	47	8	22	We are sending along with them also our brother whose earnestness we have tested many times in many ways, and who is now especially earnest because of his great confidence in you.
B047C008V023	47	8	23	If any one asks about Titus, he is my intimate friend and fellow worker for you. If it is our brethren, they are the messengers of the churches, the glory of Christ.
B047C008V024	47	8	24	Show them in the sight of the churches your love and the ground of our boasting to them about you.
B047C009V001	47	9	1	REGARDING the service to the holy, it is superfluous for me to write to you.
B047C009V002	47	9	2	For I know your readiness and I am boasting about you to the Macedonians, that Achaia was ready a year ago, and your zeal has stimulated the most of them.
B047C009V003	47	9	3	I am sending the brethren that our boasting about you may not be proved in this matter an empty boast, so that you may be ready as I have said,
B047C009V004	47	9	4	and if any Macedonians come with me and find you unprepared, we, not to say you, may not be made ashamed of this confidence.
B047C009V005	47	9	5	So I think it necessary to urge the brethren to go on in advance to you and prepare before-hand your promised gift, that it may be ready as a gift and not as if extorted.
B047C009V006	47	9	6	Remember this, he who sows sparingly will reap sparingly and he who sows bountifully will reap bountifully.
B047C009V007	47	9	7	Let each give as he has purposed in his heart, not grudgingly nor of necessity, for God loves a cheerful giver.
B047C009V008	47	9	8	God is able to make every blessing abound for you so that having in everything always all that you need, you may abound in every good work,
B047C009V009	47	9	9	as it is written, "He scattered, he gave to the poor, his righteousness endures forever."
B047C009V010	47	9	10	He who supplies seed to the sower and bread for food will supply and make abundant your seed and will increase the fruits of your righteousness.
B047C009V011	47	9	11	You will be enriched in everything so that you will have all liberality which through our agency causes thanksgiving to God.
B047C009V012	47	9	12	For the performance of this sacred service not only supplies the needs of the holy, but also overflows to God in many thanksgivings.
B047C009V013	47	9	13	By the proof afforded by this service men are led to glorify God for your fidelity to your profession of faith in the good news of Christ, and for the liberality of your contributions toward them and toward all.
B047C009V014	47	9	14	In their prayers in your behalf they pour out their longing love for you because of the surpassing grace of God that is upon you.
B047C009V015	47	9	15	Thanks be to God for his unspeakable gift!
B047C010V001	47	10	1	I MYSELF, Paul, beg you by the gentleness and sweet reasonableness of Christ \'97 I who "to your face am humble when among you, but when absent am bold toward you" \'97
B047C010V002	47	10	2	I pray that I may not when present have to be bold with the confidence with which I expect to show my courage against some who think of us as living according to the flesh.
B047C010V003	47	10	3	For although living in the flesh we do not carry on our warfare according to the flesh,
B047C010V004	47	10	4	for the weapons of our warfare are not weapons of the flesh, but powerful under God for the destruction of fortresses.
B047C010V005	47	10	5	We overthrow reasonings and every high thing that exalts itself against the knowledge of God, and take captive every thought into obedience to Christ
B047C010V006	47	10	6	and are ready to take vengeance upon every disobedience when your obedience is complete.
B047C010V007	47	10	7	Look at what is right before your eyes. If any one is confident that he belongs to Christ, let him again consider this regarding himself, that just as he belongs to Christ so also do we.
B047C010V008	47	10	8	For if I boast somewhat excessively of our authority, which the Lord gave for building you up and not for pulling you down, I shall not be ashamed.
B047C010V009	47	10	9	Let me not seem as if meaning to frighten you by letters.
B047C010V010	47	10	10	Because, "His letters," they say, "are mighty and strong, but his bodily presence is weak and his speaking amounts to nothing."
B047C010V011	47	10	11	Let such a person consider this, that what we are in words by letters when absent such we will be in deeds when present.
B047C010V012	47	10	12	We do not venture to class ourselves or compare ourselves with some of those who are commending themselves. But they, measuring themselves among themselves and comparing themselves with themselves, do not understand.
B047C010V013	47	10	13	We will not boast beyond measure, but according to the measure of the measuring rod which God assigned to us, and that reaches as far as you.
B047C010V014	47	10	14	For we are not stretching ourselves, as if we did not reach to you, for we were the first to reach you with the good news of Christ.
B047C010V015	47	10	15	We are not boasting beyond measure in the labors of others, but we have hope that as your faith grows we may have larger influence among you according to our measure and beyond,
B047C010V016	47	10	16	so that we may tell the good news to the regions lying beyond you and not boast of things already done in some other man's territory.
B047C010V017	47	10	17	"Let him who boasts boast in the Lord."
B047C010V018	47	10	18	For it is not he who commends himself that is approved, but whom the Lord commends.
B047C011V001	47	11	1	O THAT you would bear with me in a little foolishness. Yes, bear with me.
B047C011V002	47	11	2	For I am jealous over you with the jealousy of God, for I betrothed you to one husband to present you as a pure virgin to Christ.
B047C011V003	47	11	3	But I fear that, as the serpent deceived Eve by his cunning, your thoughts may be led away from sincerity and purity toward Christ.
B047C011V004	47	11	4	For if some newcomer proclaims another Jesus whom we did not proclaim, or if you receive a different kind of spirit which you did not receive, or a different good news which you did not welcome, you bear with him finely.
B047C011V005	47	11	5	I consider that I am in nothing inferior to the most eminent apostles.
B047C011V006	47	11	6	If I am an ordinary man in speaking, still I am not in knowledge, but in everything we made that altogether clear to you.
B047C011V007	47	11	7	Did I commit a sin when I humbled myself that you might be exalted, because I proclaimed to you the good news of God without pay?
B047C011V008	47	11	8	I robbed other churches by taking wages for serving you,
B047C011V009	47	11	9	and when I was with you and in need I was not a burden to any one, for the brethren who came from Macedonia supplied my need. In every way I kept myself from being a burden to you, and shall keep myself so.
B047C011V010	47	11	10	As the truth of Christ is in me, this boast of mine shall not be stopped in the region of Achaia.
B047C011V011	47	11	11	Why? Because I do not love you? God knows.
B047C011V012	47	11	12	But what I am doing I shall do so as to cut away all ground of attack from those who wish ground, and that in what they boast of they may be found just like us.
B047C011V013	47	11	13	For such are false apostles, deceitful workers, disguising themselves as apostles of Christ.
B047C011V014	47	11	14	And no wonder, for Satan himself disguises himself as an angel of light.
B047C011V015	47	11	15	So it is no great thing if his servants too disguise themselves as servants of righteousness. Their end will be according to their deeds.
B047C011V016	47	11	16	I say again, let no one think me foolish. But, even if so, receive me as foolish, that I too may boast a little.
B047C011V017	47	11	17	What I am saying I am not saying by the Lord's command, but as it were in foolishness, in this confident boasting.
B047C011V018	47	11	18	Since many are boasting according to the flesh, I too will boast,
B047C011V019	47	11	19	for you who are wise bear pleasantly with the foolish.
B047C011V020	47	11	20	You bear it if any one enslaves you, if any one devours you, if any one takes possession of you, if any one exalts himself, if any one strikes you in the face.
B047C011V021	47	11	21	I say it with shame as if we had been weak. But in whatever any one is bold 
B047C011V022	47	11	22	Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they descended from Abraham? So am I.
B047C011V023	47	11	23	Are they servants of Christ? 
B047C011V024	47	11	24	From Jews five times I received forty stripes less one,
B047C011V025	47	11	25	three times I was beaten with rods, once I was stoned, three times I was ship-wrecked, a night and day I have been in the deep;
B047C011V026	47	11	26	in journeys often, in perils of rivers, in perils of robbers, in perils from my own race, in perils from Gentiles, in perils in the city, in perils in the open country, in perils on the sea, in perils among false brethren;
B047C011V027	47	11	27	in toil and labor, in many a sleepless night, in hunger and thirst, in fastings often, in cold and nakedness.
B047C011V028	47	11	28	Aside, from other things there is that which weighs on me daily, anxiety for all the churches.
B047C011V029	47	11	29	Who is weak and I am not weak? Who stumbles and I am not burning?
B047C011V030	47	11	30	If there must be boasting, I will boast of the things that show my weakness.
B047C011V031	47	11	31	The God and Father of the Lord Jesus knows, he who is blessed forever, that I am not lying.
B047C011V032	47	11	32	In Damascus the Governor under King Aretas was guarding the city of the Damascenes to arrest me,
B047C011V033	47	11	33	and through a window I was lowered in a basket and escaped from his hands.
B047C012V001	47	12	1	I MUST boast, though it is unprofitable. I will come to visions and revelations of the Lord.
B047C012V002	47	12	2	I know a man in Christ fourteen years ago \'97 whether in the body I know not, or out of the body I know not; God knows \'97 such a man caught up to the third heaven.
B047C012V003	47	12	3	I know such a man \'97 whether in the body or out of the body I know not; God knows \'97
B047C012V004	47	12	4	that he was caught up into Paradise and heard unspeakable words which it is not lawful for man to speak.
B047C012V005	47	12	5	Of such a one I will boast, but of myself I will not boast except of my weaknesses.
B047C012V006	47	12	6	Even if I choose to boast I shall not be foolish, for I shall speak the truth. But I guard myself that no one may think of me beyond what he sees me to be, or hears from me,
B047C012V007	47	12	7	and because of the surpassing nature of the revelations. For this reason, that I should not be puffed up, there was given to me a thorn in the flesh, an angel of Satan, to torment me, so that I should not be puffed up.
B047C012V008	47	12	8	Regarding this I three times begged the Lord that it might leave me.
B047C012V009	47	12	9	But he has said to me, 
B047C012V010	47	12	10	Therefore I rejoice in weaknesses, in rough treatment, in necessities, in persecutions, in distresses for Christ's sake; for when I am weak, then I am strong.
B047C012V011	47	12	11	I have become foolish; you made me. For I ought to have been recommended by you. For in nothing have I been inferior to the most eminent apostles, even though I am nothing.
B047C012V012	47	12	12	The signs of an apostle were performed among you in all patience by miracles and wonders and deeds of power.
B047C012V013	47	12	13	What is there in which you were made inferior to the rest of the churches except that I was not a burden to you? Forgive me this wrong.
B047C012V014	47	12	14	Now this third time I am ready to come to you, and I shall not be a burden to you. For I am not seeking yours, but you. For the children ought not to lay up money for the parents, but the parents for the children.
B047C012V015	47	12	15	And I will most gladly spend and be spent for your souls. If I love you too much, am I loved the less?
B047C012V016	47	12	16	Be that as it may, I was not a burden to you. But being crafty I caught you with cunning?
B047C012V017	47	12	17	Did I take advantage of you through any one of those I sent to you?
B047C012V018	47	12	18	I begged Titus to go, and I sent along with him the brother. Did Titus take advantage of you? Did we not act in the same spirit and walk in the same steps?
B047C012V019	47	12	19	Are you thinking all this while that we are defending ourselves to you? We are speaking before God in Christ. All this, beloved, is to build you up.
B047C012V020	47	12	20	For I am afraid that when I come I shall not find you such as I wish, and I myself may not be found by you such as you wish. I am afraid that there may be strife, jealousy, anger, rivalry, slanders, whisperings, conceit, disorders.
B047C012V021	47	12	21	I am afraid that when I come again my God may humble me in your presence, and that I shall grieve over many of those who have been long sinning and have not repented of the impurity and unchastity and sensuality which they have practiced.
B047C013V001	47	13	1	THIS third time I am coming to you. "By the evidence of two witnesses, or three, every matter shall be proved."
B047C013V002	47	13	2	Those who have been long sinning and all the rest I have forewarned and now forewarn, when I was present with you the second time and now when absent, that if I come again I shall not spare;
B047C013V003	47	13	3	since you are eager to have a test of Christ speaking in me. He is not weak toward you, but powerful among you.
B047C013V004	47	13	4	He was crucified in weakness, but he is living by the power of God. And we are weak in him, but we shall live with him by the power of God for you.
B047C013V005	47	13	5	Test yourselves whether you are in the faith, put yourselves to the proof. Are you not conscious that Jesus Christ is in you? He is, unless you cannot stand the test.
B047C013V006	47	13	6	I hope that you know that we are not unable to stand the test.
B047C013V007	47	13	7	I pray to God that you may do nothing evil, not in order that we may seem to stand the test, but in order that you may do the right, though we should seem unable to stand the test.
B047C013V008	47	13	8	For we cannot do anything against the truth; our power is for the truth.
B047C013V009	47	13	9	We rejoice when we are weak and you are strong. This we are praying for, your all-round character.
B047C013V010	47	13	10	For this reason I am writing this while absent, so that when present I may not act with severity in the use of the authority which the Lord gave me for building you up, not for pulling you down.
B047C013V011	47	13	11	Now, brethren, farewell. Be fully equipped; take courage; be of one mind; live in peace; then the God of love and peace will be with you.
B047C013V012	47	13	12	Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B047C013V013	47	13	13	All the holy send greetings.
B047C013V014	47	13	14	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, and the love of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit be with you all.
B048C001V001	48	1	1	PAUL an apostle \'97 not from men or through men, but through Jesus Christ and God the Father, who raised him from the dead \'97
B048C001V002	48	1	2	and all the brethren with me, to the churches of Galatia:
B048C001V003	48	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ,
B048C001V004	48	1	4	who gave himself for our sins to deliver us from the present wicked world according to the will of our God and Father!
B048C001V005	48	1	5	To him be glory through the ages of the ages! Amen.
B048C001V006	48	1	6	I am astonished that you are so quickly changing over from him who called you by the grace of Christ to a different kind of good news,
B048C001V007	48	1	7	though it is not another good news. But there are some who are perplexing you and wishing to pervert the good news of Christ.
B048C001V008	48	1	8	But even if we, or an angel from heaven, should bring you any good news different from what we did bring you, let him be accursed!
B048C001V009	48	1	9	As I said before, I say now again, if any one brings you good news different from what you have received, let him be accursed!
B048C001V010	48	1	10	Am I now trying to please men or God? If I were still trying to please men I should not be Christ's servant.
B048C001V011	48	1	11	For I assure you, brethren, that the good news which I brought is not of man's devising.
B048C001V012	48	1	12	For neither did I receive it from man nor was I taught it through man, but through a revelation of Jesus Christ.
B048C001V013	48	1	13	You have heard of my former life in Judaism, that I furiously persecuted the church of God and made havoc of it,
B048C001V014	48	1	14	and I went further in Judaism than many of my own age and race, being intensely zealous for the traditions of my forefathers.
B048C001V015	48	1	15	But when he who had appointed me when I was in my mother's womb, and had called me by his grace,
B048C001V016	48	1	16	was pleased to reveal his Son in me that I might tell the good news of him among the Gentiles, immediately I did not consult with flesh and blood,
B048C001V017	48	1	17	nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me, but I went away into Arabia, and came back to Damascus.
B048C001V018	48	1	18	Then, after three years, I went up to Jerusalem to visit Peter and stayed with him fifteen days.
B048C001V019	48	1	19	But I saw no other one of the apostles, though I did see James the Lord's brother.
B048C001V020	48	1	20	In what I am writing to you, before God I am not lying.
B048C001V021	48	1	21	Then I came into the regions of Syria and Cilicia.
B048C001V022	48	1	22	I was not known by face to the churches of Christ in Judaea.
B048C001V023	48	1	23	Only they had heard that "he who used to persecute us is now telling the good news of the faith of which he once made havoc,"
B048C001V024	48	1	24	and they glorified God on my account.
B048C002V001	48	2	1	THEN after fourteen years I again went up to Jerusalem with Barnabas, taking along Titus.
B048C002V002	48	2	2	I went up by revelation, and I stated to them the good news which I proclaim among the Gentiles. But I did this privately before those who were most esteemed, that I might not be running, or have run, to no Purpose.
B048C002V003	48	2	3	But even Titus, who was with me and was a Greek, was not compelled to be circumcised,
B048C002V004	48	2	4	though it was suggested on account of false brethren who had been brought in, who had crept in to spy out our liberty which we have in Christ Jesus, in order to enslave us.
B048C002V005	48	2	5	But we did not yield in subjection to them even for an hour, that the truth of the good news might continue with you.
B048C002V006	48	2	6	But from those who were esteemed to be something \'97 whatever they were, it makes no difference to me; God does not regard the social standing of a man \'97 those who were most esteemed did not impart to me anything additional.
B048C002V007	48	2	7	But, on the contrary, seeing that I was entrusted with the good news for the uncircumcision as Peter was for the circumcision,
B048C002V008	48	2	8	for he who had worked in Peter for the apostleship to the circumcision had worked in me for the Gentiles,
B048C002V009	48	2	9	recognizing the grace given to me, James, Cephas, and John, who were regarded as pillars, gave the right hand of fellowship to me and Barnabas, that we should go to the Gentiles and they to the circumcision.
B048C002V010	48	2	10	Only they wished us to remember the poor. This very thing I also was earnest in doing.
B048C002V011	48	2	11	But when Peter came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face, because he had been justly censured.
B048C002V012	48	2	12	For before certain persons came from James, he was eating with the Gentiles. But when they came, he drew back and separated himself, fearing those who were of the circumcision.
B048C002V013	48	2	13	And the rest of the Jews practiced the same hypocrisy with him, so that even Barnabas was led off with them in their hypocrisy.
B048C002V014	48	2	14	But when I saw that they were not walking straight according to the truth of the good news, I said to Cephas before them all, "If you who are a Jew are living like a Gentile and not like a Jew, how can you compel the Gentiles to live like Jews?"
B048C002V015	48	2	15	We who are Jews by nature and not sinners of the Gentiles,
B048C002V016	48	2	16	knowing that a man is not declared righteous because of works of law, but through faith in Christ Jesus, we also have put our faith in Christ Jesus that we may be declared righteous because of faith in Christ, and not because of works of law, for because of works of law no human being will be declared righteous.
B048C002V017	48	2	17	If while seeking to be declared righteous in Christ we ourselves are found sinners, is Christ then a servant of sin? Never.
B048C002V018	48	2	18	For if I am building up again what I pulled down, I show myself as a transgressor.
B048C002V019	48	2	19	For I through law died to law that I might live to God.
B048C002V020	48	2	20	I have been crucified with Christ. I am living, yet no longer I, but Christ is living in me. The life that I am now living in flesh I am living by faith in the Son of God, who loved me and gave himself for me.
B048C002V021	48	2	21	I do not make nothing of the grace of God, for if righteousness is through law, then Christ died for nothing.
B048C003V001	48	3	1	O THOUGHTLESS Galatians, who has bewitched you before whose eyes Jesus Christ was pictured crucified?
B048C003V002	48	3	2	Only this I wish to learn from you: Was it because of works of law that you received the Spirit, or because of hearing with faith?
B048C003V003	48	3	3	Are you so thoughtless? After beginning with spirit are you now finishing with flesh?
B048C003V004	48	3	4	Have you suffered such things to no purpose? \'97 if it is to no purpose.
B048C003V005	48	3	5	He who supplies to you the Spirit and works miracles among you, is he doing it because of works of law or because of hearing with faith,
B048C003V006	48	3	6	just as Abraham had faith in God and it was credited to him for righteousness?
B048C003V007	48	3	7	You know, then, that those who are of faith \'97 they are children of Abraham.
B048C003V008	48	3	8	For the Scripture, foreseeing that God would declare the Gentiles righteous because of faith, announced the good news in advance to Abraham, "In you all the Gentiles will be blessed."
B048C003V009	48	3	9	So then those who are of faith are blessed with faithful Abraham.
B048C003V010	48	3	10	For all who are of the works of law are under a curse, for it is written, "Cursed is every one who does not abide by all the precepts of the book of the Law and do them."
B048C003V011	48	3	11	But that by law no one is declared righteous before God is plain, because, "He who is righteous by faith shall live."
B048C003V012	48	3	12	But the Law is not of faith, but "He who does these things shall live by them."
B048C003V013	48	3	13	Christ redeemed us from the curse of the Law by becoming a curse for our sake, for it is written, "Cursed is every one who hangs on a tree,"
B048C003V014	48	3	14	in order that the blessing of Abraham might in Jesus Christ come on the Gentiles, that they might receive through faith the promise of the Spirit.
B048C003V015	48	3	15	Brethren, I am speaking humanly, a ratified covenant, although but a man's, no one can set aside or add to.
B048C003V016	48	3	16	But the promises were spoken to Abraham and to his offspring. It does not say, "and to offsprings," as meaning many, but as if meaning one, "and to your offspring," who is Christ.
B048C003V017	48	3	17	I mean this, a covenant ratified by God, the Law that came four hundred and thirty years afterward does not annul, so as to defeat the promise.
B048C003V018	48	3	18	For if the inheritance is by law, it is no longer by promise. But God granted it to Abraham by promise.
B048C003V019	48	3	19	Why then was the Law? It was added later to make transgressions, until the Offspring should come to whom the promise had been made, and it was arranged through angels by the hand of a mediator.
B048C003V020	48	3	20	A mediator does not belong to one person, but God is one.
B048C003V021	48	3	21	Is the Law then against the promises of God? Never! For if a law had been given which could give life, then really righteousness would have come by law.
B048C003V022	48	3	22	But the Scripture has shut up all under sin that the promise based on faith in Jesus Christ may be given to those who have faith.
B048C003V023	48	3	23	Before faith came we were guarded under law, shut up waiting for the faith that was to be revealed.
B048C003V024	48	3	24	Thus the Law became our tutor leading us to Christ, that we might be declared righteous by faith.
B048C003V025	48	3	25	Now that faith has come, we are no longer under a tutor.
B048C003V026	48	3	26	You are all sons of God through faith in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V027	48	3	27	All who have been baptized into Christ have put on Christ.
B048C003V028	48	3	28	There cannot be Jew or Greek, slave or free, male or female: for you all are one in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V029	48	3	29	If you are Christ's, then you are Abraham's offspring and heirs according to the promise.
B048C004V001	48	4	1	I SAY that as long as the heir is under age he differs in nothing from a slave, though he be owner of all.
B048C004V002	48	4	2	But he is under guardians and managers until the day appointed by the father.
B048C004V003	48	4	3	So we, when we were under age, were enslaved under the elementary lessons of the world;
B048C004V004	48	4	4	but, when the fullness of time came, God sent forth his Son born of a woman, born under the Law,
B048C004V005	48	4	5	that he might redeem those who were under Law, that we might receive the recognition as sons.
B048C004V006	48	4	6	Because you are sons, God has sent into our hearts the Spirit of his Son crying Abba, Father.
B048C004V007	48	4	7	So you are no longer a slave, but a son, and if a son, then also an heir, through God's act.
B048C004V008	48	4	8	At the time when you did not know God you were enslaved to what by nature are not gods.
B048C004V009	48	4	9	But now that you know God, or rather have been known by God, how are you turning back to the weak and beggarly elementary lessons to which you wish to be slaves again?
B048C004V010	48	4	10	You observe days and months and seasons and years.
B048C004V011	48	4	11	You make me afraid that I have labored over you uselessly.
B048C004V012	48	4	12	Become like me, brethren, I beg of you, for I became like you. You have not wronged me in anything.
B048C004V013	48	4	13	You know that because of weakness of the flesh I told you the good news at first.
B048C004V014	48	4	14	And you did not despise or spurn what was a trial to you in my bodily condition, but welcomed me as you would an angel of God, as you would Christ Jesus.
B048C004V015	48	4	15	Where now is the blessing you pronounced on me? For I bear you witness that if it had been possible you would have plucked out your own eyes and given them to me.
B048C004V016	48	4	16	Have I become your enemy because I tell you the truth?
B048C004V017	48	4	17	They are paying court to you, but not honorably. No, they wish to shut you out, so that you may pay court to them.
B048C004V018	48	4	18	It is honorable to be courted in an honorable matter always, and not only when I am with you,
B048C004V019	48	4	19	my children, for whom I again am suffering birth pangs until Christ is formed in you.
B048C004V020	48	4	20	Would that I could be present with you now and could change my tone, for I am at a loss about you.
B048C004V021	48	4	21	Tell me, you who wish to be under law, do you not hear the Law?
B048C004V022	48	4	22	For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one born of the slave girl and one born of the free wife.
B048C004V023	48	4	23	But he who was born of the slave girl was born according to the flesh, while he who was born of the free wife was born by promise.
B048C004V024	48	4	24	This is an allegory. For these women are the two covenants, one from Mount Sinai, bearing children for slavery. This is Hagar.
B048C004V025	48	4	25	Hagar is Mount Sinai in Arabia. She represents the present Jerusalem, for she is in slavery along with her children.
B048C004V026	48	4	26	But the Jerusalem on high is free and she is our mother.
B048C004V027	48	4	27	For it is written, "Rejoice, O barren one, you who do not bear! Break forth and shout, you who feel no birth pangs! For many are the children of the desolate \'97 more than those of her who has a husband."
B048C004V028	48	4	28	But you, brethren, are, as Isaac was, children of promise.
B048C004V029	48	4	29	But just as then he who was born according to the flesh persecuted him who was born according to the Spirit, so it is now.
B048C004V030	48	4	30	But what says the Scripture? "Cast out the slave girl and her son. For the son of the slave girl shall not inherit along with the son of the free wife."
B048C004V031	48	4	31	Therefore, brethren, we are not children of a slave girl, but of the free wife.
B048C005V001	48	5	1	STAND firm, therefore, in the freedom with which Christ set us free, and do not wear any yoke of slavery.
B048C005V002	48	5	2	See, I, Paul, tell you that if you receive circumcision, Christ will be of no use to you.
B048C005V003	48	5	3	I testify again to every man who receives circumcision that he is under obligation to carry out the whole Law.
B048C005V004	48	5	4	You have put an end to Christ's work for you, you who are declared righteous by law; you have fallen away from grace.
B048C005V005	48	5	5	For we in the Spirit because of faith are waiting for the hope of righteousness.
B048C005V006	48	5	6	For in Christ Jesus neither has circumcision any value nor uncircumcision, but faith working through love.
B048C005V007	48	5	7	You were running finely. Who hindered you from obeying the truth?
B048C005V008	48	5	8	The persuasion was not from him who called you.
B048C005V009	48	5	9	A little yeast sets the whole lump fermenting.
B048C005V010	48	5	10	I am persuaded in regard to you in the Lord that you will have no other mind. He who is troubling you must bear his condemnation, whoever he may be.
B048C005V011	48	5	11	But I, brethren, if I am still proclaiming circumcision, why am I persecuted? Then the offensiveness of the cross has been done away.
B048C005V012	48	5	12	Would that those who are troubling you would even cut off all!
B048C005V013	48	5	13	For you were called to freedom, brethren; only do not let your freedom be an opportunity for the flesh, but in love be servants to one another.
B048C005V014	48	5	14	For the whole Law is summed up in one word: "You shall love your neighbor as yourself."
B048C005V015	48	5	15	But if you bite and devour one another, take care that you are not destroyed by one another.
B048C005V016	48	5	16	I say, walk in the Spirit and you will not carry out the passions of the flesh.
B048C005V017	48	5	17	For the flesh has passions contrary to the Spirit and the Spirit contrary to the flesh, for these are opposed to each other, so that you may not do whatever you wish.
B048C005V018	48	5	18	But if you are led by the Spirit you are not under law.
B048C005V019	48	5	19	The works of the flesh are obvious, such as unchastity, impurity, indecency,
B048C005V020	48	5	20	idolatry, magic, hatred, strife, jealousy, anger, rivalries, dissensions, factions,
B048C005V021	48	5	21	envyings, drinking bouts, revelries, and the like. Of these I tell you beforehand, as I have already told you, that those who practice such things will not inherit the kingdom of God.
B048C005V022	48	5	22	But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, slowness to anger, kindness, benevolence, faithfulness,
B048C005V023	48	5	23	gentleness, self-control; against such there is no law.
B048C005V024	48	5	24	Those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified the flesh with its emotions and passions.
B048C005V025	48	5	25	If we are living in the Spirit let us direct our lives by the Spirit.
B048C005V026	48	5	26	Let us not be vainglorious, irritating one another, envying one another.
B048C006V001	48	6	1	BRETHREN, if a man is surprised in some sin, you who are spiritual are to restore such a one in a spirit of gentleness, each looking out for himself to avoid being tempted.
B048C006V002	48	6	2	Bear one another's burdens and so fulfill the law of Christ.
B048C006V003	48	6	3	If any one thinks that he is something when he is nothing, he deceives himself.
B048C006V004	48	6	4	Let each one test his own work and then he will have his reason for boasting in himself alone and not in another.
B048C006V005	48	6	5	For each must bear his own load.
B048C006V006	48	6	6	Let him who is taught the message share with his teacher in all good things.
B048C006V007	48	6	7	Do not be deceived; God is not mocked; what a man sows that he will also reap.
B048C006V008	48	6	8	For he who sows to his own flesh will from the flesh reap decay; but he who sows to the Spirit will from the Spirit reap life eternal.
B048C006V009	48	6	9	Let us not grow discouraged in doing what is noble, for in due time we shall reap if we do not grow faint.
B048C006V010	48	6	10	So then as we have opportunity let us work for the good of all men, and especially of those who belong to the household of the faith.
B048C006V011	48	6	11	See with what great letters I write with my own hand.
B048C006V012	48	6	12	All who wish to make a fair show in the flesh are trying to compel you to receive circumcision, but only that they may not be persecuted for the cross of Christ.
B048C006V013	48	6	13	For even those who are circumcised do not themselves keep the Law, but they wish you to be circumcised in order to boast in your flesh.
B048C006V014	48	6	14	But let me never boast except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by which the world is crucified to me and I to the world.
B048C006V015	48	6	15	For neither is circumcision anything nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.
B048C006V016	48	6	16	All who walk by this rule \'97 may peace and mercy be on them, and on the Israel of God!
B048C006V017	48	6	17	For the future let no one trouble me; for I bear on my body the brands of Jesus.
B048C006V018	48	6	18	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirits, brethren. Amen.
B049C001V001	49	1	1	PAUL, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, to the Holy who are at Ephesus, faithful in Christ Jesus:
B049C001V002	49	1	2	Grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ!
B049C001V003	49	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly heights in Christ,
B049C001V004	49	1	4	even as he chose us in him before the foundation of the world to be holy and spotless before him in love.
B049C001V005	49	1	5	He predestined us to recognition as sons to himself through Jesus Christ according to the kindness of his will,
B049C001V006	49	1	6	to the praise of his glorious grace which he bestowed on us in the Beloved,
B049C001V007	49	1	7	in whom we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of our sins, according to the wealth of his loving kindness
B049C001V008	49	1	8	which he made to abound toward us in all wisdom and understanding.
B049C001V009	49	1	9	He has made known to us the mystery of his will according to his grace which he purposed in him
B049C001V010	49	1	10	for the government of the fullness of the ages, to bring to unity all things in Christ, both things in the heavens and things on the earth.
B049C001V011	49	1	11	In him we were predestined according to the plan of him who works in all things according to the purpose of his will,
B049C001V012	49	1	12	and we were made God's heritage in order that we might bring praise to his glory \'97 we who first have fixed our hope on Christ.
B049C001V013	49	1	13	In him you also, after hearing the message of the truth, the good news of your salvation, and putting your faith in him, were sealed by the promised Holy Spirit,
B049C001V014	49	1	14	which is the pledge of our inheritance in anticipation of the full redemption of God's own people to the praise of his glory.
B049C001V015	49	1	15	For this reason I also, since hearing of your faith in Jesus and your love to all the saints,
B049C001V016	49	1	16	never cease giving thanks for you when I mention you in my prayers,
B049C001V017	49	1	17	that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father most glorious, may give to you a spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of himself,
B049C001V018	49	1	18	enlightening the eyes of your heart, that you may know what is the hope of his calling, and what the glorious wealth of his inheritance in the holy,
B049C001V019	49	1	19	and what the surpassing greatness of his power toward us who believe according to the inworking of his vast might,
B049C001V020	49	1	20	which he put forth in Christ when he raised him from the dead and made him sit at his own right hand in the heavenly heights,
B049C001V021	49	1	21	far above every archangel and authority and power and lordship and every name that is named not only in this world but also in the world to come.
B049C001V022	49	1	22	He put all things under his feet and placed him as head over all for the church,
B049C001V023	49	1	23	which is his body, the fullness of him who fills all in all.
B049C002V001	49	2	1	YOU also God raised to life when you were dead in misdeeds and sins
B049C002V002	49	2	2	in which you once walked, following the ways of this age of the world, led by the Ruler of the power of the air, the spirit who now works in the sons of disobedience.
B049C002V003	49	2	3	Among these we all lived once in the passions of our flesh and of our thoughts, and we were by nature children of wrath like the rest.
B049C002V004	49	2	4	But God, who is rich in mercy, because of his great love with which he loved us,
B049C002V005	49	2	5	even when we were dead in misdeeds, made us alive along with Christ \'97 by grace we have been saved \'97
B049C002V006	49	2	6	and raised us up with him and made us sit with him in the heavenly heights in Christ Jesus,
B049C002V007	49	2	7	that he might show in the ages to come the surpassing richness of his grace in his kindness to us in Christ Jesus.
B049C002V008	49	2	8	For by grace you have been saved through faith, and that not of yourselves; it is the gift of God,
B049C002V009	49	2	9	not of works, that no one may boast.
B049C002V010	49	2	10	For we are his work, formed in Christ Jesus for good works in which God had prepared beforehand to have us live.
B049C002V011	49	2	11	Therefore remember that once you were Gentiles in the flesh and were called uncircumcision by the so-called circumcision in the flesh, made by hands,
B049C002V012	49	2	12	and that you were then apart from Christ, aliens from the commonwealth of Israel and strangers to the covenants of promise, without hope and without God in the world.
B049C002V013	49	2	13	But now in Christ Jesus you who once were far have become near by the blood of Christ.
B049C002V014	49	2	14	For he is our peace. He has made both Jew and Gentile one and has broken down the dividing wall, the enmity.
B049C002V015	49	2	15	In his own flesh he has ended the force of the law of commandments in ordinances in order to make the two, in himself, into one new man, thus making peace,
B049C002V016	49	2	16	and in order to reconcile both in one body to God through his cross, by slaying the enmity by it.
B049C002V017	49	2	17	And he came and brought the good news of peace to you who were far and peace to those who were near.
B049C002V018	49	2	18	For through him we, both Jews and Gentiles, have access through one Spirit to the Father.
B049C002V019	49	2	19	So then you are no longer strangers and resident aliens, but fellow citizens with the holy and members of the household of God,
B049C002V020	49	2	20	built on the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Jesus Christ himself being the corner stone.
B049C002V021	49	2	21	In him all the building, framed together, is growing into a holy temple in the Lord,
B049C002V022	49	2	22	in whom you also are being built for a dwelling of God in the Spirit.
B049C003V001	49	3	1	FOR this reason I, Paul, the prisoner of Christ Jesus for the sake of you Gentiles, \'97
B049C003V002	49	3	2	if you have heard of the gracious commission which God has given me to you,
B049C003V003	49	3	3	that by revelation the mystery has been disclosed to me, as I wrote before briefly,
B049C003V004	49	3	4	In reading that letter you can learn my understanding in the mystery of Christ,
B049C003V005	49	3	5	a mystery which was not disclosed in other generations to the sons of men as it has now been revealed to his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit,
B049C003V006	49	3	6	namely, that the Gentiles are fellow heirs and fellow members of the body, fellow sharers of the promise in Christ Jesus through the good news,
B049C003V007	49	3	7	of which I became a servant according to the free grace of God which was given me by the inworking of his power.
B049C003V008	49	3	8	To me, the least of all the holy, has this grace been given, to proclaim to the Gentiles the good news of the unsearchable riches of Christ
B049C003V009	49	3	9	and to show what is the working of the mystery which has been hidden for ages in God, who created all things
B049C003V010	49	3	10	in order to disclose now to the archangels and powers in the heavenly heights, through the church, the varied wisdom of God,
B049C003V011	49	3	11	according to the eternal purpose which he has accomplished by Christ Jesus our Lord,
B049C003V012	49	3	12	in whom we have boldness and confident access through faith in him.
B049C003V013	49	3	13	So I beg you not to lose heart because of the distresses that come on me for your sake. They are a high honor to you.
B049C003V014	49	3	14	For this reason I bow my knees to the Father
B049C003V015	49	3	15	from whom every family in heaven and on earth is named,
B049C003V016	49	3	16	that he may grant to you according to his glorious wealth to be strengthened with might through his Spirit in the inner man,
B049C003V017	49	3	17	that Christ may dwell in your hearts through faith, and that you, rooted and founded in love,
B049C003V018	49	3	18	may be able with all the holy to comprehend what is the breadth and length and height and depth \'97
B049C003V019	49	3	19	yes, to know the love of Christ, which yet surpasses knowledge, and may be filled with all the fullness of God.
B049C003V020	49	3	20	To him who is able to do far beyond all we ask or think by the power that works in us,
B049C003V021	49	3	21	to him be glory in the church and in Christ Jesus through all the generations of the ages! Amen.
B049C004V001	49	4	1	I, THE prisoner of the Lord, beg you, then, to live worthily of the calling with which you have been called,
B049C004V002	49	4	2	with all modesty and gentleness, being slow to anger, bearing with one another in love,
B049C004V003	49	4	3	earnest in keeping the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace.
B049C004V004	49	4	4	There is one body and one Spirit, just as you were called with one hope that belongs to your calling,
B049C004V005	49	4	5	one Lord, one faith, one baptism,
B049C004V006	49	4	6	one God and Father of all, who is over all and through all and in all.
B049C004V007	49	4	7	To each one of us grace was given according to the measure of the gift of Christ.
B049C004V008	49	4	8	Therefore it says, "He ascended on high; he led away captives; he gave gifts to men."
B049C004V009	49	4	9	What does "he ascended" mean, except that he had descended into the lowest parts of the earth?
B049C004V010	49	4	10	He who descended is also he who "ascended" high above all the heavens to fill all things.
B049C004V011	49	4	11	And he "gave" to some to be apostles, some prophets, some tellers of the good news, some shepherds and teachers,
B049C004V012	49	4	12	for the equipment of the saints, for the work of service, for building up the body of Christ,
B049C004V013	49	4	13	until we all attain oneness in the faith and the knowledge of the Son of God, and the maturity of manhood and the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ.
B049C004V014	49	4	14	Then we shall be no longer children tossed and borne about by every wind of teaching through the trickery of men and craftiness in the devices of deceit,
B049C004V015	49	4	15	but speaking the truth in love we shall grow wholly into him who is the head, Christ,
B049C004V016	49	4	16	from whom the whole body framed together and strengthened by what every joint supplies vigorously, in the measure of each, makes growth in building itself up in love.
B049C004V017	49	4	17	This then I say and solemnly protest in the Lord: that you are no longer to live as the Gentiles live in vacancy of mind,
B049C004V018	49	4	18	having their understanding darkened, aliens from the life of God because of the ignorance that is in them, and because of the hardness of their hearts.
B049C004V019	49	4	19	Lost to any sense of shame they have abandoned themselves to sensuality for the practice of every kind of impurity with greediness.
B049C004V020	49	4	20	But you have not so learned Christ,
B049C004V021	49	4	21	if you have heard him and have been taught in him as the truth is in Jesus,
B049C004V022	49	4	22	that you should put away the old man who belonged to your former way of life and was perishing in deluding passions,
B049C004V023	49	4	23	and that you should be made new in the spirit of your minds
B049C004V024	49	4	24	and put on the new man formed as God approves in the righteousness and holiness of truth.
B049C004V025	49	4	25	Therefore put aside lying and speak truth every one to his neighbor, for we are members one of another.
B049C004V026	49	4	26	"Be angry and do not sin." Do not let the sun go down on your wrath,
B049C004V027	49	4	27	neither give place for the Devil.
B049C004V028	49	4	28	He who steals must steal no longer, but rather he must labor, working with his own hands something good, so as to have something to share with any one in need.
B049C004V029	49	4	29	Let no vile word come out of your mouth, but, if anything, a good word for needed upbuilding of character to give grace to those who hear.
B049C004V030	49	4	30	Do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God by whom you have been sealed for the day of redemption.
B049C004V031	49	4	31	Let all bitterness and anger and wrath and clamor and abusive language be put away from you with every kind of malice.
B049C004V032	49	4	32	Be kind to one another, sympathetic, forgiving one another just as God in Christ has forgiven you.
B049C005V001	49	5	1	BE imitators of God as beloved children
B049C005V002	49	5	2	and live in love, as Christ loved us and gave himself for us, an offering and sacrifice to God yielding a fragrant odor.
B049C005V003	49	5	3	Unchastity or any kind of impurity or greediness must not be mentioned among you, as befits holy people;
B049C005V004	49	5	4	nor should there be indecent and foolish talk or jesting, which are unbecoming, but rather thanksgiving.
B049C005V005	49	5	5	For you know well that no unchaste or impure person, no greedy person \'97 who is an idolater \'97 has any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and God.
B049C005V006	49	5	6	Let no one deceive you with empty words; for because of these things the wrath of God comes on the sons of disobedience.
B049C005V007	49	5	7	Do not, then, be partakers with them.
B049C005V008	49	5	8	For you were once darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Live like children of light \'97
B049C005V009	49	5	9	for the fruit of light appears in all generosity and righteousness and truth \'97
B049C005V010	49	5	10	testing what is pleasing to the Lord,
B049C005V011	49	5	11	and have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them,
B049C005V012	49	5	12	for the things that they do in secret it is shameful even to speak of.
B049C005V013	49	5	13	But all things when reproved are shown truly by the light, for everything shown truly is light.
B049C005V014	49	5	14	Therefore it says, "Wake, O sleeper, and rise from the dead and Christ will give you light."
B049C005V015	49	5	15	Be strictly careful, then, how you live, not as unwise but as wise.
B049C005V016	49	5	16	Buy up the opportunity, because these are evil days.
B049C005V017	49	5	17	Therefore do not be thoughtless, but understand what is the Lord's will.
B049C005V018	49	5	18	Do not be drunk with wine, in which there is profligacy, but be full of the Spirit,
B049C005V019	49	5	19	speaking to one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and playing the harp heartily to the Lord,
B049C005V020	49	5	20	giving thanks always for all things in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ to God the Father.
B049C005V021	49	5	21	Be subject to one another in reverence for Christ,
B049C005V022	49	5	22	wives to their own husbands as in the Lord,
B049C005V023	49	5	23	because a man is the head of his wife as Christ is the head of the church and he is the savior of the body.
B049C005V024	49	5	24	But as the church is subject to Christ, so wives are to their husbands in everything.
B049C005V025	49	5	25	Husbands, love your wives, as Christ also loved the church and gave himself for it,
B049C005V026	49	5	26	that he might make it holy, cleansing it by the washing with water according to his word,
B049C005V027	49	5	27	that he might present to himself the church glorious, without spot or wrinkle or any such thing, but holy and faultless.
B049C005V028	49	5	28	Thus ought men to love their own wives as their own bodies. He who loves his own wife loves himself,
B049C005V029	49	5	29	for no one ever hates his own flesh, but nourishes and cherishes it, just as Christ does the church,
B049C005V030	49	5	30	for we are members of his body.
B049C005V031	49	5	31	"Therefore shall a man leave his father and his mother and shall cleave to his wife and the two shall become one flesh.
B049C005V032	49	5	32	"This mystery is great, but I am speaking of Christ and the church.
B049C005V033	49	5	33	But each one of you must love his own wife as himself, and the wife must reverence her husband.
B049C006V001	49	6	1	CHILDREN, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right.
B049C006V002	49	6	2	"Honor your father and your mother." This is the first commandment with a promise,
B049C006V003	49	6	3	"That it may go well with you and you may be long-lived in the land."
B049C006V004	49	6	4	And you, fathers, do not irritate your children, but bring them up in the education and admonition of the Lord.
B049C006V005	49	6	5	Slaves, obey those who according to the flesh are your masters, with reverence and awe in singleness of your hearts as to Christ,
B049C006V006	49	6	6	not with eye service as pleasers of men, but as Christ's slaves, doing the will of God in a whole-souled way,
B049C006V007	49	6	7	giving service with cheerfulness as to the Lord and not to men,
B049C006V008	49	6	8	knowing that whatever good thing each one does that he will be rewarded for by the Lord, whether he be slave or free.
B049C006V009	49	6	9	And you, masters, do the same by them, avoiding threats, knowing that the Master both of them and of you is in the heavens, and there is no partiality for rank with him.
B049C006V010	49	6	10	To conclude: Be strong in the Lord and in the power of his might.
B049C006V011	49	6	11	Put on the complete armor of God so that you may be able to stand against the cunning arts of the Devil.
B049C006V012	49	6	12	For our wrestling is not against flesh and blood, but against the arch-angels, against the authorities, against the world-rulers of this darkness, against spiritual forces of wickedness in the heavenly heights.
B049C006V013	49	6	13	Therefore take the complete armor of God, that you may be able to withstand in the evil day and, after going through everything, to stand.
B049C006V014	49	6	14	Stand, then, belted with truth, wearing the breastplate of righteousness,
B049C006V015	49	6	15	shod with the readiness of the good news of peace.
B049C006V016	49	6	16	In every event take up the shield of faith by which you will be able to quench all the fiery darts of the Evil One,
B049C006V017	49	6	17	and accept the helmet of salvation and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God.
B049C006V018	49	6	18	Pray at all times in the Spirit with all manner of prayer and entreaty; be awake to this with all intentness and with prayer for all the holy
B049C006V019	49	6	19	and in my behalf, that words may be given to me when I open my month to make known with fearlessness the mystery of the good news,
B049C006V020	49	6	20	for which I am an ambassador in chains, that I may tell it fearlessly as I ought.
B049C006V021	49	6	21	That you also may know my situation, what I am doing, Tychicus the beloved brother and faithful servant in the Lord,
B049C006V022	49	6	22	whom I am sending to you for this very purpose, will tell you everything, so that you may know the news of me and he may encourage your hearts.
B049C006V023	49	6	23	Peace to the brethren and love with faith from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ!
B049C006V024	49	6	24	Grace be with all who love our Lord Jesus Christ with undying love!
B050C001V001	50	1	1	PAUL and Timothy, servants of Christ Jesus, to all the Holy in Christ Jesus who are in Philippi, with Bishops and Deacons:
B050C001V002	50	1	2	Grace be to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B050C001V003	50	1	3	I thank my God for all your remembrance of me,
B050C001V004	50	1	4	always in every prayer of mine for you all making request with joy
B050C001V005	50	1	5	for your fellowship in spreading the good news from the first day until now,
B050C001V006	50	1	6	being confident of this very thing, that he who has begun the good work in you will carry it on to completion on the day of Christ Jesus.
B050C001V007	50	1	7	So it is right for me to think of you all, because you have me in your hearts, and in my chains and in my defense and in establishing the good news you are all sharers in my privilege.
B050C001V008	50	1	8	For God is my witness how much I long for you all in the affections of Christ Jesus.
B050C001V009	50	1	9	And this is my prayer that your love may abound more and more in knowledge and all insight,
B050C001V010	50	1	10	so that you may discriminate between the things that differ, that you may be pure and blameless in the day of Christ,
B050C001V011	50	1	11	filled with the fruit of knowledge through Jesus Christ to the glory and praise of God.
B050C001V012	50	1	12	I wish you to know, brethren, that my affairs have turned out rather to the furtherance of the good news,
B050C001V013	50	1	13	so that my chains have become well known as for Christ to the whole Praetorian Guard and to all the rest,
B050C001V014	50	1	14	and the most of the brethren in the Lord, made confident by my chains, are unusually brave in speaking the message fearlessly.
B050C001V015	50	1	15	Some indeed proclaim Christ because of envy and rivalry, some also because of good will.
B050C001V016	50	1	16	Some announce Christ from love, knowing that I am placed for the defense of the good news,
B050C001V017	50	1	17	but others out of partisanship, thinking to add distress to my chains.
B050C001V018	50	1	18	What then? Still in every way, whether in pretense or in truth, Christ is proclaimed and in that I rejoice, yes, and will rejoice.
B050C001V019	50	1	19	For I know that this will make for my salvation through your prayer and the supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ,
B050C001V020	50	1	20	according to my earnest expectation and hope that I may be put to shame in nothing, but with all courage, as always, so now Christ may be honored in my body, whether by my life or by my death.
B050C001V021	50	1	21	For to me to live is Christ and to die is gain.
B050C001V022	50	1	22	If it is to be life in the flesh, that means fruitful work for me. I know not which to choose.
B050C001V023	50	1	23	I am under pressure both ways, having the desire to depart and be with Christ, for it is far better,
B050C001V024	50	1	24	yet that I should stay in the flesh is more needful on your account.
B050C001V025	50	1	25	And this I confidently know, that I shall stay and stay near you all for your advancement and joy of faith,
B050C001V026	50	1	26	that your exultation in Christ Jesus may overflow on my account, because of my presence again with you.
B050C001V027	50	1	27	Only exercise your citizenship in a manner worthy of the good news of Christ, so that, whether I come and see you or in absence hear news of you, I may know that you are standing in one spirit, with one mind wrestling in the faith of the good news
B050C001V028	50	1	28	and not frightened in anything by your adversaries, which for them is a sign of ruin, but for you of salvation, and that from God;
B050C001V029	50	1	29	because it has been graciously allowed you not only to believe in Christ but also to suffer for his sake,
B050C001V030	50	1	30	and you have the same struggle that you saw in me and now hear of in me.
B050C002V001	50	2	1	IF there is any encouragement in Christ, any persuasive power in love, any fellowship in the Spirit, any sympathies and compassions,
B050C002V002	50	2	2	fill up my joy by having the same love, being of the same mind, thinking the same thing,
B050C002V003	50	2	3	doing nothing in a partisan or vainglorious way, but each modestly regarding the others as of more account than himself.
B050C002V004	50	2	4	Do not be each intent on his own interests, but also on the interests of others.
B050C002V005	50	2	5	Let this mind be in you which was also in Christ Jesus,
B050C002V006	50	2	6	who, though he was in the form of God, did not think that equality with God was something to be grasped,
B050C002V007	50	2	7	but emptied himself, taking the form of a servant and coming into the likeness of men,
B050C002V008	50	2	8	and when found in the condition of a man he humbled himself by becoming obedient even to death \'97 death on the cross.
B050C002V009	50	2	9	Therefore, God has highly exalted him and has graciously given him the name which is above every name,
B050C002V010	50	2	10	that at the name of Jesus every knee may bow, of beings in heaven and those on earth and those under the earth,
B050C002V011	50	2	11	and every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.
B050C002V012	50	2	12	So then, my beloved, as you have always obeyed, not in my presence only, but now much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with reverence and awe.
B050C002V013	50	2	13	For it is God who is working in you both the willing and the doing because of his kindness.
B050C002V014	50	2	14	Do everything without murmurings or disputings
B050C002V015	50	2	15	that you may be blameless and pure, children of God, spotless in the midst of a crooked and perverse generation among whom you shine as lights in the world,
B050C002V016	50	2	16	holding forth the message of life, so that on the day of Christ I can boast that I did not run in vain or labor in vain.
B050C002V017	50	2	17	But if I am poured out as a libation on your sacrificial offering of faith, I rejoice and share the joy of you all.
B050C002V018	50	2	18	In the same way you must rejoice and share my joy.
B050C002V019	50	2	19	But I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you soon, that I may be cheered by knowing about you.
B050C002V020	50	2	20	For I have no one likeminded with him who will so sincerely care for your interests.
B050C002V021	50	2	21	For all pursue their own aims, not those of Christ Jesus.
B050C002V022	50	2	22	But you know how he has been tested and how like a child with a father he has served with me in spreading the good news.
B050C002V023	50	2	23	So I hope to send him at once when I see how my affairs are going.
B050C002V024	50	2	24	And I trust in the Lord that I myself shall come quickly.
B050C002V025	50	2	25	I think it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus, my brother and fellow worker and fellow soldier, and your messenger and minister to my needs,
B050C002V026	50	2	26	since he longs for you all and is troubled because you have heard that he was sick.
B050C002V027	50	2	27	Indeed he was sick and near to death. But God had mercy on him, and not on him alone, but also on me, that I might not have sorrow upon sorrow.
B050C002V028	50	2	28	I send him the more readily that you may see him and rejoice again and I be less sorrowful.
B050C002V029	50	2	29	Receive him in the Lord with all joy and hold such men in honor,
B050C002V030	50	2	30	because for the work of Christ he was near to death, hazarding his life to complete the service you were not here to do for me.
B050C003V001	50	3	1	TO conclude, my brethren: rejoice in the Lord. To repeat to you the same things is not tiresome to me and it is safe for you.
B050C003V002	50	3	2	Beware of the dogs, beware of the bad workmen, beware of the excision.
B050C003V003	50	3	3	For we are the circumcision, we who worship in the Spirit of God and exult in Christ Jesus, and have no confidence in the flesh,
B050C003V004	50	3	4	though I have ground for confidence even in the flesh. If any other man thinks that he has ground for confidence in the flesh, I have more \'97
B050C003V005	50	3	5	circumcised the eighth day, of the race of Israel, of the tribe of Benjamin, a Hebrew of Hebrews, as to the Law a Pharisee,
B050C003V006	50	3	6	as to zeal persecuting the church, as to the righteousness of the Law blameless.
B050C003V007	50	3	7	But the things that were gain to me, those I have counted loss for Christ.
B050C003V008	50	3	8	Yes, I count all to be loss because of the surpassing worth of the knowledge of Christ Jesus my Lord, for whom I have suffered the loss of all things and count them but refuse, that I may gain Christ
B050C003V009	50	3	9	and be found in him, not having my own righteousness that was from the Law, but that which is through faith in Christ, the righteousness which comes from God and rests on faith,
B050C003V010	50	3	10	that I may know him and the power of his resurrection and the fellowship of his sufferings, becoming like him in death,
B050C003V011	50	3	11	if possibly I may attain to the resurrection from the dead.
B050C003V012	50	3	12	Not that I have already obtained it or have already been made perfect, but I press on to lay hold of that for which I was laid hold of by Christ Jesus.
B050C003V013	50	3	13	Brethren, I do not consider myself yet to have laid hold of it. But one thing I do: forgetting what is behind and stretching forward to what is in front
B050C003V014	50	3	14	I press toward the goal for the prize of the heavenly call of God in Christ Jesus.
B050C003V015	50	3	15	Let us all who are full grown think in this way. If in anything you think differently, even that God will reveal to you,
B050C003V016	50	3	16	but so far as we have attained let us walk in the same path.
B050C003V017	50	3	17	Unite in imitating me, brethren, and watch those who are living according to our example.
B050C003V018	50	3	18	For many are living as I used often to tell you and now say even weeping that they are enemies of the cross of Christ.
B050C003V019	50	3	19	Their end is ruin, their God is their stomach, their glory is in their shame, they think earthly thoughts.
B050C003V020	50	3	20	For the state of which we are citizens is in the heavens and from there we are expecting a Savior, the Lord Jesus Christ.
B050C003V021	50	3	21	He will transform the body we have in our low estate into the likeness of the body he has in glory by the power by which he can subject all things to himself.
B050C004V001	50	4	1	SO, my brethren beloved and longed for, my joy and crown, stand firm thus in the Lord, beloved.
B050C004V002	50	4	2	I beg Euodia and I beg Syntyche to be of the same mind in the Lord.
B050C004V003	50	4	3	Yes, I ask you, true yokefellow, help them, since they struggled in spreading the good news along with me and Clement and the rest of my fellow workers whose names are in the book of life.
B050C004V004	50	4	4	Rejoice in the Lord always. Again I say rejoice.
B050C004V005	50	4	5	Let your fairness be known to all men. The Lord is near.
B050C004V006	50	4	6	Do not worry, but in everything by prayer and entreaty with thanksgiving let your requests be made known to God.
B050C004V007	50	4	7	And the peace of God which passes all understanding will guard your hearts and your thoughts in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V008	50	4	8	To conclude, brethren, whatever is true, whatever is dignified, whatever is just, whatever is pure, whatever is lovable, whatever is highly spoken of \'97 if there is any virtue or any praise \'97 think of that.
B050C004V009	50	4	9	What you learned and accepted and heard and saw in me \'97 practice that. And the God of peace will be with you.
B050C004V010	50	4	10	I rejoiced in the Lord greatly that now at length your thoughtfulness for me had revived. You were thoughtful for me all along, but lacked opportunity.
B050C004V011	50	4	11	Not that I am speaking because of want; for I have learned how to be content in whatever circumstances I am.
B050C004V012	50	4	12	I know how to live humbly and I know how to enjoy abundance. In each and every situation I have been initiated into the secret both of being well fed and of going hungry, both of having abundance and of bearing want.
B050C004V013	50	4	13	I can do all things through him who gives me strength.
B050C004V014	50	4	14	Yet you did nobly in sharing with me in my distress.
B050C004V015	50	4	15	You Philippians know that at the beginning of the good news, when I came away from Macedonia, no church shared with me in the matter of giving and receiving except you only,
B050C004V016	50	4	16	and that in Thessalonica you sent once, yes, twice, for my need.
B050C004V017	50	4	17	Not that I am seeking for the gift, but I am seeking for the fruit that increases to your credit.
B050C004V018	50	4	18	I have enough of everything and more than enough. I am fully supplied since receiving from Epaphroditus the things from you, a fragrant odor, an acceptable sacrifice, pleasing to God.
B050C004V019	50	4	19	My God will supply every need of yours according to his wealth in glory in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V020	50	4	20	To God our Father be glory for the ages of the ages! Amen.
B050C004V021	50	4	21	Greet every holy one in Christ Jesus. The brethren with me send greetings to you.
B050C004V022	50	4	22	All the holy send greetings to you, especially those of Caesar's household.
B050C004V023	50	4	23	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirits!
B051C001V001	51	1	1	PAUL, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, and Timothy our brother,
B051C001V002	51	1	2	to the holy and faithful brethren in Christ in Colossae: Grace be to you and peace from God our Father!
B051C001V003	51	1	3	We always thank God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, in praying for you,
B051C001V004	51	1	4	because we have heard of your faith in Christ Jesus and the love that you have to all the holy
B051C001V005	51	1	5	because of the hope laid up for us in heaven. Of this you have already heard in the true message of the good news
B051C001V006	51	1	6	which has come to you. Just as in all the world it is bearing fruit and growing, so also it is among you since the day that you heard and learned of the grace of God in truth.
B051C001V007	51	1	7	So you learned it from Epaphras, our beloved fellow servant, who is a faithful servant of Christ in your behalf,
B051C001V008	51	1	8	and who has told us of your love in the Spirit.
B051C001V009	51	1	9	For this reason we also, from the day we heard it, never cease praying for you and asking that you may have full knowledge of his will in all wisdom and spiritual insight,
B051C001V010	51	1	10	and that you may live lives worthy of the Lord and please him in every way. May you bear fruit in every good work and grow in the knowledge of God.
B051C001V011	51	1	11	May you be strengthened with all strength according to his glorious power, so as to have all patience and endurance.
B051C001V012	51	1	12	May you joyfully give thanks to the Father who has made you fit to share in the inheritance of the holy in light.
B051C001V013	51	1	13	He has saved us from the power of darkness and transferred us into the kingdom of his beloved Son,
B051C001V014	51	1	14	in whom we have redemption, the forgiveness of our sins.
B051C001V015	51	1	15	He is the image of the invisible God, the first born of all creation;
B051C001V016	51	1	16	for in him were created all things in heaven and on earth, both visible and invisible, whether thrones or lordships or archangels or powers \'97 all things have been created through him and for him,
B051C001V017	51	1	17	and he is before all things and in him all things unite.
B051C001V018	51	1	18	And he is the head of the body, the church. He is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead, that he may be first in all things,
B051C001V019	51	1	19	because it pleased God to have all his fullness dwell in him
B051C001V020	51	1	20	and to reconcile all things to himself through him, making peace through the blood of his cross \'97 all things, I say, whether on earth or in heaven.
B051C001V021	51	1	21	And you who were once alienated and enemies in your minds, living in wicked works, he has reconciled
B051C001V022	51	1	22	by his body of flesh through death, to present you holy and spotless and blameless before him,
B051C001V023	51	1	23	if you remain in the faith, firm and steadfast, never moving from the hope of the good news which you have heard and which has been proclaimed in all the creation under heaven, and of which I, Paul, became a servant.
B051C001V024	51	1	24	Now I rejoice in what I suffer for your sake, and in my turn am filling up in my flesh what was lacking in the afflictions of Christ for the sake of his body, that is, the church.
B051C001V025	51	1	25	I became a servant of the church according to the commission from God given to me for you, to deliver fully God's message,
B051C001V026	51	1	26	the mystery hidden for ages and generations but now made plain to his holy ones,
B051C001V027	51	1	27	to whom God willed to make known what is the glorious wealth of this mystery among the Gentiles, which is Christ in you the hope of glory.
B051C001V028	51	1	28	And we are announcing him, warning every man and teaching every man in all wisdom in order that we may present every man complete in Christ.
B051C001V029	51	1	29	For this also I labor, wrestling with the energy of him who works powerfully within me.
B051C002V001	51	2	1	FOR I wish you to know how I am wrestling for you and for those in Laodicea and for all who have not seen my face in the flesh,
B051C002V002	51	2	2	that your hearts may be encouraged and that joined together in love you may reach all the wealth of the full assurance of insight into the knowledge of the mystery of God, which is Christ.
B051C002V003	51	2	3	In him all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge lie hidden.
B051C002V004	51	2	4	I say this that no one may deceive you by plausible arguments.
B051C002V005	51	2	5	For even though I am absent in the flesh, yet in the spirit I am with you, rejoicing to see your good order and the firmness of your faith in Christ.
B051C002V006	51	2	6	Since, then, you have received Christ Jesus as Lord, live in him,
B051C002V007	51	2	7	rooted and built up in him, growing strong in the faith as you have been taught, and overflowing with thanksgiving.
B051C002V008	51	2	8	Beware that no one carries you away captive by his philosophy and empty deceit according to the tradition of men, according to the elementary teachings of the world and not according to Christ.
B051C002V009	51	2	9	For in him dwells all the fullness of God in bodily form,
B051C002V010	51	2	10	and you have been filled in him. He is the head of every archangel and authority.
B051C002V011	51	2	11	In him you were circumcised with a circumcision not done by hands, by laying aside your fleshly body in the circumcision of Christ.
B051C002V012	51	2	12	You were buried with him in baptism and raised again through faith in the inworking of God who raised him from the dead.
B051C002V013	51	2	13	You who were dead in your sins and in the uncircumcision of your flesh God has made alive with him, and has forgiven us all our sins.
B051C002V014	51	2	14	He erased the writing that was against us in the rules, the writing that was opposed to us. He has taken it out of the way by nailing it to his cross.
B051C002V015	51	2	15	He despoiled the archangels and authorities and fearlessly made an example of them when he triumphed over them on the cross.
B051C002V016	51	2	16	Let no one then judge you in the matter of food or drink or in regard to a festival or new moon or Sabbath.
B051C002V017	51	2	17	These were a shadow of coming things, but the body is Christ's.
B051C002V018	51	2	18	Let no one as umpire defraud you of your prize, if he delights in excessive humility and ceremonial worship of the angels, searching into his own visions, emptily puffed up by his fleshly mind
B051C002V019	51	2	19	and not holding to the Head, from whom the whole body, supplied and held together by joints and bands, grows as God gives it growth.
B051C002V020	51	2	20	If you died with Christ to the elementary teachings of the world, why do you, as if still living in the world, have such rules as,
B051C002V021	51	2	21	"Do not touch," "Do not taste," "Do not handle"
B051C002V022	51	2	22	referring to things that perish when used?
B051C002V023	51	2	23	These rules follow the commandments and teachings of men. They have an appearance of wisdom in self-imposed ceremonial and excessive humility and severity to the body, but have no value against the indulgence of the flesh.
B051C003V001	51	3	1	IF then you have been raised with Christ, seek the things above, where Christ is sitting at the right hand of God.
B051C003V002	51	3	2	Have your minds on the things above and not on the things on the earth.
B051C003V003	51	3	3	For you have died and your life is hidden with Christ in God.
B051C003V004	51	3	4	When Christ, our life, appears, then you also will appear with him in glory.
B051C003V005	51	3	5	Treat the members of your earthly bodies as dead \'97 dead to unchastity, impurity, passion, evil desire, and avarice, which is idolatry.
B051C003V006	51	3	6	On account of these things comes the wrath of God.
B051C003V007	51	3	7	To them you also were once habituated when you lived in them.
B051C003V008	51	3	8	But now you also must put away all wrath, anger, malice, abusive language. Vile talk must not be in your mouths.
B051C003V009	51	3	9	Do not lie to one another. You have stripped off the old self with his practices
B051C003V010	51	3	10	and have clothed yourselves with the new self, which is being renewed into knowledge in the image of its Creator.
B051C003V011	51	3	11	Here there is no Greek or Jew, circumcision or uncircumcision, barbarian, Scythian, slave or freeman, but Christ is all and in all.
B051C003V012	51	3	12	Put on, then, as the chosen of God, holy and beloved, sympathies, compassions, kindness, humility, gentleness, slowness to anger,
B051C003V013	51	3	13	bearing with one another and forgiving one another, if any one has a grievance against any. Just as the Lord forgave you, so must you forgive.
B051C003V014	51	3	14	Above all these, clothe yourselves with love, which is the perfect bond of union.
B051C003V015	51	3	15	Let the peace of Christ be umpire in your hearts. For this you were called into one body. And be thankful.
B051C003V016	51	3	16	The message of Christ must dwell in you richly, as you teach in all wisdom and admonish one another with psalms and hymns and spiritual songs and sing with grace in your hearts to God.
B051C003V017	51	3	17	And whatever you do in word or deed, do all in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him.
B051C003V018	51	3	18	Wives, be in subjection to your husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.
B051C003V019	51	3	19	Husbands, love your wives and do not be harsh toward them.
B051C003V020	51	3	20	Children, obey your parents in everything, for this is pleasing in the Lord.
B051C003V021	51	3	21	Fathers, do not irritate your children, for they may lose heart.
B051C003V022	51	3	22	Slaves, obey in everything your masters in the flesh, not with eye-service as men-pleasers, but in sincerity of heart, because you reverence the Lord.
B051C003V023	51	3	23	Whatever you do, do it heartily as for the Lord and not for men,
B051C003V024	51	3	24	for you know that from the Lord you will receive the reward of the inheritance. You are slaves to the Lord Christ.
B051C003V025	51	3	25	He who does wrong will be repaid for the wrong he has done, and there is no partiality.
B051C004V001	51	4	1	MASTERS, give to your slaves what is just and equal, for you know that you have a Master in heaven.
B051C004V002	51	4	2	Be earnest and constant in prayer. Be thankfully watchful in it.
B051C004V003	51	4	3	Pray along with us and for us that God may open for us a door for the message, so that I may tell the mystery of Christ for the sake of which I am in chains \'97
B051C004V004	51	4	4	so that I may make it clear, as I ought.
B051C004V005	51	4	5	Behave wisely towards outsiders, buying up the opportunity.
B051C004V006	51	4	6	Let what you say be always with grace, seasoned with salt. Know how you should answer each one.
B051C004V007	51	4	7	Tychicus, the beloved brother and faithful worker and fellow servant in the Lord, will tell you everything about me.
B051C004V008	51	4	8	I am sending him to you for this very purpose, that you may know my situation and that he may encourage your hearts.
B051C004V009	51	4	9	And with him I am sending Onesimus, the faithful and beloved brother, who is one of you. They will tell you all about affairs here.
B051C004V010	51	4	10	Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, sends his greetings, and so does Mark, the cousin of Barnabas 
B051C004V011	51	4	11	and so does Jesus who is called Justus. These alone of those who are circumcised are my fellow workers for the kingdom of God, and they have been a comfort to me.
B051C004V012	51	4	12	Epaphras, the servant of Christ Jesus, who is one of you, sends his greetings to you. He always wrestles in prayer on your behalf that you may stand mature and fully assured in all the will of God.
B051C004V013	51	4	13	I bear witness to the burden that he carries for you and for those in Laodicea and those in Hierapolis.
B051C004V014	51	4	14	Luke, the beloved physician, and Demas send you their greetings.
B051C004V015	51	4	15	Give our greeting to the brethren in Laodicea and to Nympha and the church that meets in her house.
B051C004V016	51	4	16	When this letter has been read among you, have it read in the church of the Laodiceans, and you are to read the letter that will come from Laodicea.
B051C004V017	51	4	17	Say to Archippus, See to it that you fully perform the service which you have accepted in the Lord.
B051C004V018	51	4	18	The greeting of Paul, by my own hand. Remember my chains. Grace be with you.
B052C001V001	52	1	1	PAUL and Silvanus and Timothy, to the Church of the Thessalonians in God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ: Grace to you and peace.
B052C001V002	52	1	2	We thank God always for you all when we mention you in our prayers,
B052C001V003	52	1	3	unceasingly remembering your work of faith and labor of love and patience of hope in our Lord Jesus Christ before God our Father.
B052C001V004	52	1	4	We know, brethren beloved by God, that he has chosen you
B052C001V005	52	1	5	and that our good news came to you not in word only but in power and in the Holy Spirit and in great assurance, just as you know we acted among you for your benefit.
B052C001V006	52	1	6	You became imitators of us and of the Lord, receiving the message in great affliction with joy which the Holy Spirit gave,
B052C001V007	52	1	7	so that you became a pattern for all believers in Macedonia and in Achaia.
B052C001V008	52	1	8	For the message of the Lord sounded forth from you not only in Macedonia and Achaia, but in every place your faith toward God has gone abroad, so that there is no need for us to speak a word.
B052C001V009	52	1	9	For the people themselves are telling about us, what a reception we had with you, and how you turned to God from idols, to serve the living and true God
B052C001V010	52	1	10	and to wait for his Son from heaven \'97 his Son Jesus whom he raised from the dead and who is saving us from the coming wrath.
B052C002V001	52	2	1	YOU yourselves know, brethren, what a reception we had from you, that it was not without result,
B052C002V002	52	2	2	but after we had suffered and been roughly treated, as you know, in Philippi, we made bold in our God to speak to you the good news of God with great wrestling.
B052C002V003	52	2	3	For our appeal springs not from deception, nor from impure motives, nor from cunning,
B052C002V004	52	2	4	but as we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the good news, so we speak, not as if we were pleasing men, but God, who tests our hearts.
B052C002V005	52	2	5	Nor did we ever fall into flattering talk, as you know, nor use any pretext for self-enrichment \'97 God is witness \'97
B052C002V006	52	2	6	nor did we seek glory from men, either from you or others, although we could have claimed the dignity of Christ's apostles.
B052C002V007	52	2	7	But we became gentle in the midst of you like a nursing mother cherishing her own children.
B052C002V008	52	2	8	Yearning over you so, we would gladly have imparted to you not only God's good news but our own lives as well, because you had become dear to us.
B052C002V009	52	2	9	For you remember, brethren, our toil and labor as we worked night and day so as not to burden any one of you while we proclaimed to you the good news of God.
B052C002V010	52	2	10	You are witnesses \'97 and God is witness \'97 how purely and justly and blamelessly we acted toward you who believe.
B052C002V011	52	2	11	You know that just like a father toward his own children we encouraged each one of you, and warned and conjured you
B052C002V012	52	2	12	to live lives worthy of the God who is calling you into his own kingdom and glory.
B052C002V013	52	2	13	For this reason we unceasingly give thanks to God that when you received from us the report of the message of God you accepted it not as the message of men, but, as it truly is, the message of God, which also is doing its work in you who believe.
B052C002V014	52	2	14	For you became imitators, brethren, of the churches of God that are in Judaea in Christ Jesus, because you too suffered the same things from your fellow countrymen that they did from the Jews,
B052C002V015	52	2	15	who killed both the Lord Jesus and the prophets, and drove us out and do not please God and are enemies to all men,
B052C002V016	52	2	16	trying to prevent us from speaking to the Gentiles so that they may be saved. All this goes always to fill up the measure of their sins. But God's fiercest wrath has overtaken them.
B052C002V017	52	2	17	But we, brethren, when bereft of you for a little while, out of sight not out of mind, endeavored more earnestly to see your faces, with great longing.
B052C002V018	52	2	18	For that reason we determined to come to you, yes, I, Paul, more than once: but Satan hindered us.
B052C002V019	52	2	19	For what is our hope or joy or crown to boast of before our Lord Jesus at his coming? Is it not you?
B052C002V020	52	2	20	You are our glory and joy.
B052C003V001	52	3	1	SO when we could no longer endure the anxiety, we chose to be left at Athens alone
B052C003V002	52	3	2	and sent Timothy, our brother and God's servant in the good news of Christ, to strengthen and encourage you in your faith,
B052C003V003	52	3	3	that no one might be disturbed in these trials. For you yourselves know that we are destined to this.
B052C003V004	52	3	4	For when we were with you we told you in advance, "We shall soon have trouble." And so it came to pass, as you know.
B052C003V005	52	3	5	Therefore, when I could no longer endure the anxiety, I sent to know about your faith for fear that the tempter had tempted you and our labor had gone for nothing.
B052C003V006	52	3	6	But now that Timothy has come to us from you and has brought us good news of your faith and love, and that you always keep us well in mind and long to see us, just as we long to see you,
B052C003V007	52	3	7	we have been cheered, brethren, in regard to you, in all our straits and distresses by your faith.
B052C003V008	52	3	8	Now we are living, since you are standing firm in the Lord.
B052C003V009	52	3	9	For how can we be grateful enough to God for you in view of all the joy we have because of you,
B052C003V010	52	3	10	while we pray beyond measure night and day that we may see your faces and make good whatever lacks there may be in your faith?
B052C003V011	52	3	11	May our God and Father himself and our Lord Jesus Christ open the way for us to come to you.
B052C003V012	52	3	12	The Lord make you to abound and overflow in love toward one another and toward all men, just as we do toward you,
B052C003V013	52	3	13	that your hearts may be made firm and you may be blameless in holiness before our God and Father at the coming of our Lord Jesus with all his holy ones.
B052C004V001	52	4	1	TO conclude, brethren, we beg of you and urge you in the Lord Jesus that, as you learned from us how you ought to live to please God, and are living, you will excel still more.
B052C004V002	52	4	2	For you know what directions we have given you through the Lord Jesus.
B052C004V003	52	4	3	For this is the will of God: to have you become holy and have you shun unchastity;
B052C004V004	52	4	4	to have each of you know how to take a wife for himself in holiness and honor,
B052C004V005	52	4	5	not in the passion of lust, as the Gentiles do who know not God;
B052C004V006	52	4	6	to have no one trespass or take advantage of his brother in this matter; for the Lord is the punisher of all such, as we have already told you and solemnly warned you.
B052C004V007	52	4	7	God has not called us to live in impurity, but in holiness.
B052C004V008	52	4	8	Therefore he who disregards this disregards not man, but God, who gives his Holy Spirit to you.
B052C004V009	52	4	9	Regarding brotherly love you have no need for me to write to you. For you yourselves have been taught by God to love one another,
B052C004V010	52	4	10	and you do the same to all the brethren in the whole of Macedonia. But we urge you, brethren, to excel still further
B052C004V011	52	4	11	and to be ambitious to lead a quiet life and to mind each his own business and to work with your hands, as we instructed you.
B052C004V012	52	4	12	Thus you will live becomingly in the sight of outsiders and will have need of nothing.
B052C004V013	52	4	13	We do not wish you to be ignorant, brethren, regarding those who are sleeping, that you may not sorrow as the rest of men who have no hope.
B052C004V014	52	4	14	For since, as we believe, Jesus died and rose, so too God will through Jesus bring with him those who have fallen asleep.
B052C004V015	52	4	15	This we tell you by the word of the Lord: We, the living, who have been left until the coming of the Lord, will not have the start of those who have fallen asleep.
B052C004V016	52	4	16	For the Lord himself will descend from heaven with a shout, with the voice of an archangel and with God's trumpet-call, and first the dead in Christ will rise.
B052C004V017	52	4	17	Then we, the living, who are left, will be caught up along with them into the clouds to meet the Lord in the air. And thus we shall forever be with the Lord.
B052C004V018	52	4	18	So encourage one another with these words.
B052C005V001	52	5	1	BUT regarding times and dates, brethren, you do not need to have me write to you.
B052C005V002	52	5	2	For you yourselves know perfectly that the day of the Lord will come like a thief in the night.
B052C005V003	52	5	3	When they are saying, "Peace and safety," then sudden destruction is upon them, like the pangs upon a woman with child, and they will not escape.
B052C005V004	52	5	4	But you, brethren, are not in darkness so that the day can take you like a thief.
B052C005V005	52	5	5	You are all sons of light and sons of day. We do not belong to night or to darkness.
B052C005V006	52	5	6	Then let us not be sleeping like the rest of men, but let us watch and be sober.
B052C005V007	52	5	7	For those who sleep sleep in the night and those who drink drink in the night.
B052C005V008	52	5	8	But let us who are of the day be sober. Let us put on the breastplate of faith and love and for a helmet the hope of salvation.
B052C005V009	52	5	9	For God has not destined us to wrath, but to the winning of salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ,
B052C005V010	52	5	10	who died for us that whether we are waking or sleeping we may live in company with him.
B052C005V011	52	5	11	Therefore encourage one another and build up one another, as indeed you are doing.
B052C005V012	52	5	12	We beg you, brethren, to regard those who are laboring among you and who preside over you in the Lord and give you counsel,
B052C005V013	52	5	13	and to esteem them very highly in love on account of their work. Be at peace among yourselves.
B052C005V014	52	5	14	We urge you, brethren, to warn the disorderly, encourage the faint-hearted, help the weak, be patient with all.
B052C005V015	52	5	15	Take care that no one repays evil with evil, but always seek eagerly what is good in dealing with one another and with every one.
B052C005V016	52	5	16	Always be joyful.
B052C005V017	52	5	17	Pray without ceasing.
B052C005V018	52	5	18	In everything give thanks, for this is God's will in Christ for you.
B052C005V019	52	5	19	Do not quench the Spirit.
B052C005V020	52	5	20	Do not despise prophecies.
B052C005V021	52	5	21	Test all things; hold fast the good.
B052C005V022	52	5	22	Avoid every kind of evil.
B052C005V023	52	5	23	May the God of peace himself make you completely holy, and may your spirits and souls and bodies be kept faultless and blameless for the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B052C005V024	52	5	24	He is faithful who calls you and he will do it.
B052C005V025	52	5	25	Brethren, pray for us.
B052C005V026	52	5	26	Greet all the brethren with a holy kiss.
B052C005V027	52	5	27	I solemnly charge you in the Lord's name to have this letter read to all the brethren.
B052C005V028	52	5	28	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B053C001V001	53	1	1	PAUL and Silvanus and Timothy to the Church of the Thessalonians in God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ:
B053C001V002	53	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V003	53	1	3	We ought always to thank God for you, brethren, as is fitting, since your faith is growing greatly and the love of each and all of you toward one another is increasing,
B053C001V004	53	1	4	so that we ourselves glory in you among the churches of God because of your endurance and faith in all of your persecutions and in the distresses you are bearing.
B053C001V005	53	1	5	This is a proof of God's righteous judgment. It is to make you worthy of God's kingdom, on behalf of which you are suffering,
B053C001V006	53	1	6	since it is just on God's part to repay with trouble those who are troubling you,
B053C001V007	53	1	7	and to repay to you, who are being troubled, rest with us at the revelation of the Lord Jesus from heaven with his mighty angels.
B053C001V008	53	1	8	With flaming fire he will inflict vengeance on those who do not know God and do not obey the good news of our Lord Jesus.
B053C001V009	53	1	9	They will suffer the penalty of eternal destruction and be sent away from the face of the Lord and from his glorious power,
B053C001V010	53	1	10	when he comes to be glorified among his holy ones and to be wondered at on that day among all believers \'97 for our testimony to you was believed.
B053C001V011	53	1	11	To this end we are always praying for you that our God will make you worthy of the call, and will by his power bring to completion every one of your kind purposes and works of faith,
B053C001V012	53	1	12	that the name of our Lord Jesus may be glorified in you, according to the grace of our God and of the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V001	53	2	1	WITH regard to the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ and our being gathered to meet him, I beg you, brethren,
B053C002V002	53	2	2	not to be quickly unsettled in mind nor excited by either a revelation or by a message or a letter supposed to be from us, to the effect that the day of the Lord is close at hand.
B053C002V003	53	2	3	Let no one lead you astray in any way, because it will not come until the Apostasy has first come and the Man of Lawlessness has been revealed \'97 the Son of Perdition,
B053C002V004	53	2	4	who opposes and exalts himself above everything called God and every object of worship, so that he enters the Temple of God and seats himself there, declaring that he himself is God.
B053C002V005	53	2	5	Do you not remember that while I was still with you I used to tell you this?
B053C002V006	53	2	6	And now you know what is restraining him until he is revealed at his appointed time.
B053C002V007	53	2	7	For the mystery of lawlessness is already working, only there is just now one who is restraining it until he passes out of the way.
B053C002V008	53	2	8	And then the Lawless One will be revealed. But the Lord Jesus will sweep him away with the breath of his mouth and will make him powerless by the splendor of his coming.
B053C002V009	53	2	9	For his coming will be when Satan is active in every sort of power and in false signs and wonders
B053C002V010	53	2	10	and in every kind of wicked deception of those who are perishing, because they did not receive the love of the truth so that they might be saved.
B053C002V011	53	2	11	For this reason God sends to them a deceptive influence so that they believe a lie,
B053C002V012	53	2	12	that all who have not believed the truth but have delighted in wickedness may be condemned.
B053C002V013	53	2	13	We ought always to thank God for you, brethren, beloved by the Lord, because God chose you from the beginning for salvation through the Spirit's making you holy and your own faith in the truth.
B053C002V014	53	2	14	To this he called you through the good news that we brought, so that you may share the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V015	53	2	15	Now then, brethren, stand firm and hold fast the teachings that you have been taught whether by our words or by our letter.
B053C002V016	53	2	16	May our Lord Jesus Christ himself and God our Father, who loved us and gave us eternal encouragement and good hope through grace,
B053C002V017	53	2	17	encourage your hearts and make you strong in every good word and work.
B053C003V001	53	3	1	IN conclusion, brethren, pray for us, that the Lord's message may run and be glorified, as among you,
B053C003V002	53	3	2	and that we may be saved from the unreasonable and wicked men, for faith does not belong to all.
B053C003V003	53	3	3	But the Lord is faithful and he will strengthen you and guard you from evil.
B053C003V004	53	3	4	We are persuaded in the Lord in regard to you that you are doing and will do what we direct.
B053C003V005	53	3	5	The Lord guide your hearts in the love of God and the patience of Christ.
B053C003V006	53	3	6	We charge you, brethren, in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ, to stand aloof from every brother who is living in a disorderly way and not according to the teaching that you received from us.
B053C003V007	53	3	7	For you yourselves know that you should imitate us, for we were not disorderly when among you,
B053C003V008	53	3	8	nor did we eat bread with any one without paying, but with labor and toil night and day we worked in order not to burden any one of you.
B053C003V009	53	3	9	Not that we have not the authority, but in order to give you ourselves as an example for you to imitate.
B053C003V010	53	3	10	For when we were with you we gave you this command, "If any one will not work, neither is he to eat."
B053C003V011	53	3	11	For we hear that some among you are leading disorderly lives, busy about nothing and yet busybodies.
B053C003V012	53	3	12	Such we command and urge in the Lord Jesus Christ to work quietly and eat their own bread.
B053C003V013	53	3	13	But you, brethren, must not become discouraged in doing well.
B053C003V014	53	3	14	If any one does not obey our words in this letter, mark that man and do not associate with him, so that he may be ashamed.
B053C003V015	53	3	15	Yet do not regard him as an enemy, but warn him as a brother.
B053C003V016	53	3	16	The Lord of peace himself give you peace at all times in all ways. The Lord be with you all.
B053C003V017	53	3	17	The greeting of Paul by my own hand, which is the sign in every letter. This is my handwriting.
B053C003V018	53	3	18	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with all of you.
B054C001V001	54	1	1	PAUL, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the appointment of God, our Savior, and Christ Jesus our hope,
B054C001V002	54	1	2	to Timothy my true child in faith: Grace, mercy and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B054C001V003	54	1	3	As I begged you to stay in Ephesus when I was leaving for Macedonia, that you might charge some not to teach new and strange doctrines
B054C001V004	54	1	4	nor give attention to myths and endless genealogies, which promote disputes rather than God's plan in the faith, so I beg you now.
B054C001V005	54	1	5	The aim of the commandment is love out of a pure heart and a good conscience and a sincere faith.
B054C001V006	54	1	6	Some missing these have turned aside to empty talk,
B054C001V007	54	1	7	wishing to be teachers of the Law, but not understanding either what they are saying or what the things are that they are so positive about.
B054C001V008	54	1	8	We know that the Law is excellent, if any one uses it lawfully.
B054C001V009	54	1	9	But we know this: that law is not laid down for a righteous man, but for the lawless and the insubordinate, the ungodly and sinners, the unholy and profane, for murderers of fathers and murderers of mothers, for manslayers,
B054C001V010	54	1	10	for the unchaste, for those who practice unnatural vices, for slave-dealers, liars, perjurers, and for whatever else is contrary to wholesome teaching
B054C001V011	54	1	11	such as accords with the glorious good news of the blessed God, with which I have been entrusted.
B054C001V012	54	1	12	I thank Christ Jesus our Lord who has given me strength, because he thought me faithful and put me into his service,
B054C001V013	54	1	13	though before that I spoke profanely and was a persecutor and insolent in outrages. But I received mercy because I did it ignorantly in unbelief.
B054C001V014	54	1	14	And the grace of our Lord overflowed in me with faith and love in Christ Jesus.
B054C001V015	54	1	15	The saying is trust-worthy and deserving of full acceptance that "Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners," of whom I am the foremost.
B054C001V016	54	1	16	But I received mercy for this reason, that in me, as the foremost, Jesus Christ might show all of his long-suffering for an example for those who are to believe in him and gain life eternal.
B054C001V017	54	1	17	To the King of the ages, the immortal, invisible, only God, be honor and glory for the ages of the ages! Amen.
B054C001V018	54	1	18	This command I lay down for you, my child Timothy, in accordance with the prophecies that came in advance regarding you, in order that armed with them you may wage the noble war,
B054C001V019	54	1	19	holding to faith and a good conscience, which some have cast aside and thus made shipwreck of their faith.
B054C001V020	54	1	20	Among these are Hymenaeus and Alexander, whom I have handed over to Satan, that they may learn not to speak profanely.
B054C002V001	54	2	1	I BEG, then, first of all, that petitions, prayers, supplications, and thanksgivings be made in behalf of all men,
B054C002V002	54	2	2	in behalf of kings and all who are in authority, that we may lead a quiet and peaceful life in all piety and sobriety.
B054C002V003	54	2	3	This is excellent and pleasing in the sight of God, our Savior,
B054C002V004	54	2	4	who wishes all men to be saved and to come to the knowledge of the truth.
B054C002V005	54	2	5	For there is one God and one Mediator between God and men, himself man, Christ Jesus,
B054C002V006	54	2	6	who gave himself as a ransom for all, a fact to be witnessed to at the fitting time.
B054C002V007	54	2	7	To this I was appointed a herald and an apostle \'97 I am telling the truth, I am not lying \'97 a teacher of Gentiles in faith and truth.
B054C002V008	54	2	8	I wish, then, that the men offer prayer in every place, lifting up holy hands without wrath or debate.
B054C002V009	54	2	9	Also that the women adorn themselves in becoming dress modestly and discreetly, not with braided hair or gold or pearls or costly clothes,
B054C002V010	54	2	10	but \'97 as is becoming for women professing piety \'97 with good deeds.
B054C002V011	54	2	11	A woman is to learn in all subjection.
B054C002V012	54	2	12	I do not permit a woman to teach or to usurp authority over a man, but she must remain silent.
B054C002V013	54	2	13	Adam was first formed, then Eve.
B054C002V014	54	2	14	And Adam was not deceived; the woman was deceived and fell into sin.
B054C002V015	54	2	15	But they will be saved through child-bearing, if they continue in faith and love and holiness with self-control.
B054C003V001	54	3	1	THE saying is trustworthy: "If any one aspires to the office of a bishop, he desires a noble work."
B054C003V002	54	3	2	A bishop, then, should be above reproach, true to one woman, temperate, self-controlled, dignified, hospitable, with a gift for teaching,
B054C003V003	54	3	3	not given to wine or to blows, but fair-minded, averse to strife, not a lover of money,
B054C003V004	54	3	4	presiding well over his own house, with children obedient and respectful.
B054C003V005	54	3	5	But if any one does not know how to preside over his own house, how will he take care of the church of God?
B054C003V006	54	3	6	He must not be a new convert, for fear he may be blinded by pride and fall into the condemnation of the Devil.
B054C003V007	54	3	7	He must have a good reputation with outsiders so as not to fall into reproach and the snare of the Devil.
B054C003V008	54	3	8	Deacons, in the same way, must be dignified, not double-tongued, not given to much wine, not eager for base gain,
B054C003V009	54	3	9	holding the mystery of the faith with a pure conscience.
B054C003V010	54	3	10	They must first be tested, and then let them fill the office of deacon if there is nothing against them.
B054C003V011	54	3	11	Women, in the same way, must be dignified, not slanderers, temperate, trustworthy in everything.
B054C003V012	54	3	12	Deacons must be men true to one woman, presiding well over their children and their own houses.
B054C003V013	54	3	13	Those who have filled the office of deacon well win for themselves a high standing and great boldness in the faith in Christ Jesus.
B054C003V014	54	3	14	I am writing these things to you, although I hope to come to you soon,
B054C003V015	54	3	15	but so that if I am delayed you may know how people should conduct themselves in the household of God, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and base of the truth.
B054C003V016	54	3	16	Confessedly great is the mystery of godliness: "Who was manifested in flesh, declared righteous in spirit, seen by angels, proclaimed among Gentiles, believed on in the world, received up in glory."
B054C004V001	54	4	1	THE Spirit says distinctly that in later times some will desert from the faith, giving attention to deceiving spirits and teachings of demons,
B054C004V002	54	4	2	through the hypocrisy of men who teach falsely, branded in their own consciences,
B054C004V003	54	4	3	forbidding marriage, and insisting on abstinence from certain kinds of food which God made to be partaken of with thanksgiving by those who are faithful and know the truth.
B054C004V004	54	4	4	For everything made by God is excellent and nothing is to be rejected if taken with thanksgiving.
B054C004V005	54	4	5	For it is made holy through God's message and through prayer.
B054C004V006	54	4	6	In teaching this to the brethren you will be a noble servant of Christ Jesus, nourished by the words of the faith and of the excellent teaching which you have followed.
B054C004V007	54	4	7	But avoid profane and old-womanish myths. Exercise yourself in godliness.
B054C004V008	54	4	8	Bodily exercise is useful to a small degree, but godliness is useful for everything. "It has the promise of the present life and of the life that is to come."
B054C004V009	54	4	9	This saying is trustworthy and deserving of full acceptance.
B054C004V010	54	4	10	For to this end we are laboring and wrestling, because we have set our hope on the living God, who is the Savior of all men, especially of believers.
B054C004V011	54	4	11	Command and teach these things.
B054C004V012	54	4	12	Let no one look down on you because you are young, but be an example to believers in speech, in the life you lead, in love, in faith, in purity.
B054C004V013	54	4	13	Until I come give attention to reading, to exhortation, to teaching.
B054C004V014	54	4	14	Do not neglect the gift that is in you, which was given to you through prophecy with the laying on of the hands of the eldership.
B054C004V015	54	4	15	Be careful about these things, be fully occupied with them, that your progress may be plain to all.
B054C004V016	54	4	16	Be thoughtful about yourself and your teaching. Persevere in this; for in doing so you will save yourself and those who hear you.
B054C005V001	54	5	1	Do not rebuke an older man, but entreat him as a father, the younger men as brothers,
B054C005V002	54	5	2	the older women as mothers and the younger women as sisters, in all purity.
B054C005V003	54	5	3	Honor widows if they are really widows.
B054C005V004	54	5	4	If any widow has children or grandchildren, let them learn first to act piously toward their own family and to repay what they owe to their parents and grandparents. For this is pleasing in the sight of God.
B054C005V005	54	5	5	A real widow who is left alone has set her hope on God and devotes herself to prayers and supplications night and day.
B054C005V006	54	5	6	But the pleasure-loving widow, though living, is already dead.
B054C005V007	54	5	7	Give these commands that they may be free from reproach.
B054C005V008	54	5	8	If any one does not provide for his own, and especially those of his own household, he has disowned the faith and is worse than an unbeliever.
B054C005V009	54	5	9	A widow is to be put on the list if she has reached the age of not less than sixty years, if she has been true to one husband,
B054C005V010	54	5	10	has a reputation for good deeds, has brought up children, has entertained strangers, has washed the feet of the holy, has ministered to people in distress, has been active in every good work.
B054C005V011	54	5	11	But younger widows refuse, for when wanton desires lead them away from Christ they wish to marry
B054C005V012	54	5	12	and thus they incur condemnation for breaking their first promise.
B054C005V013	54	5	13	At the same time they learn to be idle, going around from house to house, and not only idle, but gossips, and busybodies, saying what they should not.
B054C005V014	54	5	14	I would, therefore, have the younger widows marry, bear children, keep house, give no occasion to our enemies for slander.
B054C005V015	54	5	15	For already some have turned aside after Satan.
B054C005V016	54	5	16	If any woman who is a believer has widows, she must provide for them and the church must not be burdened, so that it may provide for those who are really widows.
B054C005V017	54	5	17	The elders who preside well should be thought worthy of double salary, especially those who labor in speaking and teaching.
B054C005V018	54	5	18	For the Scripture says, "You shall not muzzle the ox while he is treading out the grain," and 
B054C005V019	54	5	19	Against an elder do not receive an accusation unless on the testimony of two or three witnesses.
B054C005V020	54	5	20	Those who are going on in sin rebuke before all, that the rest may fear.
B054C005V021	54	5	21	I charge you before God and Christ Jesus and the chosen angels to observe these directions without prejudice, doing nothing through partiality.
B054C005V022	54	5	22	Do not lay hands of ordination upon any one hastily. Have no share in the sins of other men. Keep yourself pure.
B054C005V023	54	5	23	Do not keep on being a water-drinker, but use a little wine for the sake of your stomach and because of your frequent ailments.
B054C005V024	54	5	24	Some men's sins are conspicuous and go on before to condemnation, but the sins of some men follow after them.
B054C005V025	54	5	25	Just so noble deeds are conspicuous and those that are otherwise cannot be hid.
B054C006V001	54	6	1	ALL who are slaves under the yoke must regard their own masters as worthy of all honor, so that the name of God and the teaching may not be profanely slandered.
B054C006V002	54	6	2	Those who have believing masters must not despise them because they are brothers, but rather work as slaves for them because those who are benefited by their good work are believers and beloved. Teach and urge these things.
B054C006V003	54	6	3	If any one teaches otherwise and does not agree to wholesome words, those of our Lord Jesus Christ, and to religious teaching,
B054C006V004	54	6	4	he is conceited, knowing nothing, but morbidly fond of disputes and controversies from which come envy, strife, abusive language, wicked suspicions,
B054C006V005	54	6	5	and wranglings of men of depraved minds who are destitute of the truth. They think of religion as a source of gain.
B054C006V006	54	6	6	Religion with contentment is a great source of gain.
B054C006V007	54	6	7	For we brought nothing into the world and we cannot carry anything out.
B054C006V008	54	6	8	If we have food and clothing we will be content with these.
B054C006V009	54	6	9	But those who are determined to be rich fall into temptation and a snare and many foolish and injurious passions which plunge men into destruction and ruin.
B054C006V010	54	6	10	For the love of money is a root of all kinds of evil. Some men grasping for it have strayed from the faith and have pierced themselves with many pangs.
B054C006V011	54	6	11	But you, O man of God, must shun this. Pursue righteousness, piety, faith, love, endurance, gentleness.
B054C006V012	54	6	12	Play the grand hard game of the faith. Lay hold on life eternal, to which you have been called and have made the noble confession before many witnesses.
B054C006V013	54	6	13	I charge you in the presence of God who gives life to all, and Christ Jesus who before Pontius Pilate made the noble confession,
B054C006V014	54	6	14	to keep the commandment stainless and free from reproach until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B054C006V015	54	6	15	which in due time he will show, who is the blessed and only Potentate, the King of kings and Lord of lords,
B054C006V016	54	6	16	who alone has immortality, who dwells in light unapproachable, whom no man has seen or can see. To him be honor and power eternal! Amen.
B054C006V017	54	6	17	Command those who are rich in this world not to be haughty nor to fix their hope on uncertain wealth, but on God who provides all things richly for our enjoyment.
B054C006V018	54	6	18	They must do good work, be rich in noble deeds, be generous, ready to share,
B054C006V019	54	6	19	treasuring up for themselves a good fund for the future, that they may lay hold on the life that is real.
B054C006V020	54	6	20	O Timothy, guard what has been entrusted to you, turning away from profane and empty talk and contradictions of what is falsely called "knowledge."
B054C006V021	54	6	21	Some while professing it have gone astray as regards the faith. Grace be with you all.
B055C001V001	55	1	1	PAUL, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God according to the promise of life in Christ Jesus,
B055C001V002	55	1	2	to Timothy my beloved child: Grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and from Christ Jesus our Lord.
B055C001V003	55	1	3	I thank God whom, I serve, following in the steps of my forefathers, with a pure conscience, while I constantly mention you in my prayers night and day,
B055C001V004	55	1	4	remembering your tears and longing to see you, that I may be filled with joy.
B055C001V005	55	1	5	I remember the sincere faith that is in you, which lived first in your grandmother Lois and then in your mother Eunice, and I am confident that it lives in you also.
B055C001V006	55	1	6	For this reason let me remind you to kindle anew the gift of God that is in you by the laying on of my hands.
B055C001V007	55	1	7	For God has not given us a spirit of fear, but of power and love and self-control.
B055C001V008	55	1	8	Do not be ashamed to testify for our Lord or for me his prisoner, but join in suffering hardships for the good news as God gives power.
B055C001V009	55	1	9	It is he who saved us and called us with a holy calling, not according to our deeds but according to his own purpose and grace, given to us in Christ Jesus ages ago
B055C001V010	55	1	10	but now manifested by the appearance of our Savior Christ Jesus, who has defeated death and brought to light life and immortality by the good news.
B055C001V011	55	1	11	For this I was made a herald and an apostle and a teacher,
B055C001V012	55	1	12	and for this reason I am suffering these things. But I am not ashamed, for I know in whom I have put my faith, and am confident that he is able to guard what I have entrusted to him until that day.
B055C001V013	55	1	13	Hold to the example of wholesome words which you heard from me in faith and love in Christ Jesus.
B055C001V014	55	1	14	Guard through the Holy Spirit which dwells in us the precious trust committed to you.
B055C001V015	55	1	15	You know that all of those in Asia have deserted me. Among them are Phygelus and Hermogenes.
B055C001V016	55	1	16	The Lord grant mercy to the family of Onesiphorus, for he often cheered me and was not ashamed of my chain;
B055C001V017	55	1	17	but when he came to Rome he looked me up eagerly and found me.
B055C001V018	55	1	18	The Lord grant to him to find mercy from the Lord on that day! And in how many ways he served me in Ephesus you know better still.
B055C002V001	55	2	1	YOU, therefore, my child, must be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus,
B055C002V002	55	2	2	and the things you heard from me, which came through many witnesses, you must commit to trustworthy men who will be able to teach others also.
B055C002V003	55	2	3	Take your share of hardship as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.
B055C002V004	55	2	4	No one while serving as a soldier entangles himself in the affairs of life, for the soldier must please him who enlisted him.
B055C002V005	55	2	5	And if any one enters an athletic contest, he is not crowned unless he competes according to the rules.
B055C002V006	55	2	6	The farmer who does the labor ought first to have his share of the fruits.
B055C002V007	55	2	7	Think over what I am saying, for the Lord will give you insight in all things.
B055C002V008	55	2	8	Remember Jesus Christ, raised from the dead, a descendant of David, as my good news teaches.
B055C002V009	55	2	9	In telling it I am suffering hardships even to chains, as if I were an evildoer, but God's message is not chained.
B055C002V010	55	2	10	For this reason I am enduring all for the sake of the chosen, that they may gain the salvation that is in Christ Jesus with eternal glory.
B055C002V011	55	2	11	Trustworthy is the saying, "For if we have died with him we shall also live with him;
B055C002V012	55	2	12	if we endure we shall also be kings with him; if we disown him, he will disown us;
B055C002V013	55	2	13	if we are faithless, he remains faithful; for he cannot disown himself."
B055C002V014	55	2	14	Remind them of these things, charging them before God not to engage in controversy to no profit, but to the ruin of the hearers.
B055C002V015	55	2	15	Be earnest in presenting yourself to God as a tested man, a workman who has no cause to be ashamed, rightly handling the message of truth.
B055C002V016	55	2	16	But shun profane and empty talk. It will grow into greater impiety,
B055C002V017	55	2	17	and its teachings will spread like a gangrene. Hymenaeus and Philetus are of this sort.
B055C002V018	55	2	18	They have gone astray as to the truth, saying that the resurrection has already taken place, and they are overthrowing the faith of some.
B055C002V019	55	2	19	However, God's solid foundation stands, with this inscription, "The Lord knows his own," and, "Let every one who names the Lord's name turn from wickedness."
B055C002V020	55	2	20	In a great house there are not only utensils of gold and silver, but also of wood and earthenware, and some are for honorable and others for dishonorable uses.
B055C002V021	55	2	21	If any one keeps himself pure from these errors, he will be ready for honorable use, holy, fit for the master's service, prepared for every good work.
B055C002V022	55	2	22	But flee the passions of youth and pursue righteousness, faith, love, peace, in the company of those who call on the Lord out of a pure heart.
B055C002V023	55	2	23	Avoid foolish disputes of the uneducated, knowing that they give rise to quarrels,
B055C002V024	55	2	24	and the servant of the Lord must not quarrel, but be courteous to all, skillful in teaching, forbearing,
B055C002V025	55	2	25	instructing opponents with gentleness, for God may give them a change of heart which will lead them to knowledge of the truth,
B055C002V026	55	2	26	and they may return to soberness and escape the snare of the Devil when captured by the Lord's servant to do the Lord's will.
B055C003V001	55	3	1	I WOULD have you know this, that in the last days trying times will come;
B055C003V002	55	3	2	for people will be lovers of self, lovers of money, boasters, haughty, abusive, disobedient to parents, ungrateful, profane,
B055C003V003	55	3	3	without family affection, relentless, slanderers, without self-control, brutal, haters of good,
B055C003V004	55	3	4	treacherous, reckless, conceited, lovers of pleasure rather than lovers of God.
B055C003V005	55	3	5	They will have a form of religion, but will cast off its power. Avoid such people.
B055C003V006	55	3	6	For of this class are those who make their way into houses and take captive weak women loaded with sins, led by varying passions,
B055C003V007	55	3	7	always learning and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth.
B055C003V008	55	3	8	Just as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so these men oppose the truth, depraved in mind, proved to be worthless as regards the faith.
B055C003V009	55	3	9	But they will go no further, for their folly will be manifest to all as that of Jannes and Jambres became.
B055C003V010	55	3	10	But you have kept track of my teaching, my course of life, my purpose, my faith, my slowness to anger, my love, my patience,
B055C003V011	55	3	11	my persecutions, my sufferings \'97 what happened to me at Antioch, Iconium, Lystra, what persecutions I underwent. But the Lord delivered me out of all of them.
B055C003V012	55	3	12	And all who are determined to live religiously in Christ Jesus will be persecuted.
B055C003V013	55	3	13	Wicked men and impostors will go on from bad to worse, deceiving and being deceived.
B055C003V014	55	3	14	But you must stand by what you learned and were persuaded of, knowing from whom you learned it
B055C003V015	55	3	15	and that from childhood you have known the sacred writings which can give you wisdom to gain salvation through faith in Christ Jesus.
B055C003V016	55	3	16	All Scripture is divinely inspired and is useful for teaching, for proof, for correction of error, for education in righteousness,
B055C003V017	55	3	17	that the man of God may be complete, equipped for every good work.
B055C004V001	55	4	1	I CHARGE you before God and Christ Jesus, who will soon judge the living and the dead, and by his appearing and his kingdom:
B055C004V002	55	4	2	proclaim the message, be at it in season and out of season, convince, rebuke, encourage, with all patience in teaching.
B055C004V003	55	4	3	For there will be a time when they will not endure wholesome teaching, but following their own fancies and wishing to have their ears tickled, they will get a crowd of teachers.
B055C004V004	55	4	4	They will turn their ears away from the truth and give attention to myths.
B055C004V005	55	4	5	But you must be calm in all circumstances, suffer hardships, do the work of a bringer of the good news, carry out fully all the duties of your office.
B055C004V006	55	4	6	For I am already being poured out like a drink offering, and the time of my departure is near.
B055C004V007	55	4	7	I have played the grand hard game, I have finished my race, I have kept the faith.
B055C004V008	55	4	8	Now the crown of righteousness is awaiting me. The Lord the righteous judge will give it to me on that day, and not only to me but to all those who have loved his appearing.
B055C004V009	55	4	9	Make haste to come to me quickly.
B055C004V010	55	4	10	For Demas deserted me because he loved the present world and has gone to Thessalonica. Crescens has gone to Galatia, Titus to Dalmatia.
B055C004V011	55	4	11	Luke alone is with me. Get Mark and bring him with you, for he is useful to me in service.
B055C004V012	55	4	12	I sent Tychicus to Ephesus.
B055C004V013	55	4	13	When you come, bring the cloak that I left at Troas with Carpus, and the books, and particularly the parchments.
B055C004V014	55	4	14	Alexander the coppersmith showed much ill will toward me. The Lord will repay him according to his deeds.
B055C004V015	55	4	15	Be on your guard against him, for he strongly opposed our teachings.
B055C004V016	55	4	16	At my first defense no one came to my help; all deserted me. May it not be laid up against them!
B055C004V017	55	4	17	But the Lord stood by me and strengthened me so that through me the proclamation might be fully published and all the Gentiles might hear it, and I was saved from the mouth of the lion.
B055C004V018	55	4	18	The Lord will rescue me from every wicked attack and will keep me safe for his heavenly kingdom. To him be glory for the ages of the ages! Amen.
B055C004V019	55	4	19	Give my greetings to Prises and Aquila and the household of Onesiphorus.
B055C004V020	55	4	20	Erastus stayed at Corinth. Trophimus I left at Miletus, sick.
B055C004V021	55	4	21	Try to come before winter. Eubulus and Pudens and Linus and Claudia and all the brethren send their greetings to you.
B055C004V022	55	4	22	The Lord be with your spirit. Grace be with you all.
B056C001V001	56	1	1	PAUL, a servant of God and an apostle of Jesus Christ to promote the faith of God's chosen and their knowledge of the truths of religion,
B056C001V002	56	1	2	in hope of life eternal, which the God who never lies promised ages ago
B056C001V003	56	1	3	but in due time made known as his message through the proclamation with which I was entrusted by the commission of God our Savior,
B056C001V004	56	1	4	to Titus my true child in our common faith: Grace and peace from God the Father, and from Christ Jesus, our Savior.
B056C001V005	56	1	5	For this reason I left you in Crete: to arrange the things that are lacking and appoint elders in every city as I directed you,
B056C001V006	56	1	6	wherever there is a man of irreproachable character, true to one woman, with believing children who are not charged with dissolute conduct and not unruly.
B056C001V007	56	1	7	For a bishop, as God's steward, must be above reproach, not self-willed, not quick-tempered, not given to wine, not given to blows, not eager for base gain,
B056C001V008	56	1	8	but hospitable, a lover of good, self-controlled, just, holy, temperate,
B056C001V009	56	1	9	holding to the trustworthy message which is according to the teaching, so that he may be able also to encourage others by wholesome teaching and to refute opposers.
B056C001V010	56	1	10	For there are many insubordinate persons, foolish talkers and deceivers, especially those who are of the circumcision,
B056C001V011	56	1	11	who ought to be silenced, for they are upsetting whole house-holds, teaching what they should not, merely for the sake of base gain.
B056C001V012	56	1	12	One of themselves, a prophet of their own, said, "Cretans are always liars, base brutes, lazy gluttons."
B056C001V013	56	1	13	This testimony is true. For this reason rebuke them sharply, that they may be sound in the faith,
B056C001V014	56	1	14	not giving attention to Jewish myths and rules laid down by men who are turning away from the truth.
B056C001V015	56	1	15	To the pure all things are pure; but to the polluted and unbelieving nothing is pure. Even their minds and consciences are polluted.
B056C001V016	56	1	16	They profess to know God, but by their deeds they disown him. They are detestable, disobedient, and worthless for any good work.
B056C002V001	56	2	1	YOU must speak to them of the matters which should have a place in wholesome teaching.
B056C002V002	56	2	2	Tell the older men to be temperate, dignified, self-controlled, sound in faith, in love, in patience.
B056C002V003	56	2	3	Tell the older women, in the same way, to be reverent in behavior, not slanderers, not enslaved to much wine, teachers of what is noble,
B056C002V004	56	2	4	that they may train the young women to be loving wives and loving mothers,
B056C002V005	56	2	5	self-controlled, pure, home-workers, kind, submissive to their own husbands, that God's message may not be slandered.
B056C002V006	56	2	6	Urge the younger men, in the same way, to practice self-control in everything.
B056C002V007	56	2	7	Make yourself an example of good works, sincerity in teaching, dignified behavior
B056C002V008	56	2	8	and wholesome talk that is above censure, that our opponents may be ashamed, having nothing evil to say about us.
B056C002V009	56	2	9	Tell slaves to be submissive to their own masters in all things and to try to please them, not answering back,
B056C002V010	56	2	10	not pilfering, but showing all kindly fidelity, so as to make the teaching about God our Savior seem beautiful in all respects.
B056C002V011	56	2	11	For the grace of God has appeared bringing salvation to all men,
B056C002V012	56	2	12	teaching us to renounce all irreligion and worldly passions and to live soberly, justly and piously in this present world,
B056C002V013	56	2	13	waiting for the blessed hope, the glorious appearing of the great God and of our Savior Christ Jesus,
B056C002V014	56	2	14	who gave himself for us to redeem us from all sin and purify us as his own people earnest in honorable work.
B056C002V015	56	2	15	Tell them these things, urge, convince with all authority; let no one slight you.
B056C003V001	56	3	1	REMIND them to be submissive to ruling authorities, to be obedient, to be ready for every good work,
B056C003V002	56	3	2	to speak abusively to no one, to be peaceable, to be fair, showing all gentleness toward all men.
B056C003V003	56	3	3	For we ourselves were once thoughtless, disobedient, astray, enslaved to passions and various pleasures, living in malice and envy, hateful and hating one another.
B056C003V004	56	3	4	But when the kindness of our Savior, God, and his love to men appeared,
B056C003V005	56	3	5	"not because of works that we had done in righteousness, but out of his own mercy he saved us through the bath of the new birth and the renewing of the Holy Spirit
B056C003V006	56	3	6	which he poured out upon us richly through Jesus Christ our Savior,
B056C003V007	56	3	7	that we might be declared righteous by his grace and become heirs with the hope of life eternal."
B056C003V008	56	3	8	That is a trustworthy saying. I wish you to insist on these things so that those who have put their faith in God may give earnest attention to honorable work. These things are honorable and also useful to men.
B056C003V009	56	3	9	But avoid foolish disputes and genealogies and strife and quarrels about the Law; for they are unprofitable and futile.
B056C003V010	56	3	10	If a man is factious, after one or two warnings, have nothing more to do with him,
B056C003V011	56	3	11	knowing that such a one is perverted and goes on sinning though self-condemned.
B056C003V012	56	3	12	When I send Artemas to you or Tychicus, try to come to me at Nicopolis, for I have decided to pass the winter there.
B056C003V013	56	3	13	Do your best in helping Zenas, the lawyer, and Apollos forward on their journey so that they may lack nothing.
B056C003V014	56	3	14	Our people too must learn to give attention to honorable work, so as to be able to meet pressing needs, that they may not be fruitless.
B056C003V015	56	3	15	All who are with me send you their greetings. Give our greetings to those who love us in the faith. Grace be with all of you.
B057C001V001	57	1	1	PAUL, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon, our beloved fellow worker,
B057C001V002	57	1	2	and to Apphia, our sister, and to Archippus, our fellow soldier, and to the Church that meets at your house:
B057C001V003	57	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B057C001V004	57	1	4	I always thank my God when I mention you in my prayers,
B057C001V005	57	1	5	for I hear of the love and the loyalty that you have to the Lord Jesus Christ and to all the holy.
B057C001V006	57	1	6	I pray that your fellowship in the faith may become effective in the knowledge of all the good there is in us in our relation to Christ.
B057C001V007	57	1	7	For I have had great joy and encouragement in your love, because the hearts of the holy have been refreshed by you, brother.
B057C001V008	57	1	8	Therefore, though I might have great boldness in Christ to command you what is fitting,
B057C001V009	57	1	9	I beg you rather for love's sake, as Paul the old man and now the prisoner of Christ Jesus \'97
B057C001V010	57	1	10	I beg you in behalf of my child Onesimus, born to me in my chains,
B057C001V011	57	1	11	who once was useless to you, but now is useful to you and to me.
B057C001V012	57	1	12	I am sending him back to you, though he is my very heart.
B057C001V013	57	1	13	I should like to have him for my own, to serve me in my chains for the good news, as your representative,
B057C001V014	57	1	14	but without your consent I am unwilling to do anything, so that your goodness may not be of necessity but of free will.
B057C001V015	57	1	15	Perhaps it was for this that he was separated from you for a time, that you might have him back for ever,
B057C001V016	57	1	16	no longer as a slave, but more than a slave, a brother beloved, especially to me, but how much more to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.
B057C001V017	57	1	17	If then you hold me for a partner, receive him as you would me.
B057C001V018	57	1	18	If he has wronged you in any way or owes you anything, charge that to my account.
B057C001V019	57	1	19	I, Paul, write it with my own hand. I will pay it \'97 not to mention to you that you owe me your own self besides.
B057C001V020	57	1	20	Yes, brother, let me have this help from you in the Lord; refresh my heart in Christ.
B057C001V021	57	1	21	I am writing to you confident of your obedience and knowing that you will do more than I say.
B057C001V022	57	1	22	At the same time I want you to prepare a lodging for me, for I hope that through your prayers I shall be given back to you.
B057C001V023	57	1	23	Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus,
B057C001V024	57	1	24	and Mark, Aristarchus, Demas and Luke, my fellow workers, send you their greetings.
B057C001V025	57	1	25	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirits.
B058C001V001	58	1	1	MANY times and in many ways God spoke of old to our fathers by the prophets;
B058C001V002	58	1	2	but at the end of these days he has spoken to us by a Son, whom he has appointed heir of all things and through whom he made the world,
B058C001V003	58	1	3	who is the reflection of his glory and the expression of his nature and sustains all things by his word of power, and who, when he had made purification from sins, took his seat at the right hand of the Majesty on high,
B058C001V004	58	1	4	having become as much superior to the angels as the name he has inherited surpasses theirs.
B058C001V005	58	1	5	For to which of the angels did he ever say, "Thou art my son; I have to-day become thy Father"? and again, "I will be to him a Father and he shall be to me a Son"?
B058C001V006	58	1	6	And again when he brings his first-born into the world of men he says, "And let all the angels of God bow down to him."
B058C001V007	58	1	7	Referring to the angels he says, "He makes his angels winds, his servants a flame of fire."
B058C001V008	58	1	8	But regarding the Son he says, "Thy throne, O God, is forever and ever. Thy royal scepter is a scepter of justice.
B058C001V009	58	1	9	Thou lovest righteousness and hatest lawlessness, therefore God, thy God, has anointed thee with the oil of gladness beyond thy companions."
B058C001V010	58	1	10	And, "Thou, in the beginning, O Lord, didst found the earth, and the heavens are works of thy hands.
B058C001V011	58	1	11	They will perish, but thou wilt endure. They all will grow old like a garment
B058C001V012	58	1	12	and like a mantle thou wilt roll them up. But thou art the same and thy years will never end."
B058C001V013	58	1	13	To which of the angels did he ever say, "Sit at my right hand till I make thine enemies thy footstool"?
B058C001V014	58	1	14	Are they not all ministering spirits sent forth for service in behalf of those who are to inherit salvation?
B058C002V001	58	2	1	FOR this reason we should give special attention to the things that we have heard, so as not to drift away from them.
B058C002V002	58	2	2	For if the message spoken through angels was sure and every violation and disobedience received merited punishment,
B058C002V003	58	2	3	how shall we escape if we neglect so great a salvation, which at the beginning was spoken by the Lord and was confirmed to us by those who heard him,
B058C002V004	58	2	4	while God added his testimony by signs and wonders and many kinds of miracles and impartation of the Holy Spirit according to his will?
B058C002V005	58	2	5	For he has not subjected to angels the coming world of which we speak.
B058C002V006	58	2	6	But somewhere one says, "What is man that thou rememberest him? Or the son of man that thou carest for him?
B058C002V007	58	2	7	Thou hast made him a little lower than the angels. With glory and honor thou hast crowned him.
B058C002V008	58	2	8	All things thou hast put under his feet." When he put all things under him he left nothing that was not put under him. We do not yet see all things put under him,
B058C002V009	58	2	9	but we see Jesus, who was made a little lower than the angels for the suffering of death that by the grace of God he might taste of death for every man, now crowned with glory and honor.
B058C002V010	58	2	10	For it was fitting that he through whom are all things and for whom are all things, when leading many sons to glory, should make the great Leader of their salvation perfect through sufferings.
B058C002V011	58	2	11	For he who makes holy and they who are made holy are all of one. For this cause he is not ashamed to call them brothers,
B058C002V012	58	2	12	saying, "I will tell thy name to my brothers. In the midst of the assembly I will sing praise to thee,"
B058C002V013	58	2	13	and again, "I will trust in him," and again, "Here am I and the children whom God has given me."
B058C002V014	58	2	14	Since then the children share in blood and flesh, he himself in the same way shared in them, in order that through death he might defeat him who had the power of death, that is, the Devil,
B058C002V015	58	2	15	and set free all those who through fear of death were all their lives doomed to slavery.
B058C002V016	58	2	16	For he does not come to the help of angels, but he comes to the help of the descendants of Abraham.
B058C002V017	58	2	17	And for that reason he had to be made like his brethren in everything, so as to be a compassionate and faithful high priest in things relating to God, to make propitiation for the sins of the people.
B058C002V018	58	2	18	For since he himself has suffered when tempted he is able to help those who are tempted.
B058C003V001	58	3	1	THEREFORE, holy brethren, sharers in a heavenly call, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our confession, Jesus,
B058C003V002	58	3	2	who was faithful to him who made him as also Moses was in all God's house.
B058C003V003	58	3	3	For he has been thought worthy of more glory than Moses, just as he who has built a house has more honor than the house.
B058C003V004	58	3	4	For every house is built by some one, but he who built all things is God.
B058C003V005	58	3	5	Moses was faithful in all God's house as a servant for a testimony to the things that were to be spoken,
B058C003V006	58	3	6	but Christ as a Son over his own house. We are his house if we hold firmly to the end our confidence and the hope of which we boast.
B058C003V007	58	3	7	Wherefore, as the Holy Spirit says, "To-day if you will hear his voice,
B058C003V008	58	3	8	do not harden your hearts as when they made me angry on the day when they tried me in the desert,
B058C003V009	58	3	9	when your fathers put me to a test and saw my deeds for forty years.
B058C003V010	58	3	10	Therefore I was much displeased with that generation and said, 'They always go astray in their hearts and they do not know my paths.'
B058C003V011	58	3	11	So I swore in my wrath, 'They shall not enter into my rest.'
B058C003V012	58	3	12	See to it, brethren, that there shall not be in any one of you a wicked, unbelieving heart ready to forsake the living God,
B058C003V013	58	3	13	but encourage one another daily while it is called "to-day," that no one may be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.
B058C003V014	58	3	14	For we become sharers with Christ if we hold firmly to the end the assurance with which we began.
B058C003V015	58	3	15	When it is said, "To-day if you will hear his voice, do not harden your hearts as when they made me angry" \'97
B058C003V016	58	3	16	who when they heard made him angry? Was it not all those who came out of Egypt with Moses?
B058C003V017	58	3	17	With whom was he much displeased for forty years? Was it not with those who sinned, whose bodies fell in the desert?
B058C003V018	58	3	18	To whom did he swear that they should not enter his rest, except to those who had no faith?
B058C003V019	58	3	19	We see that they were unable to enter because of their lack of faith.
B058C004V001	58	4	1	LET us, then, be afraid that, though the promise of entering his rest is still left, some one of you may seem to have missed it.
B058C004V002	58	4	2	For we have received the good news just as they did, but the message that was heard did not benefit them, since it did not meet with faith in the hearers.
B058C004V003	58	4	3	For we who have faith are entering into the rest, as he said, "As I swore in my wrath, 'They shall not enter into my rest,' " although his works had been finished since the creation of the world.
B058C004V004	58	4	4	For he has somewhere spoken of the seventh day thus, "And God rested on the seventh day from all his works,"
B058C004V005	58	4	5	and in this place again, "They shall not enter into my rest."
B058C004V006	58	4	6	Since, then, it remains for some to enter into it, and those who first received the good news did not enter because of lack of faith \'97
B058C004V007	58	4	7	again he indicates a day, "to-day," saying in David so long after, as has been already quoted, "To-day if you will hear his voice, do not harden your hearts."
B058C004V008	58	4	8	For if Joshua had given them rest he would not be speaking of another day after that.
B058C004V009	58	4	9	Therefore there still remains a rest for the people of God.
B058C004V010	58	4	10	For he who has entered into God's rest has rested from his works as God did from his.
B058C004V011	58	4	11	Let us endeavor then to enter into that rest so that no one shall fall, after that example of lack of faith.
B058C004V012	58	4	12	For the word of God is living and effective and sharper than any two-edged sword, and it pierces until it divides soul and spirit, joints and marrow, and it judges the thoughts and purposes of the heart.
B058C004V013	58	4	13	There is not a creature invisible to him, but all things are naked and defenseless before the eyes of him to whom we must account.
B058C004V014	58	4	14	Since, then, we have a great High Priest who has passed through the heavens, Jesus, the Son of God, let us hold fast our confession.
B058C004V015	58	4	15	For we have not a high priest who cannot sympathize with our weaknesses, for he has been tempted in every way just as we are, yet without sin.
B058C004V016	58	4	16	Therefore let us come with confidence to the throne of grace and receive compassion and find grace for timely help.
B058C005V001	58	5	1	FOR every high priest taken from among men is appointed in behalf of men in things relating to God to offer gifts and sacrifices for sins.
B058C005V002	58	5	2	He is able to sympathize with the ignorant and the erring, since he himself is beset with weaknesses.
B058C005V003	58	5	3	For this reason he must bring an offering for his own sins, just as he does for those of the people.
B058C005V004	58	5	4	And no one takes this honor upon himself unless called by God, as Aaron was.
B058C005V005	58	5	5	So too Christ did not take for himself the glory of becoming a high priest, but he who said to him, "Thou art my Son, to-day I have become thy Father,"
B058C005V006	58	5	6	and who says in another place, "Thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek."
B058C005V007	58	5	7	Christ, in the days of his flesh, offered prayers and supplications to him who was able to save him from death, with strong outcries and tears, and was heard and saved from his terrors.
B058C005V008	58	5	8	Although he was a Son he learned obedience from his sufferings,
B058C005V009	58	5	9	and being thus made perfect he became the author of eternal salvation to all who obey him,
B058C005V010	58	5	10	and was proclaimed by God a high priest after the order of Melchizedek.
B058C005V011	58	5	11	Regarding Melchizedek we have much to say that is hard to explain, since you have become dull of hearing.
B058C005V012	58	5	12	For when, considering the time, you ought to be teachers you need to have some one teach you again the first principles of the revelations of God. You have come to need milk and not solid food.
B058C005V013	58	5	13	For every one who takes milk is inexperienced in the doctrine of righteousness, for he is a child.
B058C005V014	58	5	14	But solid food is for adults who through practice have their senses exercised in distinguishing good and bad.
B058C006V001	58	6	1	THEREFORE let us leave elementary teaching about Christ and hasten on to what is advanced, not laying again a foundation \'97 change of heart from dead works, faith in God,
B058C006V002	58	6	2	the teaching about baptisms, the laying on of hands, resurrection of the dead, and eternal judgment.
B058C006V003	58	6	3	This we will do if God permits.
B058C006V004	58	6	4	For it is impossible for those who have been once for all enlightened and have tasted the heavenly gift and have become sharers in the Holy Spirit
B058C006V005	58	6	5	and have tasted God's word and the powers of the coming world,
B058C006V006	58	6	6	and then have fallen away, to have again a change of heart, since they are crucifying for themselves afresh the Son of God and putting him to open shame.
B058C006V007	58	6	7	For ground that drinks the rain that comes often upon it and bears plants useful to those for whom it is farmed shares in God's blessing;
B058C006V008	58	6	8	but if it bears thorns and thistles it is judged worthless and is near to being cursed. In the end it will be burnt over.
B058C006V009	58	6	9	But we are persuaded of better things regarding you, beloved, things that belong with salvation, though we thus speak.
B058C006V010	58	6	10	For God is not so unjust as to forget your work and the love that you have shown to his name as you have served and are still serving the holy.
B058C006V011	58	6	11	But we desire to have each one of you show to the end the same earnestness for the fulfillment of our hope,
B058C006V012	58	6	12	that you may not be dull, but imitators of those who through faith and patience are inheriting the promises.
B058C006V013	58	6	13	For God, when making the promise to Abraham, since he could swear by no one greater, swore by himself,
B058C006V014	58	6	14	saying, "Surely, I will greatly bless you and greatly multiply you."
B058C006V015	58	6	15	And so after patient waiting Abraham obtained what was promised.
B058C006V016	58	6	16	For men swear by the greater and an oath for confirmation is to them the end of all dispute.
B058C006V017	58	6	17	In this case God being abundantly willing to show to the heirs of the promise the unchangeable purpose of his will gave the surety of an oath,
B058C006V018	58	6	18	that by two unchangeable things, in which it was impossible for God to be false, we might have strong encouragement, we who have fled to lay hold on the hope that lies before us.
B058C006V019	58	6	19	We have this hope as an anchor of the soul, sure and firm, and it enters into the tent within the curtain
B058C006V020	58	6	20	where Jesus, our forerunner, has entered in our behalf, becoming forever a high priest after the order of Melchizedek.
B058C007V001	58	7	1	FOR, this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of God Most High, who met Abraham when he was returning from the defeat of the kings and blessed him,
B058C007V002	58	7	2	and to whom Abraham gave a tenth of all 
B058C007V003	58	7	3	without father, without mother, without ancestors, without either birthday or end of life, but made like the Son of God, remains a priest permanently.
B058C007V004	58	7	4	But see how great this man was, since Abraham the patriarch gave him a tenth of his choicest spoils.
B058C007V005	58	7	5	And even those of the sons of Levi who attain the priesthood have command according to the Law to take a tenth from the people, their own brethren, although these have sprung from the loins of Abraham.
B058C007V006	58	7	6	But he who had no genealogy from these took a tenth from Abraham and pronounced a blessing on him who had the promises.
B058C007V007	58	7	7	Without dispute the less is blessed by the greater.
B058C007V008	58	7	8	And here mortal men receive tenths, but there one of whom the witness is that he is living.
B058C007V009	58	7	9	And, to put it frankly, Levi, who receives the tenths, was made to pay a tenth through Abraham.
B058C007V010	58	7	10	For he was still in the loins of his father when Melchizedek met Abraham.
B058C007V011	58	7	11	If, then, perfection had been through the Levitical priesthood, \'97 for on the basis of that the people received the Law \'97 what need was there for another kind of priest to arise and not be called of the order of Aaron?
B058C007V012	58	7	12	For when the priesthood has been changed there comes of necessity also a change of law.
B058C007V013	58	7	13	For he of whom these things are said belongs to another tribe, from which no one has ever had anything to do with the altar.
B058C007V014	58	7	14	For it is plain that our Lord has arisen from Judah, and in connection with that tribe Moses said nothing about priests.
B058C007V015	58	7	15	And this is yet more abundantly evident if after the order of Melchizedek there arises a priest of a different kind
B058C007V016	58	7	16	who has become such, not according to the law of a commandment made for the flesh, but according to the power of unending life.
B058C007V017	58	7	17	For it is affirmed of him, "Thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek."
B058C007V018	58	7	18	There is a setting aside of the earlier commandment because of its weakness and uselessness \'97
B058C007V019	58	7	19	for the Law brought nothing to perfection \'97 and there is the bringing in of a better hope through which we draw near to God.
B058C007V020	58	7	20	And just as it was not without an oath \'97
B058C007V021	58	7	21	for those men have become priests without an oath, but he with an oath from him who said to him, "The Lord has sworn and will not change his mind: thou art a priest forever" \'97
B058C007V022	58	7	22	by so much better is the covenant of which Jesus has become surety.
B058C007V023	58	7	23	And many of them became priests because they were prevented by death from continuing,
B058C007V024	58	7	24	but he, because he continues forever, has an unending priesthood.
B058C007V025	58	7	25	And so he is able to save perfectly those who come to God through him, since he is forever living to intercede for them.
B058C007V026	58	7	26	For such was the High Priest that we needed, holy, innocent, unstained, separated from sinners, and made higher than the heavens.
B058C007V027	58	7	27	He has not the daily need, like the other priests, first to offer sacrifices for his own sins and then for those of the people. This latter he did once for all when he offered himself.
B058C007V028	58	7	28	For the Law makes high priests of men who have infirmities, but the word of the oath, which comes after the Law, makes High Priest of a Son who is perfected forever.
B058C008V001	58	8	1	THE chief point of what I have been saying is this: we have such a High Priest who has taken his seat at the right hand of the throne of Majesty in the heavens,
B058C008V002	58	8	2	and who ministers in the holy place and in the true Tent set up by the Lord, not by man.
B058C008V003	58	8	3	Now every high priest is appointed to offer gifts and sacrifices. Whence it is necessary for this one to have something to offer.
B058C008V004	58	8	4	If he were upon the earth he would not be a priest at all, since there are those who offer the gifts according to the Law.
B058C008V005	58	8	5	They minister as an example and shadow of the things in heaven, just as Moses was divinely instructed when he was about to make the Tent. "See," it was said, "that you make everything according to the model shown you on the mountain."
B058C008V006	58	8	6	But now Christ has obtained a ministry as much more excellent as the covenant of which he is mediator is better and based upon better promises.
B058C008V007	58	8	7	For if that first covenant had been faultless a place would not have been sought for a second.
B058C008V008	58	8	8	But finding fault with it he says, "The days are coming, says the Lord, when I will make for the house of Israel and for the house of Judah a new covenant,
B058C008V009	58	8	9	not in the manner of the covenant which I made with their fathers, on the day when I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt. For they did not abide by my covenant and I ceased to care for them, says the Lord.
B058C008V010	58	8	10	This is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days, says the Lord; I will put my laws into their minds and will write them upon their hearts and I will be their God and they will be my people.
B058C008V011	58	8	11	They shall not teach each one his fellow citizen and each one his brother saying, 'Know the Lord'; for all shall know me, from the least to the greatest of them,
B058C008V012	58	8	12	and I will be merciful to their wrong-doings and their sins I will remember no more."
B058C008V013	58	8	13	In saying "new" he has pronounced the first covenant old. But what grows old and decadent is near to disappearance.
B058C009V001	58	9	1	THE first covenant had regulations of worship and its holy building in this world.
B058C009V002	58	9	2	For a Tent was erected, in the first part of which were the lampstand and the table and the consecrated bread. This was called the Holy Place.
B058C009V003	58	9	3	Behind the second curtain was the part called the Holy of Holies.
B058C009V004	58	9	4	It had the golden altar of incense and the ark of the covenant all covered with gold. In this was a golden jar with the manna and Aaron's rod that sprouted and the tablets of the covenant.
B058C009V005	58	9	5	Above it were cherubim of glory overshadowing the place of propitiation. Regarding these things it is not now possible to speak in detail.
B058C009V006	58	9	6	But these things being thus arranged, the priests go constantly into the first part of the Tent, performing their services,
B058C009V007	58	9	7	but into the second part the High Priest alone goes once in the year, not without blood, which he offers for himself and for the sins ignorantly committed by the people.
B058C009V008	58	9	8	The Holy Spirit shows this, that the way into the holy place has not yet been made plain while the first Tent is standing.
B058C009V009	58	9	9	That is a symbol, for the time being, in accordance with which gifts and sacrifices are offered, though they cannot make the worshiper perfect in his conscience,
B058C009V010	58	9	10	since they consist only of foods and drinks and various baths \'97 rules respecting the flesh, imposed until the time of reformation.
B058C009V011	58	9	11	But when Christ came as High Priest of the good things that have come, he entered once for all through the greater and more perfect Tent not made by hands \'97 that is, not of this creation \'97
B058C009V012	58	9	12	and not with the blood of goats and calves, but with his own blood, into the holy place, and thereby found eternal redemption.
B058C009V013	58	9	13	For if the blood of goats and bulls, and the ashes of a heifer sprinkling the defiled, makes them holy as regards purity of their flesh,
B058C009V014	58	9	14	how much more will the blood of Christ, who through an eternal Spirit offered himself an unblemished sacrifice to God, cleanse our consciences from dead works for the service of the living God.
B058C009V015	58	9	15	For this reason he is the mediator of a better covenant that, a death having taken place for redemption from sins under the first covenant, those who have been called may receive the eternal inheritance promised to them.
B058C009V016	58	9	16	For where there is a last will and testament the death of the testator must be put in evidence.
B058C009V017	58	9	17	For a will is valid in the case of the dead: it never has any force while the testator is living.
B058C009V018	58	9	18	Hence the first covenant was not introduced without blood.
B058C009V019	58	9	19	When all the commands of the Law had been spoken by Moses to all the people, he took the blood of calves and goats, with water and scarlet wool and hyssop, and sprinkled it on the book and on all the people,
B058C009V020	58	9	20	saying, "This is the blood of the covenant which God has commanded for you."
B058C009V021	58	9	21	And the Tent and all the things used in worship he likewise sprinkled with blood.
B058C009V022	58	9	22	Almost everything is cleansed with blood, according to the Law, and without the shedding of blood there is no forgiveness.
B058C009V023	58	9	23	It was necessary, then, that the copies of the things in heaven should be cleansed with these sacrifices, but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these.
B058C009V024	58	9	24	For Christ did not enter into a holy place made by hands, a copy of the true, but into heaven itself, now to appear before the face of God in our behalf.
B058C009V025	58	9	25	Nor was it to offer himself often, as the High Priest enters into the holy place every year with blood not his own;
B058C009V026	58	9	26	then he must have suffered often since the foundation of the world. But now, once for all, at the end of the ages, he has appeared to do away with sin by his sacrifice.
B058C009V027	58	9	27	And as it is appointed for men once for all to die and after this comes judgment,
B058C009V028	58	9	28	so Christ was once for all offered to bear the sins of many and will appear the second time, apart from sin, to those who are looking for him, and bring them salvation.
B058C010V001	58	10	1	FOR the Law with a shadow of the good things that are coming, but not the very likeness of the things, cannot, by the same sacrifices which they offer constantly every year, ever make perfect those who come,
B058C010V002	58	10	2	since would they not have ceased offering them? Because the worshipers, once for all cleansed, would have had no consciousness of sins.
B058C010V003	58	10	3	But in the sacrifices these are called to mind every year.
B058C010V004	58	10	4	For the blood of bulls and goats is powerless to take away sins.
B058C010V005	58	10	5	Therefore on coming into the world he says, "Sacrifice and offering thou dost not desire: a body thou hast prepared for me.
B058C010V006	58	10	6	Whole burnt offerings and sin offerings thou dost not delight in.
B058C010V007	58	10	7	Then I said, 'Here I have come \'97 in the roll of the book it is written of me \'97 to do thy will, O God.' "
B058C010V008	58	10	8	He first says, "Sacrifices and offerings and whole burnt offerings and sin offerings thou dost not desire nor delight in," such as are offered according to the Law,
B058C010V009	58	10	9	and then he says, "Here I have come to do thy will." He takes away the first to establish the second.
B058C010V010	58	10	10	By this "will" we are made holy through the offering of the body of Jesus Christ once for all.
B058C010V011	58	10	11	Every priest stands daily doing service and offering many times the same sacrifices, although they never can take away sins.
B058C010V012	58	10	12	But this Priest after offering one sacrifice for sins forever, took his seat at the right hand of God,
B058C010V013	58	10	13	for the future only waiting until his enemies are made his footstool.
B058C010V014	58	10	14	For by one offering he has forever perfected those who are made holy.
B058C010V015	58	10	15	The Holy Spirit testifies this to us; for after having said,
B058C010V016	58	10	16	"This is the covenant that I will make with them after those days, says the Lord: I will put my laws in their hearts and on their minds I will write them," he adds,
B058C010V017	58	10	17	"and their sins and their law-breakings I will remember no more."
B058C010V018	58	10	18	But where there is forgiveness of these, there is no longer any offering for sin.
B058C010V019	58	10	19	Since we have, then, brethren, confidence in entering the holy place through the blood of Jesus,
B058C010V020	58	10	20	by the new and living way which he has made for us through the curtain, that is, his flesh,
B058C010V021	58	10	21	and since we have a great Priest over the house of God,
B058C010V022	58	10	22	let us come with true hearts in full assurance of faith, having our hearts sprinkled from an evil conscience and our bodies bathed in pure water.
B058C010V023	58	10	23	Let us hold fast the confession of our hope without wavering, for he is faithful who has promised,
B058C010V024	58	10	24	and let us keep watch to incite one another to love and noble deeds,
B058C010V025	58	10	25	not neglecting to assemble yourselves, as some do, but encouraging one another, and so much the more, as you see the day drawing near.
B058C010V026	58	10	26	For if we go on sinning willfully after receiving the knowledge of the truth, there remains no longer any sacrifice for sins,
B058C010V027	58	10	27	but a dreadful expectation of doom and a fury of fire that will devour the opposers.
B058C010V028	58	10	28	Any one who sets aside a law of Moses dies without pity on the testimony of two or three witnesses.
B058C010V029	58	10	29	Of how much worse punishment do you think he will be judged worthy who has trampled on the Son of God, who has thought the blood of the covenant, by which it was made holy, an unholy thing, and who has insulted the Spirit of grace?
B058C010V030	58	10	30	For we know him who said, "Vengeance is mine, I will repay," and again, "The Lord will judge his people."
B058C010V031	58	10	31	It is dreadful to fall into the hands of the living God.
B058C010V032	58	10	32	Remember the early days in which, after being enlightened, you endured a great struggle with sufferings,
B058C010V033	58	10	33	at one time made a public spectacle by reproaches and distresses, at another time making common cause with those who were thus treated.
B058C010V034	58	10	34	For you even suffered with the prisoners and accepted the plundering of your property with joy, knowing that you had a better and enduring possession.
B058C010V035	58	10	35	Do not, then, cast away your confidence, for it will have a great reward.
B058C010V036	58	10	36	You have need of patience so that after doing the will of God you may gain the promised blessing.
B058C010V037	58	10	37	For yet "a little, very little, while, and he who is coming will come and will not delay.
B058C010V038	58	10	38	My righteous man will live by faith; but if he shrinks back, my soul has no delight in him."
B058C010V039	58	10	39	But we are not of those who shrink back and perish, but of those who have faith and will win their souls.
B058C011V001	58	11	1	FAITH is an assurance of things hoped for, a conviction of things not seen.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	By this the men of old won their fame.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	By faith we understand that the worlds came into order at the word of God, so that what is now seen did not come out of things that are visible.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	By faith Abel offered to God a better sacrifice than Cain, for which he had witness borne to him that he was righteous, God testifying to his gifts, and by it, though dead, he still speaks.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	By faith Enoch was taken from the earth so that he did not see death, and he was not found because God had taken him. For before being taken he had this testimony that he had pleased God.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	But without faith it is impossible to please him. For he who comes to God must have faith that he exists and that he becomes the rewarder of those who seek him.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	By faith Noah, after receiving a divine warning regarding things as yet unseen, reverently built an ark for the saving of his household. Thus he condemned the world and became an heir of the righteousness of faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	By faith Abraham when called obeyed and came out into the place which he was to obtain for an inheritance. He came out not knowing where he was coming.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	By faith he made his home in the promised land as in a foreign country, living in tents with Isaac and Jacob, the heirs with him of the same promise.
B058C011V010	58	11	10	For he was looking for the city that has the foundations, whose architect and builder is God.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	By faith Sarah received power to conceive a child even when past the natural time of life, since she thought him trustworthy who had given the promise.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	And so from just one man, already dead in that respect, there sprang descendants "as the stars of heaven in multitude and as the sand on the seashore innumerable."
B058C011V013	58	11	13	These all died in faith, not having obtained the promised blessings, but they saw them and greeted them afar and confessed that they were strangers and foreigners in the land.
B058C011V014	58	11	14	For those who say such things make it plain that they are seeking a fatherland.
B058C011V015	58	11	15	And if they had been thinking of that land from which they came they would have had opportunity to return.
B058C011V016	58	11	16	But now they desire a better land, that is, a heavenly one. Therefore God is not ashamed of them \'97 of being called their God; for he has prepared for them a city.
B058C011V017	58	11	17	By faith Abraham when he was tested offered up Isaac, and he who had received the promises began offering his only son
B058C011V018	58	11	18	regarding whom it had been said, "Those only whose descent is through Isaac shall be called your descendants."
B058C011V019	58	11	19	He reasoned that God was able to raise him even from the dead, and figuratively he did win him back from the dead.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	By faith also Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau and spoke of things to come.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	By faith Jacob when dying blessed each of the sons of Joseph and worshiped leaning on the top of his staff.
B058C011V022	58	11	22	By faith Joseph, when at his end, mentioned the departure of the children of Israel and gave orders regarding his own bones.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	By faith Moses at his birth was hidden three months by his parents, because they saw that the child was beautiful, and they did not fear the king's command.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	By faith Moses when he had grown up refused to be called a son of Pharaoh's daughter.
B058C011V025	58	11	25	He chose rather to suffer hard-ship with the people of God than to enjoy the brief pleasure of sin,
B058C011V026	58	11	26	and he thought the reproach of Christ greater riches than the treasures of Egypt. For he was looking to the final reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	By faith he left Egypt, not fearing the king's anger; for he endured as if seeing him who is unseen.
B058C011V028	58	11	28	By faith he kept the Passover and the sprinkling of the blood, so that the destroyer might not touch their first-born.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	By faith they crossed the Red Sea as on dry land; but the Egyptians when they tried to do so were drowned.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	By faith the walls of Jericho fell down after they had been encircled seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	By faith Rahab, the prostitute, did not perish with those who had refused to believe; because she had welcomed the spies with peace.
B058C011V032	58	11	32	And what shall I say further? Time would fail me to tell of Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, and of David and Samuel and the prophets;
B058C011V033	58	11	33	who through faith struggled against kingdoms and subdued them, did deeds of righteousness, obtained promised blessings, shut the mouths of lions,
B058C011V034	58	11	34	quenched the power of fire, escaped the edge of the sword, out of weakness grew strong, became mighty in war, turned back armies of foreigners.
B058C011V035	58	11	35	Women received back their dead by a resurrection. Others were tortured, refusing to pay for liberation, in order to gain a better resurrection.
B058C011V036	58	11	36	Still others had experience of mockings and floggings, yes, of chains and prisons.
B058C011V037	58	11	37	They were stoned, afflicted, sawn in two, murdered with the sword. They went about in sheepskins, in goatskins, destitute, distressed, maltreated.
B058C011V038	58	11	38	The world was not worthy of them. They wandered in deserts and mountains, in caves and in holes in the earth.
B058C011V039	58	11	39	All these won God's approval by their faith. Yet they did not obtain the fulfillment of the promise.
B058C011V040	58	11	40	In reference to us God had something better in view, that they without us should not reach perfection.
B058C012V001	58	12	1	THEREFORE, surrounded as we are by so great a cloud of witnesses, let us lay aside every weight and the sin that so easily besets us, and let us run with patience the race that lies before us,
B058C012V002	58	12	2	looking to Jesus the beginner and finisher of our faith, who for the joy set before him endured a cross, thinking little of the shame, and has taken his seat at the right hand of the throne of God.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	Think of him who endured such hostile speaking of sinners against him, that you may not grow weary and despondent in heart.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	You have not yet resisted to blood in the contest against sin,
B058C012V005	58	12	5	and you have forgotten the encouragement which reasons with you as with sons, "My son, do not think slightingly of the discipline of the Lord and be not faint-hearted when reproved by him:
B058C012V006	58	12	6	for whom the Lord loves he disciplines and scourges every son whom he receives as his own."
B058C012V007	58	12	7	It is for discipline that you are enduring. God is laying it upon you as upon sons. For what son is there whom his father does not discipline?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	But if you are without discipline, in which all share, then you are bastards and not sons.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	Besides, we had fathers of our flesh who disciplined us and we used to reverence them. Shall we not much more be submissive to the Father of our spirits and live?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	For they for a few days disciplined us as seemed good to them, but he for our profit, that we may share his holiness.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	All discipline for the time being seems not joyous but grievous, but afterward it yields the peaceful fruit of righteousness to those who have passed through its training.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	So raise the relaxed hands and straighten the unstrung knees
B058C012V013	58	12	13	and make straight paths for your feet, so that the lame limb may not be put out of joint but rather cured.
B058C012V014	58	12	14	Follow after peace with all men and holiness, without which no one will see the Lord.
B058C012V015	58	12	15	Be on your guard that no one shall fail of the grace of God, that no bitter root shall sprout up and trouble you and through it many be stained,
B058C012V016	58	12	16	that there shall be none unchaste, or profane like Esau, who for one meal sold his birthright.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For you know that afterward when he wished to inherit the blessing he was rejected, for he found no place for a change in his father's mind though he sought it earnestly with tears.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For you have not come to something that may be touched, ablaze with fire, and to blackness and darkness and tempest
B058C012V019	58	12	19	and the blast of a trumpet and the sound of words which those who heard begged not to have spoken of them.
B058C012V020	58	12	20	For they could not bear the command, "If even an animal touches the mountain it must be stoned."
B058C012V021	58	12	21	And so dreadful was the sight that Moses said, "I am terrified and trembling."
B058C012V022	58	12	22	But you have come to Mount Zion and the city of the living God, heavenly Jerusalem, to tens of thousands of angels,
B058C012V023	58	12	23	to the festal assembly and congregation of first-born who are enrolled in heaven, and to God the Judge of all, and to the spirits of righteous men made perfect,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	and to Jesus the Mediator of the new covenant and to the sprinkled blood which tells something better than the blood of Abel.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	Beware of rejecting him who is speaking. For if those did not escape who rejected him who taught the divine will on earth, much less shall we if we reject him who speaks from heaven.
B058C012V026	58	12	26	His voice then shook the earth, but now he has announced, "Yet once for all I shall shake not only the earth but also heaven."
B058C012V027	58	12	27	And this expression "yet once for all" shows the removal of the things shaken, as of things that have been made, that the unshaken things may remain.
B058C012V028	58	12	28	So then, since we are receiving an unshaken kingdom, let us have grace by which we may worship God acceptably with reverence and awe.
B058C012V029	58	12	29	For our God is a consuming fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	LET brotherly love continue.
B058C013V002	58	13	2	Do not forget hospitality: for by this some have, without knowing it, had angels as their guests.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Keep in mind the prisoners, as if you were their fellow prisoners, and those who are suffering hardships, since you yourselves are also in the body.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Let marriage be held in honor by all and let the bed be undefiled; for unchaste persons and adulterers God will judge.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Let your lives be free from the love of money. Be content with what you have. For he has said, "I will not fail you nor will I forsake you."
B058C013V006	58	13	6	So we may say with courage, "The Lord is my helper; I will not fear. What can man do to me?"
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember your leaders, those who have spoken to you God's message, think how they ended their lives and imitate their faith.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jesus Christ is yesterday and to-day the same \'97 yes, and through the ages.
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Do not be carried away with all sorts of foreign teachings. It is well to have the heart strengthened by grace, not by special kinds of food. Those who live in that way are not profited.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	We have an altar of which those who worship in the Tent have no right to eat.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For the bodies of the animals whose blood is brought into the holy place by the High Priest are burned outside the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	For this reason Jesus also, to make the people holy by his own blood, suffered outside the gate.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	Let us go out to him outside the camp and bear the reproaches cast on him.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For we have here no continuing city, but we are seeking the coming one.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	Through him then let us offer to God always the sacrifice of praise, that is, the fruit of lips that make confession in his name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	Do not forget kindness and generosity, for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Obey your leaders and yield to their authority; for they watch over your souls as those who must give account, that they may do it with joy and not with sighing. That would be unprofitable for you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Pray for us: for we are confident that we have a good conscience, wishing to live nobly in every way.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	I earnestly beg you to do this that I may be restored to you the sooner.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	May the God of peace, who brought up from the dead our Lord Jesus, the great Shepherd of the sheep through the blood of an eternal covenant,
B058C013V021	58	13	21	equip you with every good thing for doing his will, doing in you what is well-pleasing in his sight through Jesus Christ, to whom be glory for the ages of the ages. Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	I beg you, brethren, to bear with my words of exhortation; for I have written to you briefly.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	I wish you to know that our brother Timothy has been set at liberty. With him, if he comes soon, I will see you.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Give my greetings to all your leaders and all the holy. Those who are from Italy send their greetings to you.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	Grace be with you all.
B059C001V001	59	1	1	JAMES, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the Twelve Tribes which are scattered in foreign lands: Greeting.
B059C001V002	59	1	2	Think it all joy, my brethren, when you fall into all sorts of trials,
B059C001V003	59	1	3	since you know that the testing of your faith brings out endurance.
B059C001V004	59	1	4	Let endurance do its complete work, that you may be complete and perfect, lacking in nothing.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	If any one of you is lacking in wisdom, let him ask it from God, who gives to all freely without reproaching, and it will be given to him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But he must ask in faith with never a doubt. For he who doubts is like a wave of the sea, driven by the wind and tossed.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	For that man must not think that he will obtain anything from the Lord \'97
B059C001V008	59	1	8	a two-minded man unsteady in all his ways.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	Let the lowly brother glory in his high station,
B059C001V010	59	1	10	and let the rich brother glory in his lowly station, for he will pass away like a flower of the grass.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	For the sun rises with scorching heat and dries up the grass, and the flower of it falls and the beauty of its face perishes. So shall the rich man wither in his pursuits.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	Blessed is the man who endures trial, for when he has been tested he will gain the crown of life which the Lord has promised to those who love him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	No one must say when tempted, "My temptation comes from God." For God cannot be tempted by evil, and he tempts no one.
B059C001V014	59	1	14	Every one is tempted when he is drawn away by his own passions and enticed.
B059C001V015	59	1	15	Then when passion has conceived it gives birth to sin, and sin, when it is full grown, gives birth to death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Make no mistake, my beloved brethren,
B059C001V017	59	1	17	every good gift and every perfect boon is from above; it descends from the Father of lights, with whom there is no change or shadow caused by turning.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	Of his own will he made us his children through the message of truth, so that we might be a sort of first fruits of his creatures.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	I wish you to know this, my beloved brethren: Every man must be quick to hear, but slow to speak, slow to anger.
B059C001V020	59	1	20	For a man's anger does not work out God's righteousness.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	So lay aside all that is vile and all that remains of malice, and receive with gentleness the implanted message which can save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	Become doers of the message and not hearers only, deceiving your own selves.
B059C001V023	59	1	23	For if one is a hearer of the message and not a doer, he is like a man who looks at his natural face in a mirror.
B059C001V024	59	1	24	He looks at himself and is gone, and immediately forgets what sort of man he was.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But he who looks earnestly into the perfect law of liberty and continues to do so, and becomes not a forgetful hearer but a doer of work \'97 that man will be blessed in what he does.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	If any one thinks himself religious while he does not bridle his tongue, but deceives his own heart, that man's religion is worthless.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	Pure and stainless religion in the sight of God the Father is to visit orphans and widows in their trouble and to keep one's self unspotted from the world.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	MY brethren, do not hold the faith of our glorious Lord Jesus Christ with partiality for persons.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	For if there comes into your assembly a man with gold rings and in fine clothes, and there comes in a poor man in soiled clothes,
B059C002V003	59	2	3	and you look up to the man who is wearing the fine clothes and say, "Take this good seat," and say to the poor man, "Stand there," or "Sit under my footstool,"
B059C002V004	59	2	4	are you not making distinctions in your own minds and have you not become judges with wicked thoughts?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Listen, my beloved brethren, did not God choose the poor of this world to be rich in faith and heirs of the kingdom which he has promised to those who love him?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But you have dishonored the poor man. Do not the rich oppress you and drag you before courts?
B059C002V007	59	2	7	Do they not speak profanely of the noble name by which you are called?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	If you keep the royal law according to the Scripture, "Thou shalt love thy neighbor as thyself," you do well.
B059C002V009	59	2	9	But if you have partiality, you commit sin and are convicted by the law as law-breakers.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	For he who keeps the whole law, but stumbles in one point, has become guilty of all.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For he who said, "Thou shalt not commit adultery," said also, "Thou shalt not commit murder." If you do not commit adultery, but do commit murder, you have become a law-breaker.
B059C002V012	59	2	12	So speak and so act as those who are soon to be judged by a law of liberty.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For judgment is merciless to him who has shown no mercy. Mercy triumphs over judgment.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	Of what use is it, my brethren, for any one to say that he has faith, if he has not works? Can faith save him?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	If a brother or sister is naked and lacks food for the day
B059C002V016	59	2	16	and one of you says to them, "Go in peace, be warmed and fed," but you do not give them what the body needs, what is the good of it?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	Just so faith by itself, if it has no works, is dead.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	But some one will say, "You have faith and I have works. Show me your faith without your works and I will show you my faith by my works."
B059C002V019	59	2	19	You have faith that there is one God. You do well. Even the demons have that faith, and they shudder.
B059C002V020	59	2	20	Are you willing to learn, O vacant-minded man, that faith without works is useless?
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Was not Abraham, our father, pronounced righteous because of works when he laid Isaac his son on the altar?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	You see that faith worked with his works, and by works faith was made perfect
B059C002V023	59	2	23	and the Scripture was fulfilled which says, "Abraham had faith in God and it was credited to him for righteousness" and he was called "God's friend."
B059C002V024	59	2	24	You see that a man is pronounced righteous because of works and not because of faith alone.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	In the same way was not Rahab, the prostitute, pronounced righteous because of works when she had received the messengers and sent them out by a different road?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	For as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is dead.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	DO not, many of you, become teachers, my brethren, for you know that we will receive severer judgment.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For in many ways we all stumble. If any one never stumbles in his talk, he is a perfect man, able to bridle also the whole body.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	If we put bits into the horses' mouths to make them obey us, we turn about their whole bodies.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	See the ships; great as they are and driven by violent winds, they are turned about by a very small rudder wherever the desire of the helmsman chooses.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	Just so the tongue is a small member, but boasts of great things. Think how small a fire may be and yet how vast the forest that it may set ablaze.
B059C003V006	59	3	6	And the tongue is a fire, a world of wickedness. The tongue stands among our members as that which spots the whole body and sets on fire the wheel of nature and is itself set on fire by Gehenna.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For every kind of wild beasts and birds and reptiles and animals from the sea is tamed and has been tamed by human kind,
B059C003V008	59	3	8	but the tongue no man is able to tame. It is a restless evil; it is full of deadly poison.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	With it we bless the Lord our Father and with it we curse the men who are made in the image of God.
B059C003V010	59	3	10	From the same mouth come blessing and cursing. This, my brethren, should not be so.
B059C003V011	59	3	11	Does a spring pour out from the same opening sweet water and bitter?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	Can a fig tree, my brethren, bear olives, or a vine figs? No more can salt water yield fresh water.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Who is wise and intelligent among you? Let him show out of the noble life that he lives his works in wise gentleness.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if you have bitter jealousy and party-spirit in your hearts, do not boast and falsely contradict the truth.
B059C003V015	59	3	15	This wisdom does not come down from on high, but is earthly, animal, demoniacal.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For where jealousy and party-spirit are, there is confusion and every base affair.
B059C003V017	59	3	17	But the wisdom from on high is first pure, then peaceable, fair-minded, easily persuaded, full of compassion and good fruits, impartial, sincere.
B059C003V018	59	3	18	The fruit of righteousness is sown in peace by those who make peace.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	WHENCE come wars and whence come strifes among you? Is it not from your pleasures which carry on war in your members?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You long for something and do not have it. You murder and envy and cannot obtain it. You battle and war. You do not have, because of your not asking.
B059C004V003	59	4	3	You ask and do not receive, because you ask wickedly to waste it on your pleasures.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	You adulteresses, do you not know that the friendship of the world is enmity to God? Whoever chooses to be a friend to the world stands as an enemy of God.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Do you think that the Scripture speaks to no purpose? Does the Spirit which he made dwell in us long enviously?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But he gives greater grace. Therefore it says, "God opposes the proud, but gives grace to the humble."
B059C004V007	59	4	7	Submit yourselves, then, to God. Resist the Devil and he will flee from you.
B059C004V008	59	4	8	Draw near to God and he will draw near to you. Make your hands clean, you sinners, and purify your hearts, you double-minded.
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Be sorrowful and mourn and lament. Let your laughter be turned into grief and your gladness into gloom.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Humble yourselves before the Lord and he will exalt you.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Do not speak against one another, brethren. He who speaks against his brother speaks against the law and judges the law. But if you judge the law you are not a doer of the law, but a judge.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	One is the Lawgiver and Judge \'97 he who is able to save and to destroy. Who are you, to judge your neighbor?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	Come, now, you who say, "To-day or to-morrow we will go to such a city and spend a year and do business and make money,"
B059C004V014	59	4	14	though you do not know what your life will be like on the morrow. For you are a vapor that appears for a little while and then disappears.
B059C004V015	59	4	15	You should rather say, "If the Lord wills it, we shall live and do this or that."
B059C004V016	59	4	16	But now you glory in bragging. All such glorying is evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	If any one, then, knows how to do good and is not doing it, he is committing sin.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	COME, now, you rich men, wail and lament over the miseries that are coming upon you.
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your riches have rotted and your garments have become moth-eaten,
B059C005V003	59	5	3	your gold and silver are rusted over and the rust on them will be an evidence against you and will eat your flesh like fire.
B059C005V004	59	5	4	You have laid up treasures in the last days. See, the wages of the laborers who reaped your fields, fraudulently kept back by you, call aloud, and the cries of the harvesters have come into the ears of the Lord of armies.
B059C005V005	59	5	5	You have lived luxuriously in the land and have given yourselves up to pleasure. You have fattened your hearts in a day of slaughter.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned, you have murdered, the righteous; he does not resist you.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	Therefore be patient, brethren, until the coming of the Lord. See how the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the ground and is patient over it until he receives the early and the late rains.
B059C005V008	59	5	8	You too must be patient. Keep your hearts steadfast, for the coming of the Lord is near.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Do not fret at one another, brethren, and then you will not be judged. The Judge is standing before your doors.
B059C005V010	59	5	10	Take, brethren, the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord as an example of patience in suffering evil.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	We call them blessed because they endured. You have heard of the patience of Job and have seen the end of the Lord's dealings with him, that the Lord is very tender and compassionate.
B059C005V012	59	5	12	Above all things, my brethren, do not swear, either by heaven or by the earth or by any other oath. Let your yes be yes and your no be no, that you may not fall under condemnation.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	Is any one of you suffering hardship? Let him pray. Is any one cheerful? Let him sing with the harp.
B059C005V014	59	5	14	Is any one of you sick? Let him call in the elders of the church and let them pray over him and anoint him with olive oil in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V015	59	5	15	The prayer of faith will save the sick and the Lord will raise him up, and if he has committed sins they will be forgiven him.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	Confess your sins to one another and pray for one another in order to be healed. The effective prayer of a righteous man has great power.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elijah was a man of the same weaknesses as ours, and he prayed earnestly that it might not rain and it did not rain on the land for three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	Then he prayed again and heaven gave rain and the land brought forth its fruits.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	My brethren, if one of you strays from the truth and any one brings him back,
B059C005V020	59	5	20	I wish you to know that he who brings back a sinner from his wanderings will save his soul from death and will hide a host of sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	PETER, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the Chosen Ones of the scattered Jews in foreign lands who are living in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia and Bithynia \'97
B060C001V002	60	1	2	chosen according to the foreknowledge of God the Father and made holy by the Spirit to obey Jesus Christ and be sprinkled with his blood: Grace be to you and peace be multiplied.
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who according to his great mercy has given us a new birth into a living hope through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead \'97
B060C001V004	60	1	4	a birth into an inheritance immortal, unstained and unfading, kept in heaven for you
B060C001V005	60	1	5	who are guarded by the power of God through faith for the salvation which is ready to be revealed on the last day.
B060C001V006	60	1	6	In this you rejoice, though now for a little while, if necessary, you are sorrowful in trials of many kinds,
B060C001V007	60	1	7	so that your tested faith, much more precious than gold that perishes though tested by fire, may be found to your praise and glory and honor when Jesus Christ is revealed,
B060C001V008	60	1	8	whom you love though you have not seen him; in whom you have faith though now you do not see him, and you rejoice with unspeakable and glorious joy
B060C001V009	60	1	9	while you receive the reward of your faith, the salvation of your souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	Regarding this salvation the prophets who foretold the grace that was to come to you
B060C001V011	60	1	11	inquired and searched, trying to find out what time, or what sort of time, the Spirit of Christ which was in them was disclosing when it witnessed beforehand regarding the sufferings of Christ and the glories to follow.
B060C001V012	60	1	12	It was revealed to them that they were serving not themselves but you, in these things which now have been announced to you through those who have told you the good news by the Holy Spirit sent forth from heaven \'97 things which angels earnestly long to look into.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Therefore brace up your minds, be calm and set your hope perfectly on the grace that is to be brought to you when Jesus Christ is revealed.
B060C001V014	60	1	14	As obedient children, do not shape your lives by the passions that ruled you in the former days of ignorance,
B060C001V015	60	1	15	but, like the Holy One who has called you, become yourselves holy in all your way of life,
B060C001V016	60	1	16	for it is written, "You shall be holy because I am holy."
B060C001V017	60	1	17	And if you call upon him as Father who impartially judges by each one's work, live out the time of your sojourn here in reverence,
B060C001V018	60	1	18	for you know that you were not ransomed with perishable things, silver or gold, from your purposeless life handed down from your forefathers,
B060C001V019	60	1	19	but by precious blood, as of a faultless, spotless lamb, the blood of Christ,
B060C001V020	60	1	20	who was foreknown before the foundation of the world, but was manifested at the end of time for your sake
B060C001V021	60	1	21	who through him are faithful to God, who raised him from the dead and gave him glory, so that your faith and hope are in God.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Now that you have made your souls holy by obedience to the truth for sincere brotherly love, you must love one another steadily from your hearts,
B060C001V023	60	1	23	for you have been reborn, not from mortal seed but from immortal by the living and enduring word of God.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	For "All flesh is like grass and all its glory is like the flower of the grass; the grass withers and the flower falls,
B060C001V025	60	1	25	but the word of the Lord endures forever." And this is the word of good news that has been brought to you.
B060C002V001	60	2	1	THEN lay aside all malice and all deceit and hypocrisy and envy and every kind of slander,
B060C002V002	60	2	2	and, like new-born babes, long for the reasonable pure milk, that by it you may grow up into salvation,
B060C002V003	60	2	3	if you have tasted that the Lord is kind.
B060C002V004	60	2	4	Coming to him, a living stone, rejected by men but with the Lord chosen and precious,
B060C002V005	60	2	5	you also as living stones are built up, a spiritual house, and become a holy priesthood to offer spiritual sacrifices acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	Therefore it is contained in Scripture, "See, I am laying in Zion a chosen stone, an honored corner stone. He who has faith in him will not be put to shame."
B060C002V007	60	2	7	To you who have faith is the "honor," but to the unbelieving "the stone which the builders rejected \'97 that has become the corner stone,
B060C002V008	60	2	8	a stone for the foot to strike, a rock to stumble over." Their feet strike the message because of their unbelief, and to this they were destined.
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen race, a kingly priesthood, a holy nation, God's own people, that you may proclaim the virtues of him who called you from darkness into his wonderful light.
B060C002V010	60	2	10	Once you were not a people, but now you are the people of God: once you had not found compassion, but now you have found compassion.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	Beloved, I beg you, as foreigners and resident aliens, to shun the passions of the flesh which war against the soul.
B060C002V012	60	2	12	Keep your daily life among the Gentiles honorable, so that, although they talk against you as if you were wrongdoers, they may, from your noble deeds that they see, glorify God on the day of inspection.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	Be submissive to every human institution for the Lord's sake, whether to the king as supreme,
B060C002V014	60	2	14	or to governors as those sent by him for the punishment of wrongdoers and the praise of those who do good.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For this is the will of God \'97 that by doing good we shall silence the ignorance of thoughtless men.
B060C002V016	60	2	16	Live as free men, yet not using freedom as a cloak for wickedness, but as God's slaves.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Honor all men, love the brotherhood, reverence God, honor the king.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	Household servants, be submissive with all reverence to your lords, not only to the good and fair, but also to the surly.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For this is grace if for conscience toward God any one bears pain, suffering unjustly.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	For what credit is it if when you sin and are struck with the fist you are patient? But if though doing well, you suffer and are patient, that is grace in God's sight.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	For to this you were called, because Christ too suffered for you, leaving you an example that you might follow in his foot-steps.
B060C002V022	60	2	22	He had done no sin, nor was deceit found in his mouth.
B060C002V023	60	2	23	When he was reviled he did not revile back; he suffered, but made no threat; he committed himself to him who judges justly.
B060C002V024	60	2	24	He bore our sins in his own body on the tree that we might die to sins and live to righteousness.
B060C002V025	60	2	25	For you were going astray like sheep, but have now returned to the shepherd and guardian of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	IN the same way you wives are to be submissive to your own husbands, so that if any disbelieve the message they may be won over by the lives of their wives without argument,
B060C003V002	60	3	2	when they look at your pure, reverential behavior.
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Your adornment must not be of the external kind \'97 braiding the hair and putting on gold and wearing fine dresses;
B060C003V004	60	3	4	but the hidden personality of the heart must wear the imperishable beauty of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is in God's sight most precious.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	For so of old the holy women who hoped in God adorned themselves. They were submissive to their own husbands,
B060C003V006	60	3	6	as Sarah obeyed Abraham and called him Master. You have become her children when you do well and feel no terror.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	In the same way, you husbands must live with your wives wisely, since woman's sex is weaker, but you must give them honor as fellow heirs of the grace of life, so that your prayers may not be hindered.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	Finally, all must be like-minded, sympathetic, full of brotherly love, compassionate, humble-minded,
B060C003V009	60	3	9	not repaying evil for evil or abuse for abuse, but rather blessing, for that is what you were called for \'97 to inherit a blessing.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	For "He who would love life and see good days must keep his tongue from evil and his lips from speaking deceit.
B060C003V011	60	3	11	He must turn away from evil and do good; he must seek peace and pursue it.
B060C003V012	60	3	12	For the eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous and his ears are open to their prayer, but the face of the Lord is against wrongdoers."
B060C003V013	60	3	13	And who is it that will harm you if you become earnest for the good?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	But if you should suffer for being righteous, you are blessed. Have no fear of them and do not be disturbed;
B060C003V015	60	3	15	but exalt Christ as Lord in your hearts and be always ready to defend yourselves to every one who asks you to give account of the hope that is in you, yet with gentleness and reverence.
B060C003V016	60	3	16	Keep a good conscience that, although you are slandered, those who misrepresent your good life in Christ may be put to shame.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	For it is better to suffer, if that should be God's will, for doing good than for doing wrong.
B060C003V018	60	3	18	For Christ once for all died for sins, a righteous man for unrighteous men, so that he might lead us to God. He was put to death in the flesh, but made alive in the spirit,
B060C003V019	60	3	19	in which he went and made proclamation to the imprisoned spirits
B060C003V020	60	3	20	who were once disobedient, when the long-suffering of God waited in the days of Noah while the ark was being prepared, into which a few, that is eight souls, went and were saved through water.
B060C003V021	60	3	21	This is a type of baptism, which now saves us \'97 not the putting off of soil from the flesh, but the endeavor for a good conscience toward God through the resurrection of Jesus Christ.
B060C003V022	60	3	22	Now that he has gone into heaven he is at the right hand of God, and angels and authorities and powers have been made subject to him.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	SINCE, then, Christ suffered in the flesh, you also must arm yourselves with the same mind. For he who has suffered in the flesh has ceased from sin,
B060C004V002	60	4	2	so that he does not go on living what remains of his time in the flesh according to human passions, but according to God's will.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	The time that has passed was enough to spend doing the will of the Gentiles, when you went on in indecencies, passions, hard drinking, revelries, carousings, and lawless idolatries.
B060C004V004	60	4	4	In these they think it strange that you are not running with them to the same excess of profligacy, and they slander you.
B060C004V005	60	4	5	But they will have to give account to him who holds himself ready to judge the living and the dead.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	And for this purpose the good news was told even to the dead, that they might be judged like men in the flesh, but live as God does in the spirit.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	The end of all things is near. Therefore be serious and sober and give yourselves to prayer.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	Above all things have earnest love to one another, for love hides a host of sins.
B060C004V009	60	4	9	Be hospitable to one another without grumbling.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	Let each, as he has received a spiritual gift, serve the others in that way, as good stewards of the varied grace of God.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	If any one speaks, let it be as uttering the oracles of God. If any one serves, let it be from the strength that God supplies. Thus in all things let God be glorified through Jesus Christ. To him be glory and strength for the ages of the ages! Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	Beloved, do not be surprised at the fiery fury that is among you, which has come to try you, as if some strange thing were happening to you.
B060C004V013	60	4	13	But rejoice since to this extent you are sharing the sufferings of Christ, that when his glory is revealed you may rejoice and exult.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	If you are reproached for the name of Christ you are blessed, for the spirit of glory and of God rests upon you.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	No one of you must suffer as a murderer or as a thief or as a wrongdoer or as a meddler in other men's affairs.
B060C004V016	60	4	16	But if he suffers as a Christian he should not be ashamed, but should glorify God by that name.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For the time has come for judgment to begin at the house of God. And if it begins first with us, what will be the end of those who disobey the good news of God?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	If the righteous is saved with difficulty, where will the godless and sinful appear?
B060C004V019	60	4	19	So then let those who are suffering according to the will of God commit their souls in well-doing to a faithful Creator.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	THE elders among you I beg \'97 I who am a fellow elder and a witness to the sufferings of Christ and a sharer in the glory soon to be revealed \'97
B060C005V002	60	5	2	I beg you to shepherd the flock of God that is among you, not because you must, but willingly, not for base gain, but eagerly,
B060C005V003	60	5	3	not lording it over your charges, but becoming examples to the flock.
B060C005V004	60	5	4	Then when the chief Shepherd appears you will be repaid with the never-fading crown of glory.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	In the same way you younger men must be subject to your elders. You all must put on the apron of humble service for one another. For God opposes the proud, but gives grace to the humble.
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Humble yourselves, then, under the mighty hand of God so that he may lift you up at the right time.
B060C005V007	60	5	7	Cast all your anxiety on him, for he cares for you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Be sober, watch. Your enemy the Devil, like a roaring lion, goes about seeking some one to devour.
B060C005V009	60	5	9	Resist him firm in the faith and knowing that the same experiences of suffering are being completed in your brotherhood throughout the world.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	The God of all grace, who called you to his eternal glory in Christ, after you have suffered a little will equip, establish and strengthen you.
B060C005V011	60	5	11	To him be power for the ages of the ages! Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	By Silvanus, your faithful brother, as I esteem him, I am writing to you briefly, to encourage you and to testify that this is the true grace of God. Take your stand in it.
B060C005V013	60	5	13	She who is in Babylon, chosen with you, sends her greeting to you, and so does Mark my son.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Salute one another with a kiss of love. Peace be to you all in Christ.
B061C001V001	61	1	1	SIMON PETER, a servant and apostle of Jesus Christ, to those who by the righteousness of our God and Savior Jesus Christ have been allotted a faith as precious as ours:
B061C001V002	61	1	2	Grace be to you and peace be multiplied in the knowledge of God and of Jesus our Lord.
B061C001V003	61	1	3	Since his divine power has given us all things helpful to life and piety through the knowledge of him who has called us by his own glory and virtue,
B061C001V004	61	1	4	and thereby great and precious promises have been granted to us, that through them you may escape the corruption that is in the world through passion and become sharers in the divine nature,
B061C001V005	61	1	5	for this very reason make it your whole endeavor to supply to your faith virtue, and to your virtue knowledge,
B061C001V006	61	1	6	and to your knowledge self-control, and to your self-control endurance, and to your endurance reverence,
B061C001V007	61	1	7	and to your reverence brotherliness, and to your brotherliness love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	For when you have these in abundance they make you to be neither idle nor fruitless regarding the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	But he who lacks these is blind, dim-sighted, and has forgotten that he was cleansed from his former sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	Therefore endeavor more earnestly, brethren, to make sure that you have been called and chosen. For while doing these things you will never stumble.
B061C001V011	61	1	11	For so entrance into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ will be richly provided for you.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	For this reason I shall always keep reminding you of these things, although you know them and are steadfast in the truth that you have.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	I think it right so long as I am in this tent to arouse you by reminding you,
B061C001V014	61	1	14	since I know that the laying aside of my tent will come soon, as our Lord Jesus Christ has made plain to me.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	I will endeavor also on every occasion to make it so that after my going you shall have these things in memory.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	For we were not following cunningly devised myths when we told you of the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but we had been eye-witnesses of his majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	For he received from God the Father honor and glory when such words as these were borne to him from the majestic glory, "This is my Son, the Beloved; in him I delight."
B061C001V018	61	1	18	And this voice we heard borne from heaven when we were with him on the holy mountain.
B061C001V019	61	1	19	Thus have we the words of the prophets confirmed, and you will do well to give attention to them as to a lamp shining in a dark place, until the day dawns and the morning star rises in your hearts;
B061C001V020	61	1	20	since you know this first, that no prophecy of Scripture comes from any one's private interpretation,
B061C001V021	61	1	21	for prophecy never came by the will of man, but men spoke from God as they were moved by the Holy Spirit.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	BUT false prophets also arose among the people, just as there will be false teachers among yourselves, and they will craftily bring in deadly heresies, even disowning the Lord who bought them and bringing on themselves quick ruin.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	Many will follow their shameless ways and by these the path of truth will be profanely spoken of.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	In covetousness they will make gain out of you by their cunning words. But their condemnation from of old has not been inactive, and their destruction has not been sleeping.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For if God did not spare angels that had sinned, but thrust them down to Tartarus and committed them to pits of darkness to be kept for judgment,
B061C002V005	61	2	5	and did not spare the ancient world, but guarded Noah, a herald of righteousness, and seven others, when he brought the flood on the world of the ungodly;
B061C002V006	61	2	6	and if reducing to ashes the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah he condemned them to destruction, making them an example for the godless of what would come upon them,
B061C002V007	61	2	7	and rescued righteous Lot worn out by the indecent lives of the lawless, \'97
B061C002V008	61	2	8	for that righteous man living among them was tortured day and night in his righteous soul by the sight and hearing of their lawless deeds, \'97
B061C002V009	61	2	9	the Lord knows how to rescue the pious from trial and how to keep the wicked under punishment for the day of judgment,
B061C002V010	61	2	10	especially those who go after flesh in polluting passions, and despise lordship. They are daring, self-willed; they do not tremble to speak insultingly of glorious beings
B061C002V011	61	2	11	even where angels greater in strength and power do not bring against them an insulting charge before the Lord.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	But they, like irrational creatures, born mere animals for capture and destruction, while speaking profanely of things they are ignorant of, will be corrupted by their own corruption,
B061C002V013	61	2	13	and will suffer unrighteously as the reward of their own unrighteousness. They think it pleasure to revel in the daytime. They are spots and blots as they revel in their deceptions while they feast sumptuously with you.
B061C002V014	61	2	14	They have eyes engrossed with some adulteress, eyes which never cease from sin. They seduce unsteady souls. They have hearts practiced in covetousness. They are children of a curse.
B061C002V015	61	2	15	Leaving the straight path they have wandered away following the path of Balaam the son of Beor, who loved the wages of unrighteousness.
B061C002V016	61	2	16	But he was reproved for his sin; a dumb beast of draught, speaking with human voice, checked the madness of the prophet.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These men are springs without water, storm-driven mists for whom the blackness of darkness is reserved.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	For by speaking great empty swelling words they entrap in the passions of the flesh \'97 wanton excesses \'97 those who are nearly escaping from those who live in error.
B061C002V019	61	2	19	While they promise them liberty they themselves are the slaves of corruption; for by whatever any one is overcome to that he is enslaved.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if, after they have escaped the defilement of the world by the knowledge of the Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, they have been again entangled and overcome, their last state has become worse than the first.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	For it would be better for them not to have known the way of righteousness than after knowing it to turn back from the holy commandment that has been committed to them.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	That has happened to them which the true proverb says, "The dog returns to his own vomit and the sow after bathing returns to wallowing in the mire."
B061C003V001	61	3	1	THIS second letter, beloved, I am writing you. In both I have tried, by awakening your memory,
B061C003V002	61	3	2	to arouse your honest minds to recall the predictions of the holy prophets and the commands of your apostles from the Lord and Savior.
B061C003V003	61	3	3	First you should know this, that in the last days scoffers will come with their scoffing, living according to their own passions
B061C003V004	61	3	4	and saying, "Where is his promised coming? for since the fathers fell asleep all things remain as they have been since the beginning of the creation?"
B061C003V005	61	3	5	For they willfully forget that there were heavens of old and an earth formed out of water and through water by God's word.
B061C003V006	61	3	6	By these means the world that then was was flooded with water and destroyed.
B061C003V007	61	3	7	But the present heavens and the earth are by the same word treasured up and kept for fire on the day of judgment and destruction of ungodly men.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	Do not forget this one thing, beloved, that one day with the Lord is like a thousand years and a thousand years are like one day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	The Lord is not slow about what he has promised, as some think of slowness, but is long-suffering toward us, wishing not to have any perish but to have all come to a change of heart.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	But the day of the Lord will come like a thief. On that day the heavens will pass away with a loud noise and the burning elements will be dissolved and the earth and the things in it will not be found.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	Since all of these things are to be dissolved, what sort of persons ought you to be in holy lives and piety,
B061C003V012	61	3	12	you who are looking for and hastening toward the coming of the day of God, when the blazing heavens will be dissolved and the burning elements melted?
B061C003V013	61	3	13	But according to his promise we are expecting new heavens and a new earth in which righteousness will dwell.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	Therefore, beloved, since you expect this, endeavor earnestly to be found by him in peace, spotless and faultless,
B061C003V015	61	3	15	and regard the long-suffering of our Lord as salvation, as also our beloved brother Paul has written to you, according to the wisdom given to him.
B061C003V016	61	3	16	So he writes in all his letters when speaking in them of these things. In those letters are some things hard to understand, and these the unlearned and unsteady twist, as they do the rest of the Scriptures, to their own ruin.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	You, then, beloved, since you know these things beforehand, be on your guard not to be led away by the error of the lawless and fall from your own steadfastness,
B061C003V018	61	3	18	but grow in grace and in knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. To him be glory now and to the day of eternity!
B062C001V001	62	1	1	WHAT was from the beginning, what we have heard, what we have seen with our eyes, what we looked upon and our hands touched \'97 it is about the Word of Life
B062C001V002	62	1	2	
        
B062C001V003	62	1	3	what wo have seen and heard we are telling you also, so that you may have fellowship with us. And our fellowship is with the Father and with his Son Jesus Christ.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	We are writing this that our joy may be complete.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	This is the message which we have heard from him and tell to you, God is light and in him is no darkness at all.
B062C001V006	62	1	6	If we say, "We have fellowship with him," and live in darkness, we lie and are not acting the truth.
B062C001V007	62	1	7	If we live in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship with one another and the blood of Jesus his Son cleanses us from all sin.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	If we say, "We have no sin," we deceive ourselves and the truth is not in us.
B062C001V009	62	1	9	If we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us our sins and cleanse us from all unrighteousness:
B062C001V010	62	1	10	If we say, "We have not sinned," we make him a liar and his message is not in us.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	MY children, I am writing this to you in order that you may not sin. Even if any one sins, we have an advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ, who is righteous.
B062C002V002	62	2	2	And he is an atoning sacrifice for our sins, and not for ours only but for those of the whole world.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	By this we know that we have come to know him, if we keep his commands.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	He who says, "I know him," and does not keep his commands, is a liar and truth is not in him.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever keeps his word, truly in him the love of God has been made perfect. By this we know that we are in him.
B062C002V006	62	2	6	He who says that he is abiding in him ought himself to live as he lived.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	Beloved, I am not writing a new command for you, but an old command, which you have had from the beginning. The old command is the message that you have heard.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	Again I am writing a new command, which is true in him and in you, because the darkness is passing away and the true Light is already shining.
B062C002V009	62	2	9	He who says that he is in the light and hates his brother is in darkness still.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	He who loves his brother remains in the light and there is no stumbling block in him.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	He who hates his brother is in darkness and walks in darkness and knows not where he is going, because the darkness has blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I am writing to you, little children, because your sins have been forgiven for his name's sake.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I am writing to you, fathers, because you have come to know him who has been from the beginning. I am writing to you, young men, because you have conquered the Evil One. I have written to you, little children, because you have come to know the Father.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I have written to you, fathers, because you have come to know him who has been from the beginning. I have written to you, young men, because you are strong and the message of God remains in you and you have conquered the Evil One.
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Do not love the world nor the things that are in the world. If any one loves the world, the love of the Father is not in him;
B062C002V016	62	2	16	for all that is in the world, the passions of the flesh and the lust of the eyes and the show and pride of life, is not from the Father, but from the world.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	And the world is passing away with its passions. But he who does the will of God endures forever.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	Little children, it is the last hour, and as you have heard that Antichrist is coming, even now many Antichrists have arisen. By this we know that it is the last hour.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	They went out from us, but they were not of us, for if they had been of us they would have continued with us. But they went out so that it might be plainly seen that not all are of us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	You have an anointing from the Holy One and you all know.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I am not writing to you because you do not know the truth, but because you know it and know that no lie is from the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is a liar but he who denies that Jesus is the Christ? He is the Antichrist who denies the Father and the Son.
B062C002V023	62	2	23	No one who denies the Son has the Father either. He who confesses the Son has the Father also.
B062C002V024	62	2	24	Let what you have heard from the beginning remain in you. If what you have heard from the beginning remains in you, you also will remain in the Son and in the Father.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	And this is the promise that he has promised us \'97 the life eternal.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	I am writing this to you in regard to those who are misleading you.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	But as for you, the anointing that you have received from him remains in you and you have no need for any one to teach you, but as his anointing teaches you about all things and is true and is no lie and as it has taught you, you must remain in him.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	And now, little children, remain in him so that if he appears we may have confidence and not shrink in shame from him at his coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	If you know that he is righteous, you know that every one who does righteousness has been born of him.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	SEE what love the Father has bestowed on us that we should be called children of God. And so we are. The reason why tho world does not know us is that it did not know him.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	Beloved, we are now children of God and it is not yet plain what we shall be. But we know that if he appears we shall be like him, for we shall see him as he is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	And every one who has this hope set upon Christ purifies himself just as Christ is pure.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	Every one who commits sin commits also lawlessness; for sin is lawlessness.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	You know that Christ appeared to take away sins and in him there is no sin.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	Whoever remains in him does not sin; whoever sins has not seen him nor known him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	Little children, let no one deceive you. He who is doing righteousness is righteous as Christ is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	He who is committing sin is of the Devil, for the Devil has been sinning from the beginning. For this the Son of God appeared \'97 to undo the works of the Devil.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	No one who has been born of God commits sin, for God's life-giving germ remains in him and he cannot continue sinning, because he has been born of God.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	By this the children of God are plain to see, also the children of the Devil. Every one who is not doing righteousness is not of God, nor is he who does not love his brother.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	For this is the message which you have heard from the beginning, that we must love one another.
B062C003V012	62	3	12	Not like Cain, who was of the Wicked One and killed his brother. And for what reason did he kill him? Because his own deeds were wicked and his brother's righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	Do not be surprised, brethren, if the world hates you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	We know that we have passed from death into life because we love the brethren. Whoever does not love remains in death.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	Every one who hates his brother is a murderer, and you know that no murderer has life eternal remaining in him.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	By this we have come to know love \'97 that Christ laid down his life for us, and we ought to lay down our lives for the brethren.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	But if any one has this world's goods and sees his brother in need and shuts away his sympathies from him, how can the love of God remain in him?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	Let us not love in word or in tongue, but in deed and in truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	By this we shall know that we are of the truth and shall give confidence to our hearts in his presence,
B062C003V020	62	3	20	because if our hearts condemn us God is greater than our hearts and knows all things.
B062C003V021	62	3	21	Beloved, if our hearts do not condemn us we have confidence toward God,
B062C003V022	62	3	22	and whatever we ask we receive from him, because we keep his commands and do what is pleasing in his sight.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	And this is his command \'97 to believe in the name of his Son Jesus Christ and love one another as he has given us command.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	He who keeps his commands remains in God and God remains in him. By this we know that God remains in us \'97 by the Spirit which he has given to us.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	BELOVED, do not trust every spirit, but test the spirits whether they are from God. For many false prophets have come out into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	By this we know the Spirit of God: every spirit that confesses that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is from God,
B062C004V003	62	4	3	and no spirit that does not confess Jesus is from God. This is the spirit of Antichrist, which you have heard is coming into the world and is already in the world.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	But you are of God, little children, and have conquered them, because he who is in us is greater than he who is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	They belong to the world and for that reason they speak as the world speaks and the world listens to them.
B062C004V006	62	4	6	We are of God. Whoever knows God listens to us: whoever is not of God does not listen to us. In this way we know the spirit of truth and the spirit of error.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	Beloved, let us love one another, for love is from God, and every one who loves has been born of God and knows God.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	He who does not love does not know God; for God is love.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	By this the love of God to us was made plain: that God sent his only Son into the world so that we may have life through him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	In this is love \'97 not that we loved God, but that he loved us and sent his Son to be an atoning sacrifice for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	Beloved, if God has so loved us, we ought also to love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	No one has ever seen God. If we love one another God abides in us and his love is made perfect in us.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	By this we know that we abide in him and he in us, because he has imparted to us of his Spirit.
B062C004V014	62	4	14	We have seen and we bear witness that the Father has sent the Son to be the Savior of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	Whoever confesses that Jesus is the Son of God, God abides in him and he in God.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	We have come to know and have put our trust in the love which God has for us. God is love, and he who remains in love remains in God and God remains in him.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	Thus love has been made perfect with us so that we may have confidence on the day of judgment, because as God is we also are in this world.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	There is no fear in love, but perfect love casts out fear, because fear has pain. He who fears has not been made perfect in love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We love because he first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	If any one says, "I love God," and hates his brother, he is a liar. For he who does not love his brother whom he has seen cannot love God whom he has not seen.
B062C004V021	62	4	21	This command we have from him, that he who loves God shall love his brother also.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	EVERY one who believes that Jesus is the Christ has been born of God, and every one who loves the father who gave him life loves every one who has received life from that father.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God and do his commands.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	For this is the love of God, our keeping his commands. And his commands are not burden-some,
B062C005V004	62	5	4	because all that is born of God conquers the world. And this is the victory that conquers the world, our faith.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	Who is the conqueror of the world but he who believes that Jesus is the Son of God?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	This is he who came through water and blood, Jesus Christ. Not with the water only, but with the water and the blood. And the Spirit is the witness, because the Spirit is the truth.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	
        
B062C005V008	62	5	8	For there are three that bear witness, the Spirit and the water and the blood, and the three are in accord.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If we accept the testimony of men the testimony of God is greater; for this is God's testimony, that he has testified regarding his Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	He who believes in the Son of God has the testimony within himself. He who does not believe God has made him a liar; because he has not believed the testimony which God has borne regarding his Son.
B062C005V011	62	5	11	This is the testimony: that God has given to us life eternal and this life is in his Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	He who has the Son has life; he who has not the Son of God has not life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	I am writing this to you so that you may know that you have life eternal, you who believe in the name of the Son of God.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	This is the confidence that we have toward him: that if we ask anything according to his will he hears us.
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And if we know that he hears us when we ask anything, we know that we obtain the things that we have asked of him.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	If any one sees his brother committing a sin that is not deadly, he must ask and God will give him life for those who are committing sin that is not deadly. There is sin that is deadly. I do not say that he should pray in behalf of that.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	All unrighteousness is sin, and there is sin that is not deadly.
B062C005V018	62	5	18	We know that every one who has been born of God lives without sinning, but he who was born of God keeps him, and the Evil One does not lay hold of him.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	We know that we are of God and the whole world lies in the Evil One.
B062C005V020	62	5	20	We know that the Son of God has come and has given us understanding to know him who is true, and we are in him who is true and in his Son, Jesus Christ. This is the true God and life eternal.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	Little children, guard yourselves from idols.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	THE Elder to the chosen Lady and her children, whom I love in truth 
B063C001V002	63	1	2	for the sake of the truth which remains in us and will be with us forever:
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace, mercy, and peace will be with us from God the Father and from Jesus Christ, the Son of the Father, in truth and love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	I rejoiced greatly to find some of your children living in truth, as we received command from the Father.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	And now I pray you, Lady, not as if writing a new command for you, but one that we have had from the beginning, let us love one another.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	This is love: to live by his commands. This is the command, as you heard from the beginning that you must live by it.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	For many deceivers have come out into the world and they do not confess that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh. Such a one is the deceiver and the Antichrist.
B063C001V008	63	1	8	Guard yourselves so as not to lose what we have worked for, but so that you may gain a full reward.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	Every one who goes forward and does not remain in the teaching of Christ is without God. He who remains in the teaching, he has the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If any one comes to you and does not bring this teaching, do not take him into your house and do not bid him welcome.
B063C001V011	63	1	11	He who bids him welcome becomes a sharer in his wicked works.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	I have much to write to you, but I will not do it with paper and ink. I hope to be with you soon and to speak face to face so that our joy may be complete.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The children of your chosen sister send greetings to you.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	THE Elder to Gaius the beloved, whom I love in truth:
B064C001V002	64	1	2	Beloved, I pray that in everything you may prosper and be in health, just as your soul now prospers.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For I rejoiced greatly when brethren came and testified to your truth \'97 that you are living in the truth.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	I have no greater joy than this: to hear that my children are living in the truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	Beloved, you do faithfully whatever work you do for the brethren, even when they are strangers,
B064C001V006	64	1	6	and they have testified to your love before the church. You will do well to help them forward on their journey in a manner worthy of God.
B064C001V007	64	1	7	For it was for the Name that they came out, taking nothing from the Gentiles.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	We ought to help such men so as to be fellow workers with the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I wrote something to the church; but Diotrephes, who desires to be first among them, does not receive us.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	Therefore, if I come I will bring to mind the works that he is doing, accusing us with wicked words, and not satisfied with that, neither does he receive the brethren, and he hinders those who wish to do so and expels them from the church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	Beloved, do not imitate evil, but good. He who does good is of God. He who does evil has not seen God.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	Testimony has been borne to Demetrius by all and by the truth itself. We too bear testimony, and you know that our testimony is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	I had much to write to you, but I will not write to you with ink and pen.
B064C001V014	64	1	14	But I hope to see you shortly, and we shall speak face to face. Peace be to you. The friends send greetings to you. Greet the friends by name.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	JUDE, a servant of Jesus Christ and a brother of James, to those who are in God the Father, beloved, kept for Jesus Christ and called:
B065C001V002	65	1	2	Mercy and peace and love be multiplied to you.
B065C001V003	65	1	3	Beloved, although I have been making every effort to write to you regarding our common salvation, I now find it necessary to write and urge you to contend vigorously for the faith that was once for all delivered to the holy.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For certain persons have crept in, who of old were written of as predestined to this doom, godless, changing the grace of our God into profligacy and disowning our only Ruler and Lord, Jesus Christ.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	I wish to remind you, although you know all things once for all, that the Lord, after saving a people from the land of Egypt, then destroyed those who had no faith;
B065C001V006	65	1	6	and angels who did not keep their own rank, but left their own abode, he has kept for the judgment of the great day in everlasting chains under blackness of darkness.
B065C001V007	65	1	7	So Sodom and Gomorrah, and the cities around them, which in the same way gave themselves up to unchastity and the pursuit of unnatural vices, serve as an example while they undergo the punishment of eternal fire.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	Just so these dreamers defile the flesh, reject government, and speak abusively of glorious beings.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	But Michael, the arch-angel, when in dispute with the Devil he was arguing about the body of Moses, did not venture to bring against him an abusive judgment, but said, "The Lord rebuke you."
B065C001V010	65	1	10	But these speak profanely of whatever they do not know, and all that physically as irrational animals they do understand, in these things they corrupt themselves.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	Alas for them! for they have traveled in the path of Cain, and for hire have rushed headlong into the error of Balaam, and have perished in the rebellious talk of Korah.
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These are the hidden reefs in your love-feasts while they feast freely with you without fear, shepherds who care only for themselves, waterless clouds driven by winds, trees in autumn fruitless, twice dead, uprooted,
B065C001V013	65	1	13	wild waves of the sea foaming out their own shame, wandering stars for which the blackness of darkness is reserved forever.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	Enoch, the seventh from Adam, prophesied of these men when he said, "See, the Lord has come with ten thousand of his holy ones
B065C001V015	65	1	15	to do judgment upon all and to convict all the irreverent of all their deeds of irreverence which they have irreverently done, and of all the hard things which they have spoken against him, irreverent sinners that they are."
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These men are complaining grumblers, living according to their own passions, and their mouths speak great swelling words. They show admiration for persons for the sake of their own gain.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But you, beloved, remember the words which were long ago spoken by the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B065C001V018	65	1	18	how they told you that in the latter time there would be scoffers living according to their own ungodly passions.
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are those who cause divisions, sensual and unspiritual.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, beloved, building yourselves up in your most holy faith and praying in the Holy Spirit,
B065C001V021	65	1	21	must keep yourselves in the love of God, looking for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ to bring you into life eternal.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	On some have pity when they are in doubt;
B065C001V023	65	1	23	pull them out of the fire and save them. Others pity with fear, hating even the tunic spotted by the flesh.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	To him who is able to guard you from falling and to make you stand faultless before his glory in great joy,
B065C001V025	65	1	25	to the only God our Savior, be, through Jesus Christ our Lord, glory, majesty, might, and authority, before all time and now and for all the ages! Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	A REVELATION of Jesus Christ which God gave to him, to make known to his servants things which must soon take place. He sent and made it known through his angel to his servant John,
B066C001V002	66	1	2	who bears witness to the message of God and the testimony of Jesus Christ \'97 everything that he saw.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	Blessed is he who reads, and blessed are those who hear the words of this prophecy and keep in mind what is written in it; for the time is near.
B066C001V004	66	1	4	John to the seven Churches in Asia: Grace be to you and peace from him who is and who was and who is to come, and from the seven Spirits that are before his throne,
B066C001V005	66	1	5	and from Jesus Christ, the faithful witness, the first-born of the dead, and the ruler of the kings of the earth. To him who loves us and freed us from our sins by his blood,
B066C001V006	66	1	6	and made us a kingdom, priests to God his Father, to him be glory and power for the ages of the ages! Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	He is coming with clouds and every eye will see him, even of those who pierced him, and all the tribes of the earth will beat their breasts because of him. Yes, Amen.
B066C001V008	66	1	8	
        
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I, John, your brother and fellow sharer in the distresses and the kingdom and the endurance in Jesus, came to the island called Patmos, for the sake of the message of God and the testimony of Jesus.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	I became in the Spirit on the Lord's day and heard behind me a loud voice, as of a trumpet,
B066C001V011	66	1	11	saying, 
B066C001V012	66	1	12	I turned to see the voice that was speaking with me, and upon turning I saw seven golden lampstands
B066C001V013	66	1	13	and in the midst of the lampstands one like a son of man, clothed in a robe that reached his feet, and girded across the breast with a golden girdle.
B066C001V014	66	1	14	His head and his hair were white, like white wool, like snow, and his eyes were like a flame of fire,
B066C001V015	66	1	15	and his feet were like fine brass when molten in a furnace, and his voice was like the sound of many waters.
B066C001V016	66	1	16	He had in his right hand seven stars, and from his mouth there issued a sharp two-edged sword. His face was like the sun shining in full strength.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	When I saw him I fell at his feet as if dead. But he laid his right hand on me and said: 
