B066C004V001	66	4	1	AFTER this I looked and there was an open door in heaven and the voice that I had heard at first, as if of a trumpet speaking with me, said, "Come up here and I will show you things that must come to pass hereafter."
B066C004V002	66	4	2	Immediately I became in the Spirit. A throne was standing in heaven and on the throne One was sitting.
B066C004V003	66	4	3	He who was sitting there was in appearance like a jasper stone and a sardius. A rainbow, in appearance like an emerald, encircled the throne.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	Around the throne I saw twenty-four thrones and on these thrones twenty-four elders seated, clothed in white garments and with golden crowns on their heads.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	From the throne issued lightnings and voices and thunders. There were seven lamps of fire burning before the throne. These are the seven Spirits of God.
B066C004V006	66	4	6	Before the throne there was as it were a glassy sea, like crystal. Near the throne and around the throne there were four living creatures full of eyes before and behind.
B066C004V007	66	4	7	The first living creature was like a lion, the second living creature was like a calf, the third living creature had a face like a man's, and the fourth living creature was like a flying eagle.
B066C004V008	66	4	8	The four living creatures have each six wings, and around and within they are full of eyes. They cease not saying day and night, "Holy, holy, holy is the Lord God Almighty, who was and is and is to come."
B066C004V009	66	4	9	And when the living creatures give glory and honor and thanks to him who sits on the throne, who lives for the ages of the ages,
B066C004V010	66	4	10	the twenty-four elders fall down before him who sits on the throne and worship him who lives for the ages of the ages, and they cast their crowns before the throne saying,
B066C004V011	66	4	11	"Worthy art thou, our Lord and God, to receive glory and honor and power, for thou didst create all things and because of thy will they existed and were created."
B066C005V001	66	5	1	THEN I saw in the right hand of him who was sitting on the throne a book with writing inside and outside and closely sealed with seven seals.
B066C005V002	66	5	2	I saw a strong angel proclaiming with a loud voice, "Who is worthy to open the book and loose its seals?"
B066C005V003	66	5	3	But no one in heaven or on the earth or under the earth was able to open the book or to look into it.
B066C005V004	66	5	4	I wept much because no one was found worthy to open the book or to look into it.
B066C005V005	66	5	5	Then one of the elders said to me, "Do not weep. The Lion of the tribe of Judah, the Root of David, has conquered and can open the book and its seven seals."
B066C005V006	66	5	6	Then I saw midway between the throne and the four living creatures and the elders a Lamb standing. He seemed as if he had been slain. He had seven horns and seven eyes which are the seven Spirits of God sent forth into all the earth.
B066C005V007	66	5	7	He came and took the book from the right hand of him who was sitting on the throne.
B066C005V008	66	5	8	When he took the book the four living creatures and the twenty-four elders fell down before the Lamb, each having a harp and a golden bowl full of incense, which is the prayers of the holy.
B066C005V009	66	5	9	Then they sang a new song, saying, "Worthy art thou to take the book and to open its seals, for thou wast slain and didst ransom for God by thy blood men from every tribe and tongue and people and nation,
B066C005V010	66	5	10	and hast made them a kingdom of priests to our God, and they shall be kings on the earth."
B066C005V011	66	5	11	Then I looked and I heard the voices of many angels encircling the throne and the voices of the four living creatures and of the elders \'97 the number of them was myriads of myriads and thousands of thousands \'97
B066C005V012	66	5	12	crying aloud, "Worthy is the Lamb who was slain to receive power and riches and wisdom and strength and honor and glory and blessing."
B066C005V013	66	5	13	And every creature that is in heaven and on the earth and under the earth and on the sea, and all creatures in them, I heard saying, "To him who sits on the throne and to the Lamb be blessing and honor and glory and power for the ages of the ages."
B066C005V014	66	5	14	The four living creatures said, "Amen," and the elders fell down and worshiped.
B066C006V001	66	6	1	THEN I saw when the Lamb opened one of the seven seals and I heard one of the living creatures say, as if with a voice of thunder, "Come."
B066C006V002	66	6	2	I looked and there came a white horse, and he who was sitting on it had a bow, and a crown was given to him and he went forth conquering and to conquer.
B066C006V003	66	6	3	When he opened the second seal I heard the second living creature say, "Come."
B066C006V004	66	6	4	Then another horse came out. It was fiery red, and to him who was sitting on it was granted to take peace from the earth so that men should kill one another, and a great sword was given to him.
B066C006V005	66	6	5	When he opened the third seal I heard the third living creature say, "Come." I looked and there came a black horse, and he who was sitting on it had a pair of scales in his hand.
B066C006V006	66	6	6	I heard what seemed a voice in the midst of the four living creatures saying, "A measure of wheat for a shilling and three measures of barley for a shilling. But do no harm to the oil or the wine."
B066C006V007	66	6	7	When he opened the fourth seal I heard the voice of the fourth living creature say, "Come."
B066C006V008	66	6	8	I looked and there came a pale yellow horse. The name of him who was sitting on it was Death, and Hades was following along with him. Authority was granted to them over one fourth of the earth, to kill with the sword and with famine and with pestilence and with the wild beasts of the earth.
B066C006V009	66	6	9	When he opened the fifth seal, I saw under the altar the souls of those who had been slain for the sake of God's message and because of the testimony which they had borne.
B066C006V010	66	6	10	They cried with a loud voice, saying, "How long, O Ruler holy and true, wilt thou delay to judge and take vengeance for our blood upon those who dwell on the earth?"
B066C006V011	66	6	11	To each of them a white robe was given, and it was said to them that they must wait quietly yet a little while until the number of their fellow servants and their brethren was complete, who were yet to be killed as they had been.
