B066C015V006	66	15	6	and the seven angels with the seven last plagues came out of the Temple, clothed in pure shining linen and girded around their breasts with golden girdles.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	One of the four living creatures gave to the seven angels seven golden bowls filled with the wrath of God who lives for the ages of the ages.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	The Temple was filled with smoke from the glory of God and from his power, and no one could enter the Temple until the seven plagues of the seven angels were finished.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	THEN I heard a loud voice saying from the Temple to the seven angels, "Go and pour out the seven bowls of the wrath of God upon the earth."
B066C016V002	66	16	2	The first went away and poured his bowl upon the land, and there came an evil and malignant ulcer on the men who had the mark of the Beast and those who worshiped its image.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	The second angel poured out his bowl upon the sea, and it became blood like that of a dead man and every living thing that was in the sea died.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	The third angel poured out his bowl upon the rivers and the springs of water, and they became blood.
B066C016V005	66	16	5	Then I heard the angel of the waters saying, "Just art thou who art and wast, the Holy One, because thou hast so judged,
B066C016V006	66	16	6	for they poured out the blood of thy holy ones and prophets and thou hast given them blood to drink. They deserve it."
B066C016V007	66	16	7	Then I heard the altar saying, "Yes, O Lord God Almighty, true and just are thy judgments."
B066C016V008	66	16	8	The fourth angel poured out his bowl on the sun, and it was granted to him to scorch men with fire.
