B066C021V001	66	21	1	THEN I saw a new heaven and a new earth, for the first heaven and the first earth had passed away and the sea was no more.
B066C021V002	66	21	2	I saw the holy city, new Jerusalem, descending out of heaven from God, prepared as a bride adorned for her husband.
B066C021V003	66	21	3	And I heard a loud voice from the throne saying, "The Tent of God is with men. He will tent with them and they will be his people and he will be their God.
B066C021V004	66	21	4	He will wipe every tear from their eyes. Death shall be no more; neither shall there any longer be sorrow or wailing or painful toil; for the first things have passed away."
B066C021V005	66	21	5	He who was sitting on the throne said, "See, I am making all things new." He said, "Write; for these words are trustworthy and true."
B066C021V006	66	21	6	He said to me, "They have come to pass. I am the Alpha and the Omega, the beginning and the end. To him who is thirsting I will give from the spring of the water of life freely.
